title: diane's rice and spinach casserole
directions: Saute onions and garlic in 1/4 cup oil.
Add rice and lightly brown.
Add chicken stock or broth.
Stir spinach into rice mixture.
Add Parmesan cheese; salt and pepper to taste.
Place in casserole and cook at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: old-fashioned meat loaf
directions: Combine all ingredients (except cheese) and shape into a loaf (for an 8 x 4-inch loaf pan) or put ingredients into a 9 or 10-inch pie dish or ring mold.
(Cheese could be added to top the last 10 to 15 minutes of baking time.)

title: hot chocolate mix
directions: Mix ingredients and store in refrigerator.
When ready to serve, place 3 tablespoons of mix in a cup.
Add boiling water and stir.

title: sweet potato apple casserole
directions: Steam the sweet potatoes in 1/2 cup water, 15 to 20 minutes until tender.
Peel and slice lengthwise in 1/2-inch slices. Layer in casserole.
Peel and core apples. Slice 1/2-inch thick and lay on top of the sweet potatoes.
Heat juice to a boil. Combine cornstarch and water.
Add to juice.
Cook until clear and thickened.
Add honey.
Pour sauce over apples and top with 1/3 cup wheat germ. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until apples are done.

title: carrot loaf
directions: Cook enough carrots to make 1 1/2 cup mashed carrots.
Save liquid.
Mix ingredients in order given.
Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites.
Bake in casserole place in a pan of water.
Bake 1/2 hour at 350°.

title: microwave pizza casserole
directions: Microwave:
In a 2-quart casserole dish, microwave the ground beef for 3 1/2 minutes.
Stir and microwave another 2 1/2 minutes or until done.
Drain thoroughly.
Add remaining ingredients except cheese.
Mix well.
Cook 17 minutes on High, stirring twice. Sprinkle cheese on top and cook 1 minute on High until cheese melts.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Line a 7 x 11-inch pan with sliced peaches.
Make a batter of the next 7 ingredients.
Pour over the peaches and spread evenly. Mix 1 cup of sugar and 1/2 cup of water together and pour over the batter.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: parmesan chicken
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Spray 15 x 10-inch pan with nonstick spray. Combine butter, Parmesan and bread crumbs into a spread.
Dip chicken in spread; coat with combined remaining ingredients.
Place in pan.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes until tender.

title: seven minute frosting
directions: Combine all ingredients in double boiler.
Beat with rotary beater or mixer, about 1 minute or until well mixed.
Cook over boiling water, beating constantly, until frosting stands in stiff peaks.
Add 1 teaspoon vanilla.

title: salsa
directions: Place onion, pepper and garlic in a 2-quart bowl.
Microwave on High for 3 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients and toss.
Cover and chill.
Serve with fresh baked tortilla chips.

title: hawaiian chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 275°.
Place chicken in shallow pan, skin side up.
Mix all remaining ingredients and pour over chicken.
Bake, uncovered, 2 hours.
Serve with rice.

title: super cheese ball
directions: Soften cheeses, then blend all ingredients together and blend well.
Roll, swash and make into round ball, then roll in finely chopped pecans.
Serve with crackers.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Chill and stir again before serving.

title: chicken rice medley
directions: Place chicken in a shallow, buttered 2 1/2-quart baking dish. Bake, uncovered, at 450° for 30 minutes or until browned.

title: dip for fruit
directions: Mix both ingredients in food processor and blend until creamy and smooth.
Add food coloring if desired.

title: potato soup
directions: Cut potatoes in small cubes.
Pour in water and cook until tender on low heat.
Put milk, salt, pepper, chives and butter in and bring to a slow boil.
Cook for approximately 3 minutes.
Good plain or garnished with grated cheese.

title: chicken in ros sauce
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt 2 tablespoons margarine in baking pan; add chicken breasts and bake for 30 minutes.
Melt remaining margarine in a saucepan.
Add flour and cook briefly, stirring. Add chicken broth and wine, stirring constantly until sauce is thick and smooth.
Remove chicken breasts from oven; turn and cover each with sliced mushrooms, green onion and artichokes. Pour sauce over all and bake for 30 minutes or until tender.

title: easy key lime pie
directions: In large bowl, beat milk and lime juice on high speed with an electric mixer until smooth and thickened.	Fold in whipped topping, spoon mixture into pie crust.
Cover and refrigerate about one hour or until set.
Garnish with lime peel.

title: fire department commodity cake
directions: Combine flour, sugar and baking powder; slightly beat 3 eggs and add to flour mixture.
Melt 2 sticks of butter and add to mix. Add milk and vanilla.
Bake at 375° to 400° until done.
Grease and flour pan.

title: veal in sour cream
directions: Brown veal in butter and place in casserole.
Cover tightly. Add 3 tablespoons water to frypan which has been used to brown veal.
Blend in flour; stir until smooth.
Slowly add sour cream, stirring constantly.
When thick, add seasonings and mushrooms which have been sauteed in butter.
Pour over veal.
Bake for 1 hour in a 350° oven that has been preheated.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream butter and add sugar.
Add egg and vanilla.
Next, add flour, baking soda and chips.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: cornbread salad
directions: Mix mayonnaise, mustard and salad dressing.
Pour over remaining ingredients and mix well.
Chill before serving.

title: potato casserole
directions: Thaw potatoes; mix with other ingredients.
Place into a 13 x 9-inch pan.

title: mandarin orange mold
directions: Drain juice from oranges and pineapple.
Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water.
Add drained fruit juices.
Cool and refrigerate until consistency of unbeaten eggs.
Add fruit and orange sherbet. Mix thoroughly and put in 12-cup mold.
Fill ring with cottage cheese for luncheon.
Serves 10.

title: mama's chicken pie
directions: Line
baking dish with pastry.	Melt margarine in large saucepan over medium heat.	Add flour, salt and pepper.
Blend together and add milk and chicken broth to consistency of thin gravy.
Place
boiled,
cut
up chicken in pastry.	Cover with sauce.
Cover
with
top crust; sprinkle with black pepper and dot with butter and bake in moderate oven until brown.

title: basil sauce for pasta
directions: Saute garlic and onion in oil until soft.
Add basil and salt. Stir for 2 minutes.
Take from heat and add tomatoes.
Serve over favorite pasta.

title: red beans and rice
directions: Rinse and sort beans.
Put all ingredients in a large kettle and cover with water.
Simmer 3 to 4 hours until beans are tender. Add water, if needed, while cooking.
Serve over cooked rice, using pot liquids.
Good with cornbread.

title: steak and kidney pie
directions: Saute beef and kidney with onion in large skillet.
Add salt and pepper.
Bring to boil.
Reduce heat and simmer covered for 45 minutes.
Add potatoes; return mixture to boiling and simmer covered for 20 minutes longer or until potatoes and meat are tender.

title: chuck wagon casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 400°. Put onions and bell peppers in skillet and cook. Add ground beef and cook 8 to 10 minutes longer. Drain. Stir in chili beans, barbecue sauce and salt. Bring to boil. Spoon into baking dish that has been sprayed with Pam. Prepare corn muffin mix according to mix directions. Stir in corn. Spoon over meat mixture. Bake 30 minutes or until golden brown.

title: peanut kisses(these are molded cookies)
directions: You will need ungreased cookie sheet.

title: gaumies
directions: Melt caramels and evaporated milk over low heat.
Hand stir cake mixture and spread half in greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 6 minutes.
Spread chocolate chips on top. Spread caramel mixture over and pat on remaining cake.
Bake 18 minutes.
Cool, then refrigerate for 30 minutes.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Form into a loaf and put in baking pan.
Bake at 400° for 1 hour.

title: low carb stuffed mushrooms
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees. Clean mushrooms with cloth. Remove stems and use a paring knife to make the hole for stuffing larger. Brown and drain the sausage. Crumble sausage and stir in the cream cheese. Spoon mixture into the mushroom caps. Bake for 20 minutes. May sprinkle with grated parmesan cheese if desired. Yield: about 30 mushrooms.

title: potato soup
directions: Cook bacon and keep grease.
Cook onion in grease until clear. Remove onion.
Gradually add flour, stirring constantly to avoid lumps.
Cook until golden brown.
Add chicken stock and stir with a whisk.
Turn heat to low, add potatoes, bacon, cream and spices. Simmer 10 minutes.
Add cheese and onion.
Stir until melted. Add hot sauce to taste.

title: overnight egg casserole
directions: Beat eggs, add milk, mustard, salt and pepper.
Put bread cubes in 13 x 9-inch pan.
Sprinkle meat on top, then pour egg mixture over top.
Sprinkle cheese on top.
Put in refrigerator overnight. In the morning, bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: spicy chicken casserole
directions: Prepare rice according to package directions. In a large bowl combine rice, cooked chicken, salsa and 3/4 cup cheese.
In a small bowl stir together sour cream and mayonnaise.
Add to rice mixture.
Place mixture in casserole dish.
Put remainder of cheese and crumbled corn chips on top.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes or until bubbly.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add vanilla and bananas.
Add flour, baking powder and salt.
Add baking soda and sour cream which have been mixed together.
Last, add the nuts.
Bake in loaf pan at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Cream together butter and sugar. Add eggs and mix well.
Add vanilla and almond extract.
Mix together flour, baking soda and cream of tartar. Add flour mixture to butter mixture; mix well. Refrigerate dough for 1 hour.
Roll out cookies (using more flour, if needed) and cut out with cookie cutters. Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: cherry fluff
directions: Mix all ingredients. Chill and serve.

title: congo squares
directions: Melt butter.
Add brown sugar, eggs and vanilla. Add dry ingredients and mix well.
Add chocolate chips and nuts.
Bake for 20 to 25 minutes at 375°.

title: strawberry pudding
directions: Heat Jell-O, sugar and berries to dissolve Jell-O, stirring constantly.
Cool, mix pudding and milk.
Add sour cream, fold in 3/4 Cool
Whip.

title: vegetable-burger soup
directions: In large saucepan, brown meat.
Drain off fat.
Stir in 4 cups water and remaining ingredients.
Bring to boiling.
Add 2 more cups of water.
Reduce heat; cover and simmer for 20 minutes.

title: sweet popcorn
directions: Mix corn and nuts together.
Cook sugar, margarine, syrup and salt.
Bring to a boil over medium heat; then turn down and continue to boil 5 minutes.
Remove from heat and add 1 teaspoon vanilla.
Pour over popped corn.
Spread on a cookie sheet and let cool.

title: strawberry cheesecake trifle
directions: In a large bowl, cream together cream cheese and sugar. Add sour cream,
vanilla
and almond extract; set aside.
In a small deep bowl,	whip cream, vanilla and sugar.	Fold whipped cream into cream	cheese	mix.
Add cake pieces and set aside. Starting with
strawberries,
layer	cake
mixture
and strawberries (1/3 mixture for each layer).
Cover with plastic wrap and refrigerate.

title: arkansas travelers
directions: Cream butter.
Add vanilla and sugar.
Beat in eggs.
Mix thoroughly.
Add peanut butter.
Sift in flour and baking powder. Roll into small balls and place on greased cookie sheet.
Flatten with tines of a fork that has been dipped in water.
Bake in moderate oven at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes about 5 dozen.

title: toasted pecan supreme 4 layer pie
directions: Step 1:
Mix and press flour, pecan pieces and melted butter in long cake pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cool thoroughly!

title: scalloped potatoes and ham
directions: Place cooked potatoes in an 8 x 8 x 2-inch dish.
Toss 1 tablespoon margarine with bread crumbs, paprika and thyme; set aside.
Blend flour, mustard and pepper into 2 tablespoons margarine.
Add reserved potato water and milk.
Cook and stir until thickened and bubbly.
Stir in ham and cut up cheese.
Cook until cheese is melted.
Place onion rings over potatoes.
Pour sauce over onions and potatoes.
Sprinkle with crumbs.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: noel fudge
directions: Combine the wafers and milk in the top of a double boiler and melt over hot, not boiling water.
Chop fruit and nuts and add. Pour into buttered plate and chill for 15 to 20 minutes and it's ready to eat.

title: cranberry bread
directions: Heat oven to 350°. Grease bottom only of two loaf pans.
Mix flour, sugar, brown sugar, baking powder, salt, oil, milk and egg. Stir in nuts and cranberry halves.

title: irish creme
directions: Blend all ingredients in blender.
Pour into glass container and refrigerate up to 6 weeks.
Before serving, shake well.
Serve as is or in coffee.

title: greek spinach pie
directions: Preheat the oven to 375°. Coat a 9 x 13-inch baking dish with nonstick cooking spray.

title: cooking "red beans supreme and rice" with the rice family
directions: Wash pork chops and dry with a paper towel.
Season both sides to taste with salt, pepper and cayenne pepper.
Place chops in a bag with flour and shake until chops are covered.
Remove excess flour from chops.
Add 1 cup of oil, depending on size of frying pan.
Heat on medium.
Place chops in frying pan; fry until golden brown on both sides.
Remove chops and place on paper towels to drain.
At this point, remove oil and make gravy or you can cheat, remove oil and add Pepperidge Farm brown gravy to frying pan.
Add chops and let simmer 15 to 30 minutes, depending on thickness of the chops.
Note:
Gravy should cover chops.

title: delicious candy
directions: Boil until mixture forms firm ball, 238°.
Beat and beat and beat and beat.
Add 1 cup nut meats and flour.

title: lemon curd
directions: Beat eggs; add sugar and then strained lemon juice.
Cook in double boiler or in microwave bowl in microwave oven.
Add butter, cut in small pieces, as soon as mixture is hot.
Cook until thick.
Cool and store in refrigerator.
Keeps for several months.

title: chocolate supreme bars
directions: Melt butter and peanut butter in saucepan, stirring frequently.
Add marshmallows and cereal; stir until marshmallows start to melt and stick to cereal.
Remove from heat.
Press mixture firmly into buttered 8-inch square pan.
Chill about an hour.
Cut into squares.

title: layered pea salad
directions: Layer vegetables
starting
with
lettuce
in casserole dish or salad bowl.
Mix
mayonnaise, vinegar, lemon juice and sugar together and pour over
peas.
Top with cheese and bacon bits.

title: chocolate delight
directions: Mix together and pat out in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan and bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: pineapple cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together with spoon.
Butter a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: carrot cake
directions: Bake cake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: banana bread
directions: Grease and flour 8 x 4-inch loaf pan.
Combine flour, soda, salt and baking powder in bowl.
Cream shortening and sugars in 3-quart bowl until fluffy.
Add eggs, 1 at a time, and beat well. Stir in bananas and 1/2 cup walnut meats if prefer.
Add flour mixture in 4 portions; beat until smooth.
Bake in prepared pan for 50 minutes or until inserted tester comes out clean at 350°.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into casserole dish. Bake uncovered at 350 degrees for 40 minutes.

title: sausage egg casserole
directions: Mix all in a bowl.
Grease a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Pour into and let stand overnight in refrigerator.
Bake next morning at 350° for 1 hour until firm, 30 to 45 minutes.

title: barbecued spareribs
directions: Brown spareribs on all sides. Combine remaining ingredients and pour over ribs.

title: hamburger jiffy noodles
directions: Sear meat and onions in fat until all the red is out of meat, turning frequently.
Cook noodles about 10 minutes; strain. Spread over the meat and onions in pan.
Pour warmed tomato sauce over noodles.
Cover skillet and simmer 20 minutes over low heat. Do not stir too much.

title: million dollar fudge
directions: Boil sugar, milk and butter for 5 minutes.
Pour over chocolate bits, chocolate Hershey bars and marshmallow cream. Stir and beat until smooth.
Pour into buttered pans and cool. Cut into squares.
Makes almost 5 pounds.

title: now and later dessert
directions: Line bottom of 13 x 9-inch baking pan with sliced pound cake. Mix cream cheese and 1/4 cup sugar, dash of almond extract and enough milk to make the consistency of whipped topping; set aside. Mix pudding with remaining milk; add cream cheese mixture. Spread over pound cake.
Mix pie filling and 1/4 cup sugar. Spread over cream cheese mixture.
Top with Cool Whip.
Can use different pie fillings and flavors of pudding.

title: banana cake
directions: Cream sugar and shortening; add eggs.
Sift together flour and other dry ingredients.
Add to creamed mixture with milk and bananas; add vanilla.
Beat until smooth.
Bake in 3 greased and floured 9-inch cakes pans at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Good with Creamy Nut Frosting.

title: chicken nuggets
directions: Cube chicken breast.
Dip in milk, coat with flavored bread crumbs.
Cook over medium heat for 11 to 14 minutes.
Serve with rice, French fries or baked potatoes.
Serves 4.

title: stroganoff sauce
directions: Heat butter or margarine in a heavy pan; add onion and saute until onion is limp. Stir in flour and cook until blended and bubbly. Slowly stir in broth and cook, stirring until thickened. Mix in sour cream, dill weed, salt and pepper to taste. Do not let sauce boil after sour cream has been added. Reheat over low heat, stirring constantly, just to boiling point. Makes about 3 1/2 to 4 cups.

title: fruit dip
directions: Mix and eat with apples, bananas and pears or pretzels.

title: pineapple pie
directions: Stir with a spoon. Reserve 3/4
cup for topping. Press into a 9-inch pie pan and bake at 400°.

title: spring pea salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together.

title: chicken potato soup
directions: Add to large cooking pot the amount of water, or the amount of soup, you desire. Boil chicken 1-2 hours in pot with water to get the broth. Remove chicken from water and remove bones and skin. Cut up potatoes and chicken and add to the broth. Add seasonings to taste, and regular salt if desired. Boil for 1 to 1-1/2 hours. Add milk to your liking.

title: divinity candy or frosting
directions: Cook the first 4 ingredients until hard ball in cold water or soft crack on thermometer.
While it is cooking, beat egg whites until stiff.
When mixture gets ready, beat egg whites in, a little at a time, and beat until it loses its gloss.
When it starts thickening, add nuts, then beat.
Put on wax paper by tablespoons.

title: czeck potato dumplings
directions: Add eggs, salt and flour to cooled mashed potatoes.
Knead lightly.
Form into golf ball size.
Drop in boiling water.
Boil 10 to 15 minutes (covered).

title: leslie's sausage balls
directions: Combine sausage, cheese, milk and egg in bowl.
Mix well.
Add Bisquick and Lipton onion soup; mix well.
Roll into small balls. Put on cookie sheet and bake at 375° for 15 minutes or until golden brown.

title: coffee cake
directions: Mix first 8 ingredients together.
Put one-half of batter into pan.
Mix together brown sugar and cinnamon.
Sprinkle on top of batter in pan.
Add other half of batter.
Bake 1 hour at 325°.

title: baked popcorn
directions: Pop 4 quarts popcorn.
Boil butter, brown sugar and syrup for 5 minutes.
Add baking soda and cream of tartar to the butter and sugar mixture.
Pour over popcorn.
Stir until well mixed.
Spread on cookie sheet and bake at 225° for 1 hour.
Stir every 15 minutes.

title: watergate salad
directions: Mix pudding and crushed pineapple.
Mix with rest of ingredients.
Chill.

title: oyster casserole
directions: Place oysters in a 10 x 6 x 2-inch baking dish or a 9-inch pie plate.
Sprinkle with parsley and green onions.
Combine crumbs and remaining ingredients, stirring well.
Sprinkle over casserole. Bake uncovered at 450° for 10 to 15 minutes or until edges begin to curl.
Serve immediately.

title: "could-be bojangles" biscuits
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients, blending well.
Cut in shortening.
Stir in buttermilk.
Dough will be sticky.
Knead lightly 4 to 5 times; then roll out to 1/2-inch thickness on a lightly floured surface.
Cut into biscuits.
Bake at 450° for 12 minutes or until golden brown.
Brush tops with melted butter.

title: chicken tetrazzini
directions: Melt margarine in a large saucepan over medium heat. Add mushrooms and onion and saute 7 minutes or until liquid evaporates. Stir in all-purpose flour. Gradually add chicken broth, skim milk and cream cheese. Bring to a boil and cook 5 minutes, stirring constantly. Remove from heat. Stir in 2 tablespoons Parmesan cheese and next 4 ingredients. Set aside. Break spaghetti into 4-inch pieces. Cook according to package directions, omitting salt and fat. Drain well. Stir spaghetti and chicken into mushroom mixture. Spoon mixture into a deep 3-quart casserole coated with cooking spray. Sprinkle with remaining 2 tablespoons Parmesan cheese. Cover casserole and bake at 350° for 20 minutes. Bake, uncovered, 10 minutes. Let stand 5 minutes before serving.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Cream together the sugar and butter.
Add the eggs, one at the time.
Then mix in flour, sour cream and lemon extract.
Mix well for 3 minutes.

title: chocolate balls
directions: Mix powdered sugar, coconut, butter, nuts, milk, vanilla and cherries (if desired).
Roll in small balls.
Put in refrigerator for 30 minutes.
Melt 3/4 block paraffin wax in top of double boiler with chocolate chips. Dip balls into mixture.
Place on wax paper on cookie sheet until hard.

title: dessert
directions: Crush cookies and put on bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Save out 1/2 cup of the crumbs.
Melt butter and pour over crushed cookies. Put in freezer for 15 to 20 minutes.
Mix together 1 bowl of Cool Whip, cream cheese and powdered sugar.
Mix the pudding according to box directions.
Put the cream cheese mixture over the cookies. Pour pudding over the cream cheese layer.
Spread the other bowl of Cool Whip over the pudding.
Sprinkle the 1/2 cup of cookie crumbs on top and refrigerate.

title: easy peanut butter chocolate fudge
directions: In large saucepan, melt peanut butter chips, 1 cup Eagle Brand milk and 2 tablespoons margarine.
Stir occasionally.
Remove from heat.
Stir in peanuts.
Spread mixture into wax paper lined 8-inch square pan.
In small saucepan, melt chocolate chips, remaining Eagle Brand milk and margarine.
Spread chocolate mixture on top of peanut butter mixture.
(Chill 2 hours or until firm.)

title: macaroon souffle
directions: Combine milk, egg yolks, sugar and salt.
Bring to a boil.
Add gelatin which has been dissolved in a little cold water.
When mixture is cold, add the 3 beaten egg whites and vanilla.
Mix in macaroon crumbs (or vanilla wafer crumbs).
Stir occasionally until mixture begins to thicken.
Put in mold (dish).
Serve with whipped cream.
Serves 8.

title: herbed ham slices
directions: Soak ham in cold water overnight.
Drain. Add fresh water and boil 20 minutes per pound. Remove from broth.
Cool 5 to 10 minutes. Trim off skin, leaving fat.
Brush with dark corn syrup and bake 20 minutes or until brown.

title: spiced holiday tea
directions: Bring the 7 cups of water and the sugar to boil in a large saucepan; cook until the sugar dissolves.
Add the tea bags. Remove from the heat and steep for 5 minutes; remove the tea bags. Add the orange juice concentrate and 1 can of water and the lemon juice.
In a separate pan, combine the 4 cups of water, the cinnamon sticks and the cloves.
Simmer, covered, for 20 minutes. Strain and add to the tea mixture.
Serve hot, garnished with lemon slices or cinnamon sticks.
Yields 3 1/4 quarts.

title: oriental salad
directions: Mix first five ingredients together.
Mix the remaining ingredients for dressing and pour over noodle mixture and mix thoroughly.

title: oreo cheesecake
directions: For crust, mix crushed cookies and butter; press onto bottom of a 9-inch spring-form pan. Bake at 325° for 10 minutes.

title: tuna noodle casserole
directions: Cook the egg noodles per package directions, drain.
Put into a large casserole dish.
Pour into this the tuna and soup.
Stir well. Dot butter across the top.
Bake at 425° for 15 minutes until golden brown.

title: lasagne(uncooked noodles)
directions: Mix sauce and meat.
Spoon thin layer on bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Next, add layer of noodles.

title: shrimp & crab casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Finely chop green pepper, celery and onion.
Drain shrimp and crab.
Mix all ingredients.
Top with bread crumbs.
Reduce heat to 350° and cook 30 minutes.

title: stuffed shells
directions: Cook shells.
Drain and rinse in cold water.
While shells are cooking, cook spinach.
Squeeze excess water from spinach.
Mix together cottage cheese, onion, spinach and 1/2 cup of Parmesan cheese.

title: danielle's quick pizza
directions: You take a bun, put the pizza sauce on, then sprinkle grated cheese on top, then put it in the oven and cook until cheese melts.
Take it out and eat it!
Yum.

title: rolled sugar cookies
directions: Mix flour, baking powder, soda, brown and granulated sugar and oleo together. Put in a cup 2 eggs and 1 1/2 teaspoons vanilla; add enough milk to fill the cup. Mix together and roll out; cut into your favorite shapes. Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: chocolate praline torte
directions: In saucepan, combine brown sugar, butter and 1/4 cup whipping cream. Stir over low heat until butter is melted. Pour into 2 greased 9-inch round cake pans. Sprinkle with pecans and set aside. Prepare cake mix according to package directions. Carefully pour batter over pecans. Bake at 325° for 35 to 45 minutes or until a toothpick comes out clean. Cool in pans for 10 minutes then invert onto wire racks to cool completely.

title: peanut blossoms
directions: Sift flour, soda and salt.
Cream shortening, peanut butter, sugar and brown sugar.
Blend in egg and vanilla.
Add dry ingredients.
Mix thoroughly.
Shape by teaspoonful into balls. Roll in sugar.
Place on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.
Remove.
Top each with a candy Kiss, pressing down so cookie cracks.
Return to oven, 2 to 5 minutes.

title: tamale pie
directions: In 2-cup measuring cup, measure 1 cup water and pour cornmeal on top; set aside.
In heavy pan bring the other 2 cups water to boil with salt and 1 tablespoon chili powder.
Stir moistened cornmeal into boiling mixture.
Stir and cook until consistency of mush.
Saute onion with meat.
Add remaining chili powder and tomato sauce.
Cook until bubbly, 2 layers of meat and mush.
Cook at 350° for 45 minutes.
Add cheese last few minutes of baking.

title: coffee cake
directions: *Mix cake mix according to directions on box.
For amount of liquid given on cake mix box, use vegetable oil for 3/4 amount and use water for the remaining.

title: vegetable stir-fry
directions: Heat vegetable oil in wok or heavy skillet.
Add garlic. Saute over medium heat until garlic is golden brown.
Discard garlic; add carrots and celery.
Stir-fry for 3 to 4 minutes or until partially cooked.
Add onion, squash and green pepper. Stir-fry for 2 to 4 minutes or until vegetables are crisp-tender. Add soy sauce, salt and pepper; mix lightly.
Makes 4 servings.

title: christmas hard candy
directions: Heat and stir until dissolved.
Boil to 300°.
Remove from heat and add 1 dram of flavoring and food coloring desired.
Pour on powdered sugar coated cookie sheet.
Break up when cool.

title: rhubarb pie
directions: Coat rhubarb and strawberries with sugar and flour mixture. Put in pie shell; add top.
Bake at 400° for 50 minutes.
Brush top with milk and sprinkle with sugar.

title: french dressing
directions: Blend all ingredients in blender a few seconds.
Makes approximately 1 pint.

title: angel cookies
directions: Melt butter.
Add sugar, dates and slightly beaten egg.
Bring to boil and cook 3 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Add nuts and Rice Krispies.
When cool, roll into balls and roll in coconut.
Makes 7 dozen.

title: refrigerator rolls
directions: Stir first 3 ingredients until dissolved and let stand 45 minutes.
Cream the 1/2 cup sugar and shortening.
Add salt and egg.
Beat well.
Add warm water and yeast mixture.
Add enough flour to make a soft dough and let rise until double in bulk. Knead smooth.
Cover and place in refrigerator until wanted. Shape into rolls.
Let rise until double.
Bake 15 minutes in 450° oven.

title: meat croquettes
directions: Make thick white sauce by melting butter over low heat; blend in flour, salt and pepper and stir until bubbly.
Remove from heat and stir in milk.
Bring to boil.
Boil 1 minute, stirring constantly.
Mix in onion, parsley and meat.
Spread out on plate. Chill thoroughly.
Shape into balls and then roll in flour, egg slightly beaten with 2 tablespoons water, then roll in dry bread crumbs.
Fry in hot oil, 365°, for 1 1/2 to 2 minutes.
Drain on paper towel.

title: turkey pot pie
directions: Melt mayonnaise in a heavy saucepan over low heat; add flour, stirring until smooth.
Cook 1 minute, stirring constantly. Gradually add milk; cook over medium heat, stirring constantly until mixture is thickened and bubbly.
Stir in turkey, mixed vegetables, bouillon granules and pepper; cook over medium heat until thoroughly heated.
Spoon into a 9-inch quiche dish or pie plate.

title: refrigerator slaw
directions: Layer cabbage and onions in glass bowl.
Pour 12 tablespoons sugar over top.
Boil other ingredients and pour over top.
Do not stir!
Cover and refrigerate for 24 hours.
Keeps for weeks!

title: strawberry frozen yogurt pie
directions: Thaw frozen strawberries; drain off excess juice.
Combine Cool Whip, yogurt and berries in large bowl.
Pour into pie shell and put in freezer.
Serve frozen, cut in pie wedges.
Makes a great hot weather dessert.
(To make this more attractive, serve a whole strawberry on each piece.)

title: smoked turkey
directions: Salt and pepper neck and chest cavities well.
Quarter onions and cut celery stalks into 9 pieces.
Stuff neck cavity with 2 quarters of onion and three pieces of celery.
Stuff chest cavity with remaining pieces of onion and celery.
Skewer cavities, legs and wings by tying to bird.
Salt and pepper very generously. Place on grill.
Turn 15 minutes to keep from burning.
Cook 10 minutes per pound.

title: senate bean soup
directions: Soak beans as directed on package.
Combine beans, water and ham shank in large deep pot.
Simmer, covered, for 1 1/2 hours. Remove 1 cup beans; place in small bowl and mash well.
Remove ham shank; trim meat off bone.
Return mashed beans and meat to pot. Add remaining ingredients; simmer an additional 20 to 30 minutes, until beans are tender and soup has thickened.
Makes 10 (1-cup) servings.

title: lemony chinese chicken morsels
directions: In a medium size bowl, combine lemon juice, soy sauce, mustard, oil and cayenne pepper.
Add chicken cubes and toss well to coat.
Cover and refrigerate at least 1 hour, tossing occasionally.
Heat broiler.
Lightly grease broiler pan rack. Drain chicken and place cubes on rack about 1 inch apart.
Broil 4 to 5 inches from heat for 7 minutes, brushing with the marinade and turning them halfway through cooking time.
Serve immediately.

title: onion and tomato dip
directions: Mix sour cream and dressing. Put on on glass tray and refrigerate overnight. Just before serving put chopped tomatoes and onion on top of mixture. Then add the cheese. Serve with chips or crackers.

title: moussaka
directions: This dish is a combination of 3 parts that we must prepare separately.

title: double almond biscotti
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Heat dry 8-inch skillet over low heat. Add 3/4 cup chopped almonds, cook 5 to 6 minutes, stirring frequently until golden.
Set aside to cool.

title: ez stir-fry
directions: Heat oil in large pan.
Add meat and mushrooms.
Cook until meat is browned.
Add soy sauce and stir.
Add frozen vegetables. Cover and heat until tender, then add bean sprouts and stir-fry vegetables.
Heat through.
May make "saucy" by adding 1 tablespoon of cornstarch with 1/3 cup cold water.
Serve over rice.

title: cottage cheese dip
directions: Mix well together.
Good with crackers, veggies, by itself or with a meat.

title: mom's meat loaf
directions: Combine the first 6 ingredients with salt in saucepan, mixing well.
Cook for 5 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Combine ground beef with half the tomato sauce mixture and remaining ingredients, mixing well.
Shape into loaf shape and place in loaf baking pan. Pour remaining tomato sauce mixture over meat loaf.
Place 2 strips of bacon over the top.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: cranberry relish
directions: Combine all ingredients, mixing well. Chill several hours before serving.
Yields 1 quart.

title: meatballs
directions: Soak bread in milk, add eggs, let stand 1/2 hour.
Add rest of ingredients then shape into meatballs.
Place meatballs on ungreased cookie sheet and bake at 350 degrees for 20 minutes.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix pineapple, oranges, apricot halves, strawberries and poppy seed.
Fold in peach pie filling; refrigerate.
Before serving, add bananas.
Can be made and refrigerated.

title: carrie moore's soft raisin cookies
directions: Cream sugar and butter.
Add eggs (one at a time) beating. Mix flour, salt and soda.
Add alternately with raisin juice.
Add raisins and nuts.
Drop on greased baking sheet by teaspoons. Bake at 350° until lightly browned.

title: apple cobbler
directions: Mix 1 cup sugar, the cinnamon, nutmeg and salt; pour over apples that have been peeled, cored and sliced.
Let set while you mix the crust.

title: homemade vanilla ice cream
directions: Mix ingredients in blender.
Pour into ice cream freezer container, takes 45 minutes using electric unit.

title: oven fried style baked potatoes
directions: Wash, peel and cut potatoes into small chunks.
Place on a cookie sheet sprayed with Pam.
Sprinkle bell pepper and onion on potatoes.
Sprinkle water over items to keep them moist.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for about 20 minutes, stirring occasionally. (Optional:
Can leave peel on potatoes.)

title: soap from tallow or lard
directions: Dissolve lye in water.
Let both stand until 90°.
Use a stone or granite container to make soap in.
Stir lye into fat very slowly, constantly stirring.
Dissolve 1 ounce Borax in 1 cup hot water and add with 1 cup liquid ammonia to mixture 1/2 cup granulated sugar dissolved in warm water and 1 ounce oil citronella.
Mix thoroughly until thick.
Pour into molds and set for a short time.
Cut and lay out to dry.
Ready for use in 10 days.

title: onion rings
directions: Combine dry ingredients in bowl.
Combine egg, milk and oil. Mix all ingredients together.
Slice onions 1/4 inch thick.
Dip in mixture and fry in hot oil, turning once.

title: turkey and stuffing pie
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Pat stuffing evenly into 9-inch pie plate to form crust, building up sides to form rim.
Sprinkle turkey and cheese evenly over stuffing.
In small bowl, beat together milk and eggs; pour over turkey.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes or until knife inserted near center comes out clean.
Let stand 5 minutes before serving.
Serves 6.

title: cream of broccoli soup(low-fat)
directions: In a large saucepan, cook broccoli in water.
Bring to a boil. Lower heat to medium; cook 5 minutes.
Add carrots; cook an additional 4 minutes.
Do not drain.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients together and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: seafood fettucini
directions: Melt butter and flour together gradually.
Add half and half until thickens.
Add cheese; cook until smooth.
Fold in crab; heat 3 minutes.
Serve over fettucini.

title: taco salad
directions: Brown ground beef with taco seasoning and salt.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix all together. Form into small balls. Bake on cookie sheet at 325° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: taco casserole
directions: Brown ground beef.
Add tomato sauce, taco mix and water.
Let simmer for 15 minutes.
In casserole dish, layer meat mixture, grated cheese and crushed corn chips.
Warm in oven for about 10 to 15 minutes, until cheese is melted and casserole is warm.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Boil cauliflower and carrots for 5 to 7 minutes.
Drain.
Mix all ingredients well and put in casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: lun lafollette's tuna casserole
directions: Cook noodles, mix with all other ingredients except cheese. Put in 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Sprinkle cheese on top.
Cook at 375° for 30 minutes or until bubbly.

title: persimmon pudding
directions: Beat eggs, sugar and butter.
Add persimmon pulp.
Add soda and flour; add milk.
Mix well and bake 2 to 3 hours in 250° oven. Stir occasionally.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Brown beef with green pepper and onion. Drain. Add beans. In baking dish, layer tortillas. Spread sour cream. Spread salsa. Spread meat mixture. Spread cheese. Repeat layers 3 or 4 times. Bake 20 minutes at 450°.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli according to directions on package.
Drain and chop into small pieces.
Mix with cooked rice, Cheez Whiz, water chestnuts and soup.
Pour into casserole dish.
Top with buttered Ritz cracker crumbs.
Bake in 350° oven until crumbs are brown.

title: butter cookies
directions: Soften butter and mix with sugar.
Add other ingredients except flour.
Blend well.
Add flour.
Blend well.
Spoon out in balls onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Lightly press balls with a fork.
Bake at 350° until brown.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Drain juice from pineapple.
Add water to make 1 cup.
Heat; stir into jello.
Set jello until syrupy.
Add cranberry sauce, pineapple, nuts and celery.
Refrigerate until solid.
Serve.

title: dill dip
directions: Mix ingredients thoroughly and serve with chips and/or vegetables.

title: glazed hamburger loaf
directions: Mix
ground
beef, onion, celery,
bell
pepper,
bread crumbs, 1 cup catsup, salt and pepper together.
Shape
into a loaf.
Bake in a loaf pan at 350° for 30 minutes.
Remove from oven.
Mix 1 cup catsup, pineapple and
brown
sugar
together and spread over hamburger loaf.
Return to the	oven
and cook about 30 minutes longer.	Serve with rice.

title: onion au gratin
directions: Mix onions, 4 cups cheese and remaining ingredients.
Pour into a 2-quart casserole dish.
Sprinkle 1 cup grated cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Makes 10 to 12 servings.

title: raw apple cake
directions: Cream the first 3 ingredients, until well blended.

title: green chili stew
directions: Partially brown ground beef.
Add onions, chili and tomatoes. continue browning.
Add flour.
Stir in water, potatoes and corn. Season to taste with salt, pepper and garlic powder.
Simmer for 1 hour.

title: chocolate candy
directions: Mix sugar and cocoa together.
Melt margarine, cheese and vanilla and mix all ingredients together.
Pour in buttered dish and put in refrigerator.
Cut later.

title: coffee roast
directions: Melt 2 tablespoons of butter in a large saucepan over medium-high heat. Add the roast and sear on all sides until well browned. Set aside.

title: luscious lemon or chocolate pie
directions: Mix flour, pecans and oleo until it looks like biscuit dough; press into pie pan.
Bake at 300° for 15 minutes.
Mix confectioners sugar, Cool Whip and cream cheese; put in the crust while still warm.
Mix pudding and pour over top of cheese filling. Top with Cool Whip and coconut.
Chill before serving.
On the chocolate, put grated chocolate instead of coconut.

title: banana split torte
directions: Melt oleo and add crushed graham crackers, mix well and press into bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Refrigerate.
In a small bowl mix cream cheese, confectioners sugar and 1/2 (1 cup) of Cool Whip and then spread this over the crust.
Slice the bananas and dip into the juice of the pineapple you've just drained, then remove from juice and place the bananas on the cream cheese layer.
Spread the drained pineapple over the bananas and then cover them with the remaining Cool Whip.
Sprinkle cut up cherries and chopped nuts on top then drizzle with chocolate syrup.
Cover and refrigerate for at least 6 hours.

title: lemon squares
directions: Mix butter, flour and confectioners sugar.
Press into 10 x 10-inch pan.
Bake at 325° for 15 minutes.

title: spinach rolls
directions: Prepare and cook cornbread and crumble.
Mix with sour cream and spinach. Fill and roll ham slices.
Pour cheese sauce over ham rolls in baking dish. Bake at 350°, covered, 30 minutes.
Uncover and bake 5 to 10 minutes. Serve with fruit and rolls.

title: dill pickles
directions: Simmer
all
ingredients about 15 minutes.
Pack pickles in jar with 1 head of dill plus several stems.
A chili pepper in each
jar adds to flavor.
Pour liquid mixture over pickles and bring
to
boil
5 to 7 minutes, until all green color has changed.
(Garlic may be added.)

title: spicy pumpkin bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Beat with mixer the eggs until frothy; beat in sugar and beat for 2 minutes. Beat in the oil and pumpkin. Sift dry ingredients over the raisins and nuts and fold dry mixture into egg mixture; do not overmix. Pour into a greased 13 x 9-inch pan. Bake for 35 to 40 minutes. Cool on rack.

title: party sandwich loaves
directions: Remove crust from loaf of bread.
Cut 4 lengthwise slices. Spread each bread slice with softened butter.
Spread chicken salad first and second slice of bread.
Put cheese spread between second and third slice.
Put ham salad between third and fourth slices.
Press loaf together; wrap in wax paper.
Chill 1 hour. Frost top and sides of loaf with cream cheese, softened with cream.
Arrange chopped parsley, sliced green pepper or sliced tomatoes on top.
Cut into thick slices when serving.

title: rice and broccoli
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Mix well.
Put mixture in a 1 1/2 quart greased casserole dish.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: baked fish with cheese sauce
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Spray a shallow baking dish with nonstick coating.
Place fillets in dish, tucking under any thin edges.
Melt margarine or butter; brush on top of fish.
Top with bread crumbs.
Bake in oven for 10 to 15 minutes or until fish flakes easily with a fork.
While fish is baking, prepare sauce. In a small saucepan, stir together milk and flour.
Cook and stir over medium heat until thickened and bubbly.
Add cheese and mustard.
Cook and stir until cheese melts.

title: banana bread
directions: Combine eggs, shortening, sugar and bananas in blender.
Cover and blend about 30 seconds or until smooth.
Sift dry ingredients together in mixing bowl.
Pour blender combination over dry ingredients.
Stir only until combined.
Grease 8 x 4-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Turn out of pan and cool.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli and rice as directed.
Mix remaining ingredients.
Put in a greased covered casserole.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: quick macaroni and cheese
directions: Place uncooked macaroni in casserole dish.
Add margarine, salt and cheese.
Mix; pour milk over ingredients and stir.
Bake in oven 1 hour at 350°.
Do not stir.
Bake uncovered.
Makes 4 servings.

title: poppy seed bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Use metal loaf pans; do not oil pans. Mix ingredients together; pour into loaf pans.
Bake for 40 minutes.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix together.
Form small balls.
Bake at 325° for 25 minutes.
Serve warm.

title: italian cream cheese cake
directions: Stir baking soda into buttermilk and set aside.
Cream butter, shortening and sugar.
Add egg yolks, one at a time, beating after each addition.
Add buttermilk alternately with flour, beginning and ending with flour.
Fold in coconut, pecans and vanilla extract.
Beat egg whites until stiff peaks form, but not dry. Fold into batter.
Pour into 3 greased and floured 9-inch cake pans.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Cool layers completely before icing cake.

title: liver and onions
directions: Melt 2 teaspoons of butter in nonstick skillet.
Add onion and saute over medium heat about 10 minutes.
Remove onion from skillet.
Melt remaining butter and add liver.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Brown over medium heat about 3 minutes each side. Distribute onion evenly over browned liver in skillet.

title: crushed mint salad
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients together (will look gummy).
Place in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Refrigerate 4 to 8 hours.
Then take Cool Whip and mix with crushed after-dinner mints.
Mix with jello mixture and freeze overnight.
Keep in freezer until ready to serve.

title: cheese straws
directions: Mix all ingredients except olives into a smooth dough.

title: crisp roasted duck with plum sauce(total time:  2 hours)
directions: Preheat the oven to 400°.
Simmer the ducks in salted boiling water for 10 minutes.
Remove and drain them.
Combine the salt, pepper, garlic, soy sauce and honey in a small bowl.

title: jello popcorn balls
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Stir until dissolved.
Quickly pour over popcorn.
Then shake bag and make into balls.
Makes 9 cups.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli; strain.
Mix egg, soup, milk, mayonnaise and cheese.
Place broccoli in 1-quart baking
dish.
Pour mixture over broccoli.
Sprinkle bread crumbs on top.
Drizzle melted butter on top of bread crumbs.
Bake in 350° oven for 45 minutes.

title: diet faygo strawberry pie
directions: Stir in Faygo, Jell-O and cornstarch and bring to a boil until Jell-O dissolves.
Cool it.
Put strawberries in 9-inch pie pan. Pour sauce over berries.
Store in refrigerator.

title: apple squares
directions: Grease 13-inch baking pan.
Beat sugar, eggs, vanilla and oil. Sift dry ingredients.
Add to wet ingredients.
Mix well by hand. Add nuts and apples.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: creamy tacos
directions: Brown hamburger.
Add chili.
Add Velveeta cheese, Ro-Tel tomatoes and whipping cream.
Heat; pour over chips and eat.

title: corn chowder
directions: Cook onion in margarine.
Blend in flour, salt and pepper. Add milk, stirring until bubbly.
Add sausage, corn, lima beans and potato.
Simmer until thickens.

title: cherry chiffon cake
directions: Sift together flour, sugar, baking powder and salt 3 times. Make a well and add in order given the next 5 ingredients.
Beat until smooth.
Into large bowl measure egg whites and cream of tartar.
Beat until whites form very stiff peaks.
Do not underbeat.
Peaks will stand alone.
Gradually pour egg yolk mixture into the beaten egg whites, folding gently as you pour, just until blended.
Do not stir.
Mix together maraschino cherries and chopped nuts.
Sprinkle over batter and fold gently with a few strokes.
Pour immediately into ungreased angel food pan (10 x 4-inch).
Bake at 325° for 65 to 70 minutes until top springs back or needle inserted into cake returns clean.
When done, turn pan upside down with tube part of pan over neck of thin bottle.
Cool thoroughly before removing from pan.
Frost with either white mountain icing or cherry nut icing.

title: missouri cookies
directions: Combine sugar, cocoa, milk and margarine in pan.
Cook to full rolling boil, then time for 1 minute at full rolling boil.
Remove from burner.
Add vanilla, salt, peanut butter and oats; mix well. Drop by teaspoonful onto waxed paper.
You'll have to do the spooning quickly.

title: parker house roll sandwiches
directions: Cut rolls in half.
Spread mixture of butter, mustard and onion on both sides of ham.
Place shredded cheese on top of ham. Place sandwiches in oven and bake at 350° until cheese melts.
Cut in squares.

title: oatmeal snaps
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Grease baking sheet with Crisco.
Combine brown sugar, Crisco, eggs and vanilla in large bowl.
Beat at medium speed on electric mixer until well blended.
Combine flour, soda, cinnamon and salt.
Add gradually to creamed mixture at low speed.
Beat until well blended.
Stir in oats and raisins with spoon.

title: cornbread salad
directions: Combine the first 3 ingredients; set aside.
Combine the tomatoes, bell pepper and green onion.
Layer ingredients in this order (use a large salad bowl):
1/2 crumbled bread, 1/2 of beans, 1/2 vegetable mixture, 1/2 cheese, 1/2 bacon, 1/2 corn and 1/2 dressing mixture.
Repeat order.
Store in refrigerator.
Best if made 2 hours ahead.

title: waldorf salad
directions: Stir apples in lemon and water.
Mix all ingredients together. If possible let this stand for a few hours so the wonderful flavors can blend together.

title: cherry-berries on a cloud
directions: Stir together and use as topping.

title: raisin pie
directions: Combine eggs, sugar, spices, salt, lemon juice and butter. Stir in raisins and nuts.
Pour into pie shell and bake for 35 to 40 minutes or until filling is set in center.
Cool.

title: cheese ball
directions: Grate all cheeses; add all ingredients into mixing bowl and mix until all ingredients are completely blended.
Place Saran Wrap in the bottom of a bowl and spoon in the cheese mix.
Cover top of mixture with the Saran Wrap and refrigerate for several hours. Will keep in refrigerator for 2 to 3 weeks.
Serve with celery sticks, carrot sticks or crackers.

title: crock-pot dressing
directions: Break up bread.
Mix everything together except margarine. Pour into crock-pot and dot with butter.
Cover and cook on high for 2 hours.

title: basil tomato salad
directions: Whisk together oil, vinegar, basil, salt and pepper in large bowl. Add rice, tomatoes, cucumbers and onion; toss lightly. Makes 6 servings.

title: grape-nut pudding
directions: Cream together butter and sugar.
Add egg yolks, flour, Grape-Nuts, milk and lemon juice and rind.
Fold in 4 beaten egg whites.
Pour in casserole.
Place casserole in pan of water.
Bake at 375° for 50 minutes.
Very lemony and rich.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Brown roast or steak and onions; drain.
Add onion soup and mushrooms and simmer at least an hour, uncovered.
Just before serving, add sour cream.
Serve over cooked noodles.

title: no fail 7 minute icing
directions: Combine sugar, salt, cream of tartar and water in boiler. Bring to boiling and cook. Stir until sugar dissolves. Place egg whites in small bowl of electric mixer. Pour boiling syrup in a thin stream over unbeaten egg whites, beating at high speed until of spreading consistency. Add vanilla. Spread on cooled cake. May be used for pineapple or coconut cake.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix the first 5 ingredients.
Add nuts. Pour into shell. Bake at 350° for 50-55 minutes.
Cool.

title: cucumber and onion salad
directions: Slice cucumbers thin (peeling or not as you wish). Slice onion into rings. Place cucumber slices in between paper towels and squeeze or press hard. Try to remove as much moisture from cucumbers as you can. Place squeezed cucumbers in bowl and add the onion rings. Cover with vinegar to which a small amount of cold water and a hint of sugar have been added. Add salt; sprinkle freely with pepper. Refrigerate and let stand several hours; the colder the better. An excellent side dish or fabulous accompaniment for cold meats. Makes 4 to 6 servings. Enjoy!

title: honey bars
directions: Mix ingredients in order given.
Spread in 9 x 13-inch cake pan and bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
A thin powdered sugar frosting may be drizzled on top. Cut while warm.
The bars will be crispy when first baked, but will be softer when they have set awhile.

title: sweet and sour chicken
directions: Saute onion until soft in oil.
Combine ketchup, sugar, soy sauce, lemon juice and black pepper.
Add to onion.
Add chicken; cover and simmer 30 minutes or until done.
Remove chicken to platter.
Dissolve cornstarch with 2 tablespoons water.
Add to sauce; bring to boil, stirring and cooking until thickened.
Pour sauce over chicken.

title: harvard beets
directions: Melt butter and add flour.
Blend.
Add beet liquid.
Cook until thickened, stirring constantly.
Add brown sugar, vinegar, salt, pepper and cloves.
Stir until sugar dissolves.
Drain beets and add.
Heat thoroughly.
Serves 6.

title: double chocolate eggnog
directions: In large mixing bowl, beat eggs on low speed mixer until blended.
Gradually add sugar, beating on high about 5 minutes, or until eggs are very thick.
Stir in the chocolate milk, vanilla and 1/4 teaspoon nutmeg.
Pour mixture into large container. Gently fold in chocolate ice cream and whipping cream.
Cover and chill eggnog until serving time.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into 2 unbaked 9-inch pie shells.
Bake 10 minutes at 425°.
Reduce heat to 350°.
Bake 30 minutes longer or until done.

title: raspberry chiffon pie
directions: Drain thawed berries.
Reserve syrup.
Garnish with whole berries.
Add enough water to syrup to make 1 1/2 cups.

title: strawberry pretzel salad
directions: Combine first 2 ingredients; press into lightly greased 8 x 8 x 2-inch dish.
Bake at 250° for 10 minutes; let cool.
Beat cream cheese at medium speed with electric mixer until light and fluffy; add sugar, mixing until well blended.
Fold in Cool Whip and carefully spread over pretzel crust.
Combine gelatin and boiling water into a bowl, stirring 2 minutes or until dissolved.
Add cold water and chill until mixture is the consistency of unbeaten egg whites.
Stir in strawberries; pour over cream cheese layer. Refrigerate until firm.
Cut into squares; serve on lettuce leaves and a dollop of mayonnaise, if desired.

title: barbecued ribs sauce
directions: Warm all ingredients in saucepan.
Place ribs in 475° oven for 30 minutes.
Put slices of onion and lemon juice on ribs.
Put oven at 350°. Pour sauce over ribs.
Bake 45 minutes to 1
hour, basting ribs every 15 minutes.

title: blueberry-sour cream corn muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Grease 12 medium sized muffin cups or line with paper liners; set aside.
Combine dry ingredients in medium bowl.
Add combined egg, sour cream and apple juice concentrate; mix just until dry ingredients are moistened.
Gently stir in blueberries.

title: fudge
directions: Mix sugar, syrup, cocoa and milk and cook slowly to soft ball stage.
Remove from heat and add vanilla, margarine and marshmallows.
Beat until candy becomes stiff.
Add nuts.
Pour into buttered dish.

title: 5 cup salad
directions: Mix together and chill.
Better if allowed to set overnight.

title: farm house pound cake
directions: Cream butter, gradually adding sugar, beating well.
Blend in flavorings.
Beat egg yolks until thick and lemon colored.
Stir into creamed mixture.
Sift flour, baking powder and salt.
Add to egg mixture 1/3 at a time, stirring well after each addition. Beat egg whites until stiff, but not dry.
Fold into batter until just patches of egg white disappear.
Pour into buttered, lightly floured 10-inch ring tube pan.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 30 minutes.
Reduce oven temperature to 300° and cook 30 minutes longer or until cake is done.
Remove from pan, cool on wire rack. Serve with fruit preserves.

title: best-ever chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream margarine with sugars, eggs; add salt, vanilla and soda, all at once.
Stir in flour until all is blended together.
Add chips
and	nuts
and stir again.
Wet your hands and using 1 heaping
teaspoonful
for
each
cookie,
roll in hands until round.
Place about 2 inches apart on cookie sheet.
Bake in 375° oven for
about
minutes.
Remove
to
wire rack to cool. These are even better when baked in a convection oven at 375°for 12 minutes.
Yield: about 48 cookies

title: sweet and sour meatballs
directions: Mix hamburger, 1/2 can soup and cracker crumbs.
Form into meatballs.
Spray electric skillet and cook meatballs.
When done, add 1 1/2 cans soup, onion, Worcestershire sauce, vinegar and sugar.
Simmer 10 to 15 minutes.
Serve with mashed potatoes.

title: bertha's fruit cake bar
directions: Melt oleo in 15 x 10-inch jelly roll pan.
Sprinkle crumbs evenly.
Add remaining ingredients and press down to even mixture. Pour sweetened condensed milk evenly over mixture.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cool and cut into squares.
Keeps for weeks in refrigerator.

title: sweet and sour pork
directions: Brown pork well in oil in skillet.
Add onion; cover and simmer 20 minutes.
Combine vinegar, cornstarch, salt, ginger and pepper.
Add jelly to mixture and pepper strips.
Place into skillet; bring to a boil, stirring.
Cover and simmer 5 minutes. Add pineapple chunks and heat.
Serve over a bed of rice.

title: the ultimate grilled cheese sandwich(serves 6)
directions: In a mixing bowl, beat cream cheese and mayonnaise until smooth. Stir in cheeses, garlic powder and seasoned salt. Spread 6 slices of bread evenly with the cheese mixture. Top with remaining bread. Butter the outside of sandwiches; cook in a large skillet over medium heat until golden brown on both sides.

title: vermont doughnuts
directions: Sift together dry ingredients.
Beat together eggs.
Add 1 cup sugar until light.
Add butter, milk and vanilla.
Add dry ingredients all at once, stirring just until smooth.
(Dough is very soft.)
Knead dough lightly on floured surface.
Roll out dough 3/8-inch thick.
Cut with floured doughnut cutter.
Fry doughnuts in hot cooking oil (370°) until golden brown, turning once.
Drain on paper towels.
Roll doughnuts in sugar.
Makes 2 dozen.

title: ivy's christmas salad
directions: Mix all ingredients except cream.
Whip the cream until stiff; fold with other mixture.
Freeze.

title: pork chop supreme
directions: Quickly brown pork chops in a small amount of oil.
Place in a casserole dish.
Combine remaining ingredients and pour over chops.
Bake at 350° for 90 minutes.
Serve with rice or mashed potatoes.

title: greenbrier salad(12 servings)
directions: Mix Jell-O, water and marshmallows. Place on medium heat until marshmallows dissolve. Cool. Fold in cottage cheese, pineapple, nuts and Cool Whip. Spread in 9 x 13 pan. Refrigerate. Stir twice until sets.

title: honey bran muffins
directions: Cream honey and Crisco.
Add eggs, cereal and boiling water. Add dry ingredients and buttermilk.
Bake at 375° until done. Batter can be stored in refrigerator until ready to use.

title: lori's plaza iii steak soup
directions: Melt margarine in Dutch oven over low heat, slowly stir in flour.
Add 8 cups water, mixing well.
Add rest of ingredients. Simmer over low heat for 2 to 6 hours.

title: caramel popcorn
directions: Combine popcorn and nuts in lightly greased 14 x 11 x 2-inch roasting pan.
Mix well and set aside.
Melt butter over low heat in medium saucepan.
Add brown sugar and honey; bring to a boil and boil 5 minutes without stirring.
Add vanilla, stirring well. Pour syrup over popcorn mixture, stirring until popcorn is evenly coated.
Bake at 250° for 1 hour, stirring every 15 minutes.
Cool completely and break into pieces.

title: holiday punch
directions: Using a large pot, combine all ingredients.
Bring to boil over medium heat.
Reduce heat and simmer 30 minutes.
To serve, strain and float orange slices.

title: buttermilk biscuits
directions: Cut Crisco; stir in buttermilk.
Mix and roll out.
Cut with a 3-inch cutter.
Bake at 450° for 20 minutes.

title: frozen dessert
directions: Mix in large dish, sprinkle nuts on top and freeze.
Can be dipped or cut in squares.

title: dried beef casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Let stand 3 hours or longer; can let stand overnight.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°; this goes in a 9 x 9-inch or 8 x 8-inch pan.

title: double-crust pizza casserole
directions: For crust, combine flour, potatoes, milk and margarine or butter.
Set aside.

title: pecan cake
directions: Chop the pecans.
Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each addition.
In a large pan, mix all dry ingredients, fruit and nuts, then add gradually to batter.
Put in pan with buttered paper in the bottom and pack well.
Bake at 250° for 3 hours or more.

title: yellow punch(serves 50 punch cups)
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients and freeze.
Remove from freezer before serving time and allow to partially thaw.
Add 4 quarts of ginger ale when ready to serve.

title: recipe for happiness
directions: Combine ingredients; mix in a quantity of patience.
Serve with laughter.
Make a dedicated Christian.

title: pineapple - pear salad
directions: Drain fruit and reserve juices.
Cut pears in bite-size pieces.
Add water to juice to make 2 cups liquid.
Dissolve jello in boiling water; add reserved juices.
Combine cream cheese and mayonnaise.
Stir fruits in cheese mixture and add to jello mixture.
Pour into lightly oiled 8-cup mold and chill until firm. Makes 10 to 12 servings.

title: heart vegetable soup
directions: Combine all ingredients in crock-pot.
Add water to cover (about 2 cups).
Stir well.
Cover and cook on low for 12 to 18 hours or 5 to 7 hours on high.

title: glazed cinnamon bar
directions: Combine butter, sugar, egg yolks and salt; beat until creamy. Stir in flour and cinnamon; mix well.
Spread thick batter in a greased 15 x 10-inch pan.
Beat egg white until foamy.
Stir in powdered sugar; brush this over batter.
Sprinkle nuts over top. Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Cut while hot into bars or squares.
Remove from pan and cool.

title: campfire kitchen
directions: Shape ground beef into large patty.
Place onion on large piece of foil.
Add patty. Season. Add green pepper, celery and cabbage. Top with carrot and potato. Add soup and water. Wrap tightly. Grill for 1 hour or until done.
May bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Yields 1 serving.

title: popovers
directions: Blend all ingredients well.
Spray muffin tins with nonstick spray (more than you think you need until it runs down sides) and place these in 400° oven for 10 minutes.
Pour batter into hot muffin tins, filling each 3/4 full.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes, then reduce heat to 350°.
Bake another 30 minutes.
Do not open oven door until the popovers have finished baking.

title: dandy apple cake
directions: Spread one can of apple pie filling in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle with 1/2 box of yellow butter cake mix, melt butter and pour over cake mix.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes. Serve warm with ice cream.

title: pork in green chile
directions: *Wear gloves to clean and cut peppers; do not touch eyes!

title: chocolate angel pie
directions: Beat first 4 crust ingredients to soft peaks.
Gradually add 2/3 cup sugar.
Beat until stiff and add chopped pecans.
Grease a 9-inch pie pan with butter.
Pour crust in and bake at 300° for 55 minutes.
Let stand in oven overnight.

title: hawaiian chicken salad
directions: Drain pineapple; reserve 1 tablespoon syrup.
In large mixing bowl, lightly toss chicken, celery, pineapple, almonds and grapes. In bowl, mix reserved syrup, oil, vinegar, mayonnaise and salt. Pour over chicken; toss lightly.
Arrange in lettuce cups.
Garnish with olives, parsley and pickles.

title: blueberry bread
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Grease 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan.
Sift flour. In large bowl, combine margarine, granulated sugar and eggs. Beat at high speed until fluffy.
At low speed, add dry ingredients alternately with milk.
Fold in blueberries.
Pour into prepared pan; sprinkle with brown sugar and cinnamon.
Bake for 35 minutes.
Serve warm.

title: baked seafood salad
directions: Combine first 2 ingredients with vegetables.
Blend next 6 ingredients; stir into seafood mixture.
Spoon into a large baking dish.
Sprinkle bread crumbs over the top.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: green tomato mincemeat
directions: Chop up
tomatoes
in
food processor.	Drain juice and cover with cold
water.
Cook 1/2 hour after tomatoes begin to boil. Drain and
add
4 quarts chopped apples, 2 pounds brown sugar, salt, vinegar, cassia, cloves, allspice, salt pork (cut up), raisins, currants and citron.
Cook slowly, 3 to 4 hours, until thick.

title: caramel layer bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease 9 x 13 pan.
Combine in large bowl remaining ingredients, except chocolate chips.
By hand, stir until dough holds together.
Press one-half of dough into pan and reserve remaining dough for topping.
Bake at 350° for 6 minutes. Sprinkle chocolate chips over baked crust, then spread caramel mixture over all.
Crumble reserved dough over caramel mixture. Bake at 350° for 15-20 minutes.
Cool completely.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Brown chicken.
Spread rice in slightly greased 9 x 11-inch casserole.
(We use a 8 1/2 x 13 1/2-inch Pyrex baking dish; 10 halved chicken breasts fit well.)

title: quick peanut butter cookies
directions: In large bowl, mix all ingredients.
Scoop level tablespoonfuls and roll into balls.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Flatten with fork.
Bake at 350° for about 18 minutes. Remove to wire rack to chill.
Yield:
2 dozen.

title: zucchini parmesan
directions: Heat oil in large skillet or wok.
Add zucchini and onion. Saute until tender.
Add other ingredients.
Cover and simmer 10 minutes.
Stir occasionally.
Sprinkle with Parmesan before serving.

title: london broil demeritt style
directions: Mix soy sauce, ginger, garlic, oil, lemon juice and brown sugar in a saucepan.
Bring mixture to a boil.
Cool mixture; then place London broil and sauce in a large Ziploc bag and marinate overnight.

title: french silk pie
directions: Cream together margarine and sugar.
Add vanilla and unsweetened chocolate.
Beat in 4 eggs.
Add one egg at a time and beat each for 5 minutes. Spoon into a graham cracker crust.
Chill until set.
Serve with a spoon of Cool Whip.

title: ham loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.

title: turkey and dressing
directions: Put turkey in roasting pan and add 2 quarts of water. Add 1 stick melted butter on top of the turkey. Cover tightly and bake until tender at 200° overnight or 6 to 7 hours.

title: dried apple pound cake
directions: Cook apples until done.
Add raisins, nuts and half the sugar. Cream remaining sugar, butter and eggs.
Sift flour, soda and spices and add last.
Bake 1 hour in loaf pan at 325°.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Roll out and cut.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: raspberry tang salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water; soften cream cheese with salad dressing and add to Jell-O after Jell-O has cooled.
Add other ingredients except whipped cream.
Set aside.
Whip cream and add to mixture.
Chill and serve.

title: cranberry bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Sift flour, sugar, baking powder and salt into a mixing bowl.

title: aunt retta's quick and easy apple pie
directions: Place apples in long baking dish.
Top with bread, cut into thirds.

title: stuffed chicken(djaj mahshi)
directions: Set oven at 400°.
Wash and drain rice.
Place rice and water in saucepan.
Cover and simmer for 15 minutes so rice will be partially cooked.
Remove from heat.
Add meat, salt, pepper, cinnamon, butter and pine nuts.
Mix well.
Set aside.

title: easy tuna fish salad
directions: Mix ingredients, adding salad dressing until creamy.
Serve cold.

title: brazil-nut bread pudding
directions: Cut buttered bread into finger-width pieces.
Arrange in layers in buttered baking dish, sprinkling each layer with Brazil nuts.
Beat eggs slightly, add sugar, salt, vanilla and milk.
Mix well and pour over bread.
Garnish top with Brazil nuts and bake in slow oven (325°) for 1 hour.
Serves 6.

title: cocktail wafers on tap
directions: Mix ingredients and form into a log.
Chill.
Slice when ready to serve.
Bake in a 350° oven 10 to 12 minutes.

title: tuna noodle casserole
directions: Cook and drain noodles.
In large bowl, mix all ingredients, using enough milk to blend.
Pour into a casserole.
Top with bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.

title: cool off smoothie
directions: In a blender, combine strawberries, yogurt, ice and banana. Blend until smooth.

title: mexican taco salad
directions: Brown meat; drain.
Add onion.
Cook until tender.
Add beans and seasonings; cover and cook over medium heat for 10 minutes. Combine remaining ingredients.
Add meat mixture.
Mix lightly and serve immediately.
Yield: 6 servings.

title: meat and rice casserole
directions: Saute meat; season with onion, bay leaf and seasoned salt while cooking.
Mix with dry rice.
Mix well and place in bottom of casserole.
Top with 1 cup cottage cheese.
Top this with 1 can mushroom soup, mixed with 1/3 cup water.
Spread grated cheese on top.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: deep-fried catfish
directions: Use the whole fish or pieces of fish.
Heat fat to 370°.
Beat eggs lightly.
Dip the fish into beaten eggs, then roll in cornmeal.
Fry for 3 to 5 minutes.
Drain and season.
Serve with hush puppies.

title: party rye snacks
directions: Brown hamburger and sausage together; drain the grease.
Put meat in a bowl.
Melt cheese in a pan on low heat.
Add meat to cheese; stir together.
Add seasonings; stir.
Line cookie sheet with bread; spoon meat onto bread.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes, or pop them in the microwave.
You can freeze them on the cookie sheets and place them in plastic bags to be eaten later.

title: baked apples
directions: Core apples.
Pack brown sugar into center.
Sprinkle each with lemon juice.
Sprinkle cinnamon lightly over each apple. Place in baking dish with about 2 inches of water.
Bake in 325° oven for 1 hour.
Serve with light cream.
Serves 4.

title: potato shoestring salad
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients ahead of time.
Just before serving add shoestring potatoes or Chinese noodles.

title: pumpkin cookies
directions: Mix well and drop on oiled cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: anderson's pea soup
directions: Combine
water with all ingredients.
Bring to boil and continue to
boil hard for 20 minutes.
Reduce heat and simmer 45 minutes
or
until	peas
are
tender.
Strain through fine sieve and reheat to boiling point.

title: liberian sauce and rice
directions: Saute onions and peppers in oil.
Add meat to sear and brown. Chop greens very fine and add to pot and cover for 2 to 3 minutes, until greens appear slick.
Stir and add other ingredients.
Simmer for 10 to 15 minutes on low heat.
Serve over steamed rice.

title: cool summer cloud
directions: Mix together well and let set in refrigerator for 1 hour. Enjoy!

title: mexican dip
directions: Blend first four ingredients.
Spread in 6 x 9-inch dish. Then spread bean dip.
Then spread tomatoes and cheeses.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: appetizer ham ball
directions: Blend ham, olives, mustard and pepper sauce to taste.
Form a ball and place on a serving dish.
Combine cream cheese and milk; frost ham ball.
Chill.
Remove from refrigerator 15 minutes before serving.
Trim with parsley, if desired.

title: cole slaw(servings:  8)
directions: Mix together all ingredients except oil and vinegar.
Cook oil and vinegar with generous amounts of black pepper until in a full boil.
Pour over cabbage and mix well.
Cover tightly and marinate 6 hours.
Do not refrigerate.

title: meat stew
directions: Cut meat into small pieces, roll in seasoned flour and brown in the fat in a heavy kettle.
Make sure every piece is well browned for best flavor.
Add 2 cups of water and simmer in tightly covered kettle until meat is tender (about 2 hours).
Then add vegetables which have been cut into fairly large chunks and continue cooking in covered kettle until vegetables are tender.
Add catsup, salt to taste and just a little flour in cold water to thicken if broth is too soupy.
Serve while steaming hot.
Ma's cooking.

title: lemon sauce
directions: Mix dry ingredients; add boiling water gradually, stirring constantly.
Cook over low heat until thick and clear.
Add butter and lemon.

title: seafood casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients, except bread crumbs, salt, pepper and butter.
Pour into casserole and top with a mixture of bread crumbs and melted butter.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until bubbly.

title: chicken and wild rice
directions: Prepare rice according to directions.
Saute onions and celery in margarine until onion is soft.
Add mushrooms, pimento, chicken and mushroom soup.
Simmer 15 minutes.
Mix cooked rice with other ingredients and put in baking dish.
Cover with grated cheese. Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: pumpkin cake
directions: Pour prepared cake mix into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix eggs and pumpkin pie mix together and spoon or pour slowly over cake dough.
Then pour 1/2 cup boiling water over this.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Mix all.
Place in a 13 x 9-inch pan and refrigerate 15 hours. Bake in a 350° oven for 1 hour and serve hot.
Knife should be dry when tested.
Handy to make the afternoon before you expect at least 10 people for breakfast.
Serves 10.

title: cucumber aspic(serves 12)
directions: Prepare Jell-O little light on water.
Put aside to slightly set.
Mix all other ingredients with sour cream and then blend together.

title: chicken marsala
directions: Flatten chicken pieces to about 1/4-inch thickness.
Combine egg and milk in shallow bowl.
Combine flour, seasonings and herbs on a plate.
Dip each piece into egg mixture, then into flour mixture to coat all sides.	Allow to rest briefly while preparing remainder of ingredients.
Over medium high heat, melt oil and butter in heavy skillet.
Brown the chicken pieces on both sides and remove to an ovenproof platter.
Place in a 200° oven to keep warm.

title: german pancakes
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Place butter in skillet and melt in oven.
In one bowl, beat eggs.
In second bowl, combine flour and milk.
Cream out lumps and combine with eggs.
Pour mixture into melted butter.
Bake 20 minutes. When done, sprinkle with lemon juice and powdered sugar.

title: oyster stew
directions: Heat oysters until they are plump and smoking hot.
Season with salt and pepper.
Heat milk with butter dropped in it to the boiling point.
As you take oysters and the milk off stove, pour the 2 together.
Serve at once in heated bowls with plenty of oyster crackers.
Serves 6.

title: swiss steak
directions: Salt and pepper pieces of steak and coat with flour.
Brown in oil and drain on paper.
Put steak in casserole dish and cover with layers of sliced onions, peppers and mushrooms.
Cover with tomato sauce and bake, covered, in a 325° oven for 45 minutes. Serves 6.

title: lemon pound cake
directions: Cream margarine, Crisco and sugar.
Add eggs and beat well. Add baking powder and flour; alternate with milk.
Add lemon flavoring.
Beat until fluffy.
Cook in preheated oven at 325° for 1 hour.

title: banana nut cake
directions: Cream butter, sugar and eggs until fluffy.
Stir in mashed bananas.
Sift soda with flour and add alternately with buttermilk.
Add nuts and vanilla.
Cook until toothpick comes out clean at 325°.
(Don't overcook.)

title: italian whipped cream icing
directions: Combine flour and milk and cook over low flame until thick like a sauce.
Cool.
Cream butter or margarine, shortening, sugar and vanilla.
Beat this well until it is fluffy.
Then add this mixture with the flour and milk mixture.
Whip until nice and light.

title: quick chicken pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cook and bone chicken.
Put in baking dish.
Mix milk and flour; salt and pepper.
Add celery soup. Pour flour mixture over chicken and bake 45 minutes at 350°. Makes its own crust.

title: chicken soup(by a "navy" cook)
directions: After chicken boils, skim.
Add seasonings, celery and onion. Boil 1 hour.
Take meat off bones; discard skin.
Strain out vegetables and return chicken to clear soup.
Add either cooked noodles or rice to soup if desired.
I like it plain.
Very nice for sick people.

title: cinnamon graham cracker cookies
directions: Take a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan and spread aluminum foil in the bottom.
Place a single layer of crackers on the foil.
In a pan, melt butter and margarine.
Add sugar and bring to a boil. Boil 3 to 4 minutes.
Pour over graham crackers.
Sprinkle pecans on top. Bake at 350° for 10 minutes. Remove from oven and let cool. Break into pieces and eat.

title: cocktail sausages and pineapple
directions: Lightly brown sausages in a large frying pan (no oil needed) and set aside.
Mix pineapple chunks and juice, brown sugar, Worcestershire sauce, cinnamon and pepper sauce.
Heat until boiling point.
Add sausages and simmer until flavors are blended. Serve hot with picks.

title: sloppy joes
directions: Cook ground chuck, onion, green pepper and celery in Dutch oven.
Add Sloppy Joes mix and Spatini mix, ketchup, water, tomato sauce, sugars and spices.
Simmer 30 minutes.

title: chili rellenos casserole
directions: In skillet, brown ground beef and onions.
Drain.
Add salt and pepper.
Cut green chili in half lengthwise and remove seeds. Place half chili in large baking dish (greased).
Spread meat mixture over chili; top with shredded cheese.
Arrange remaining chili over mixture.
Combine remaining ingredients; beat until smooth.
Pour over meat-chili mixture.
Bake at 360° for 45 to 60 minutes or until knife inserted comes out clean.
Let cool 5 minutes and cut into squares.
Serves 12 people.

title: no bake chocolate chip cookies
directions: Mix together and roll into balls.

title: carrot cake
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Add oil and blend.
Add eggs, 1 at a time, and beat.
Add carrots and nuts.
Bake in 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 1 hour.

title: sweet potato pone
directions: Mix in order given and heat thoroughly.
Put in covered baking dish.
Dot with butter, sugar and nutmeg.
Cover and bake 3 hours in moderate oven.
May be served with hard sauce or whipped cream or plain.

title: microwave marmalade pears
directions: Mix 1/3 cup marmalade and the orange juice in square microwavable dish, 8 x 8 x 2-inches or round microwavable dish, 8 x 1 1/2-inches.
Arrange pears, cut side down, in sauce.
Cover tightly and microwave on High until pears are almost tender when pierced with fork, 4 to 6 minutes.
Let stand 3 minutes.
Spoon into bowls.
Refrigerate.
Swirl sour cream and 1 tablespoon of orange marmalade.
Spoon over pears.

title: divinity with a dixieland beat
directions: In a heavy saucepan, combine sugar, corn syrup and water. Cook syrup slowly, stirring constantly with a wooden spoon, until sugar dissolves and syrup reaches boiling stage.
Place candy thermometer in saucepan.
Boil syrup, without stirring, over medium heat until thermometer registers 256°.
Remove from heat. Beat egg whites until stiff peaks form.
Pour hot syrup slowly into egg whites, beating constantly.
Continue to beat mixture until it holds shape and loses gloss.
Stir in vanilla and pecans. Drop onto wax paper with a tablespoon.

title: puppy chow
directions: Melt chocolate chips, peanut butter and margarine in a saucepan.
Put cereal in a large bowl.
Pour chocolate mix over cereal and toss to coat.
Let cool in fridge for 1 hour.
Put into a bowl with a lid.
Pour about 1 cup powdered sugar over cereal mixture.
Put on lid and shake to coat.
If cereal is not white, add more powdered sugar.
Store in refrigerator.

title: a. morgan meal
directions: Form hamburger into medium sized, equally portioned patties. Place in large baking dish.
Cover patties with mixture of carrots and potatoes.
Top with onion slices.
Pour Worcestershire on top until mixture is nearly covered.
