Add 1/4 cup water.
Cover baking dish with foil wrap.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: ham in pastry
directions: Mix mustard, sherry and cloves.
Spread over ham.
Roll out dough.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Place ham on crust. Cover ham on all sides and flute edges.
Mix egg yolk and brush crust.
Prick and bake at 400° for 30 minutes.

title: caramel icing
directions: Combine butter, cream and brown sugar together.
Bring to a rolling boil.
Remove from heat and let cool.
Gradually add confectioners sugar until you get your desired thickness.
You may need to double this recipe if you really like caramel icing.

title: cheese sauce
directions: Mix milk, flour, salt, pepper and margarine in saucepan.
Heat to boiling over medium heat, stirring constantly.
Boil and stir 1 minute. Remove from heat. Stir in remaining ingredients until cheese is melted.

title: sausage stuffing
directions: Saute celery, onion and parsley in 3/4 cup butter.
Add cooked sausage.
Mix with stuffing cubes, broth and eggs.
Toss lightly until moistened.
Rub turkey with 1 tablespoon lemon juice and 1/4 cup melted butter.
Stuff into 18 to 24 pound turkey or separately in covered casserole for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: spicy stuffing
directions: Brown sausage with onion.
Add water and simmer for 30 minutes. Add spices and celery.
Add meat mixture with broth to bread.
Mix well, adding more water if too dry.
Put stuffing in turkey or chicken, or in a buttered pan, covered with foil.
Bake at 350° until chicken or turkey is done, or bake in pan for 45 minutes and serve hot.

title: baked chicken breasts(mom's)
directions: Wrap 1 slice bacon around each piece of chicken and roll up. Cover bottom of large baking dish (greased) with beef.
Place chicken on top.
Mix soup and sour cream and pour over chicken. Bake in a 275° oven for 3 hours.

title: cheesy-tuna-onion fondue
directions: Combine all ingredients in fondue pot, mixing well.
Cover and cook on low for 1 to 2 hours.
Serve with bread, crackers or over buttered toast.

title: magic cookie bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a 13 x 9-inch baking pan, melt oleo in oven.
Sprinkle crumbs over melted oleo.
Pour sweetened condensed milk evenly over crumbs.
Top with remaining ingredients.
Press down firmly over entire top of ingredients. Bake
25 to 30 minutes or until lightly browned.
Cool.
Cut into bars.

title: cocoa brownies supreme
directions: Cream together shortening and sugar.
Add vanilla and eggs. Add cocoa and mix thoroughly.
Mix dry ingredients together and add to other mixture.
Stir until just incorporated.
Spread in greased 9 X 13 inch pan.
Bake at 350 for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients together.
Brown meat, onion and peppers; then add to corn mixture.
Pour into real hot greased skillet and bake about 30 minutes at 375°.
Top with grated cheese.

title: afloat boaters breakfast(swiss muesli)
directions: Combine oats, water, apples, prunes, honey, lemon juice and cinnamon; cover and refrigerate overnight.

title: baked chicken sandwiches
directions: Trim crust off bread and butter each side.
Place 8 slices of bread in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Saute mushrooms in 2 tablespoons butter.
Cover bread with mixture of mushrooms, chicken, eggs, olives, mayonnaise and onions.
Arrange remaining 8 slices of bread on top.
Combine soup, sour cream and sherry; pour over sandwich.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.

title: crusty tuna-bean bake
directions: Drain tuna; flake.
Mix tuna with 1/2 cup soup, bread crumbs, onion, eggs, salt and 1/8 teaspoon pepper.
Line a greased baking dish, 13 x 9 x 2-inch with tuna mixture, letting the mixture extend up the sides of the dish.

title: trout with dill butter
directions: Trout is available all the year round, fresh or frozen.
Allow frozen trout to thaw before using.
Rub the insides of the trout with salt,
allspice, 1/4 teaspoon of the pepper and half the lemon juice.
Mix the dill with the butter and spread inside the trout.
Lay the fish on the broiler pan or barbecue rack; brush with oil and broil or barbecue for about 5 minutes on each side.

title: chicken italian
directions: Cut chicken in pieces.
Sprinkle with seasoning, garlic salt and lemon pepper each side of chicken.
Roll chicken in Ritz cracker crumbs.
Melt butter and pour over chicken pieces.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes uncovered.

title: angie's chicken cacciatore
directions: Brown chicken on both sides.
Remove chicken and saute 3 slices of onion, then put chicken back in skillet.
Add tomato sauce, water and seasonings.
Cover and cook on medium for 20 minutes, then cook, uncovered, for 15 minutes.
Serve over noodles or rice.

title: chicken enchilada casserole
directions: Mix everything together except potato chips.
Heat in large saucepan.
Crush Doritos and cover bottom of large casserole dish. Layer mixture three times.
Bake 20 minutes at 400°.

title: quick yeast rolls
directions: Heat milk and shortening to lukewarm; put yeast into this mixture.
Add flour, sugar and salt.
Place on floured board and roll out and cut.
Let rise 1 hour and bake at 400°.

title: texas caviar
directions: Drain everything and mix in large bowl.
Chop all raw vegetables.
Mix in together.
Let stand in refrigerator overnight, covered.

title: crispy baked chicken
directions: In a small bowl, combine the first 5 ingredients.
Coat the chicken with mayonnaise mixture, then with the bread crumbs. Arrange on rack in broiler pan.
Bake for 40 minutes or until golden brown and tender in a 425° oven.

title: cheese ball snack mix
directions: In a bowl, combine the cashews, cheese balls, cereal, pretzels and chow mein noodles. In another bowl, combine the remaining ingredients. Pour over cereal mixture and toss to coat. Transfer to an ungreased 15 x 10 x 1-inch baking pan. Bake at 250° for 1 hour, stirring every 15 minutes. Yield: 6 cups.

title: chow mein
directions: Cut meat in small cubes. Brown meat and onions for 45 min. Cover with water, add celery and tsp. salt. Simmer 2 hours. Then add bean sprouts and water chestnuts. Simmer for another hour. Thicken sauce with flour and water. Serve over rice or mashed potatoes.

title: tartar sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients; chill.
Serve with fish or deviled crabs.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Spread rolls out on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes, until golden brown.
Cool.
Cream together all other ingredients, except vegetables.
Spread cream cheese mixture on crust.
Sprinkle vegetables on top; cut into squares.

title: vegetable bean soup
directions: Cover ham hocks, bay leaves, basil, pepper and bouillon cubes with water.
Cook until meat separates from bones.
Discard bones. Cut up meat.
Add carrots, onion and ham.
Cook until tender, about 1 hour.
Add tomato juice and tomato sauce and simmer 30 minutes.
Add kidney beans, macaroni and potato.
Simmer 30 minutes.
Add cabbage.
Cook about another 30 minutes.
Adjust seasoning, if desired.

title: lime cream pie
directions: Mix limeade and milk.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Pour into baked pie shell or graham cracker crust.
Chill before serving.

title: million dollar pie
directions: Drain pineapple well.
Mix with other ingredients.
Mix well. Place in crust and chill.
Makes 2 pies.

title: steak and potatoes
directions: Cut meat into serving size pieces.
Coat meat with mixture of flour, salt and pepper.
Brown steak in shortening.
Add water, potatoes and onion.
Season with salt and pepper.
Reduce heat, cover and cook about 45 minutes.

title: church punch
directions: Mix all ingredients, then fill the container with water to get the full gallon.

title: brown sugar shortbread
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Butter an 8-inch round cake pan.
In medium mixing bowl, combine butter, sugar and vanilla.
Beat with mixer until fluffy.
Gradually add flour, 1/4 cup at a time, by hand.
Transfer to pan; pat dough evenly in layer.
Prick surface all over with a fork.
Bake about 50 minutes, until light brown. This shortbread will melt in your mouth.

title: praline cake
directions: Cream butter or margarine with sugar until light.
Add egg yolks, one at a time, and beat until fluffy.
Combine sifted cake flour with cream of tartar and soda.
Sift again.
Add to the batter alternately with the buttermilk.
Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites.
Bake in 9 x 13-inch greased and floured pan at 350° for 50 minutes.
Remove from oven and spread with topping.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Bring to a boil sugar, milk, cocoa, butter and salt.
Add oats and coconut.
Spoon on ungreased pan and let chill.

title: st. nicholas day cookies(december 6)
directions: Cream butter, shortening and sugar.
Add sour cream alternately with dry ingredients.
Stir in the nuts.
Knead dough into rolls.
Wrap the rolls in wax paper and chill in refrigerator overnight.
Roll dough very thin; cut into shapes (St. Nicholas, birds, fish, animals, etc.).
Bake in moderate oven at 375° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: zucchini bake
directions: Combine onion and zucchini in 1 cup water.
Cover and heat to boiling. Steam 4 minutes.
Drain.
Beat eggs with milk, flour and salt.
Combine with zucchini and onion.
Add mushrooms, Mozzarella cheese and all but 1/2 cup of Parmesan cheese. Turn into greased 1 1/2-quart baking dish.
Sprinkle with 1/2 cup Parmesan cheese. Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Serves 4.

title: lime salad
directions: Mix gelatin and 1 cup of hot water; add cream cheese and marshmallows.
Stir until almost melted.
Add 1 cup of cold water; mix and refrigerate until jelly-like.
Stir in pineapple, nuts and whipped cream.
Pour in oblong or square dish and refrigerate until formed.

title: 90 minute soft pretzels
directions: Mix 1 cup flour, sugar, salt and undissolved yeast.
Heat 1 cup water and margarine to 120° to 130°.
Gradually add to dry ingredients and beat 2 minutes at medium speed.
Add 1/2 cup flour. Beat at high 2 minutes.
Stir in enough additional flour to make a soft dough.
Knead on floured board 5 minutes (or in mixer with dough hooks approximately 3 minutes).
May need to add additional flour.
Put in greased bowl.
Turn to grease top.
Cover.
Let rise in draft free place 40 minutes.
Divide dough into 12 pieces.
Roll into 20-inch ropes.
Shape into pretzels.
Place on greased cookie sheets.
Cover and let rest 15 minutes.
Mix egg yolk and 1 tablespoon water.
Brush on pretzels.
Sprinkle with coarse salt. Bake at 375° for 20 minutes or until done.
Cool on racks.

title: hello dollies
directions: Melt the butter in an
8-ounce square pan.
Mix the graham cracker crumbs in with the butter and press into bottom of pan. Add in layers the coconut, chocolate chips and pecans.
Pour Eagle Brand milk over all.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cool completely before cutting into small squares.

title: oatmeal chocolate chip cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Beat margarine or butter and sugar until creamy.
Add eggs, vanilla and milk.
Beat well.
Stir in oatmeal, chocolate chips, flour and nuts along with soda and baking powder. Bake 10 to 12 minutes on an ungreased cookie sheet.
Cool completely.

title: fluffy cherry salad
directions: Mix jello, sugar and pineapple in saucepan;
cook until pineapple turns
red.
Cool.
Fold in cottage cheese, nuts and Cool Whip.
Put in 9 x 13-inch Pyrex dish and congeal.
Cut in 3-inch squares and serve on lettuce leaf.

title: brunch easter eggs(makes 6 servings)
directions: In a large saucepan, melt butter; add onion and parsley.
Cook until onion is tender.
Add mushrooms and cook until tender. Sprinkle with flour; mix well.
Stir in milk, orange juice, salt, pepper and tarragon.
Place over low heat and cook, stirring constantly, until sauce comes to boil.
Stir in ham and eggs; heat.
Serve over toasted muffin halves.

title: zucchini, tomato and swiss cheese pie
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Using 1/2 tablespoon butter, grease the pie plate, then sprinkle the bread crumbs over the bottom and sides.
Heat olive oil in large skillet over medium heat.
Add onion and garlic; saute 10 minutes.
Stir in the diced tomatoes; saute 5 minutes.
Raise the heat to high.
Mix in the zucchini, fennel seed, salt and pepper.
Cook until zucchini is barely tender, about 5 minutes.
(The mixture should begin to stick to pan.)
Remove pan from heat and cool 5 minutes.
Bring to room temperature before proceeding.
Beat eggs in large bowl.
Stir in milk, then mix in the zucchini mixture.
Pour 1/2 into prepared pie plate; top with Swiss cheese, then pour on remaining vegetable mixture.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese and dot with remaining butter.
Bake 30 minutes.
Let sit 10 minutes.

title: hearty winter vegetable soup
directions: *One tablespoon gives the soup broth a nice smoked flavor with a little heat.

title: linda's raw cranberry salad
directions: Pick and wash cranberries.
Drain well and grind in blender. Stir sugar into ground cranberries; let stand overnight.
Whip cream quite stiff.
Fold in cranberries, celery, marshmallows and coarsely chopped pecans.
Chill thoroughly and serve.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.
Very good.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Follow directions for cooking broccoli; drain.
Mix all ingredients together, using only 1/2 bag of stuffing mix.
Put in a 2-quart casserole dish and use the rest of stuffing mix to cover.
Bake approximately 30 minutes at 350°.
Let set in refrigerator overnight.
Reheat and serve.

title: veggie pizza
directions: Open package of dinner rolls and pat into a jelly roll pan. Bake according to directions.
When cool, mix mayonnaise with cream cheese and spices; spread on crust.
Cover with veggies of your choice, all cut the same size, and sprinkle on top of pizza crust.
Refrigerate leftovers.

title: pasta vegetable salad
directions: Cook macaroni to desired doneness.
Drain and rinse with cold water.
In large bowl, combine cooked macaroni, zucchini, broccoli, onions, mushrooms, artichokes and salad dressing; toss gently.
Cover and refrigerate at least 3 hours to blend flavors. Just before serving, stir in tomatoes and avocados.
Makes 12 (1/2 cup) servings.

title: spinach and rotelle salad
directions: Cook rotelle according to package directions; drain and toss with 1/4 cup olive oil.
Slice spinach leaves crosswise; quarter and strip.

title: french salad dressing
directions: Combine all ingredients in a blender and blend well.
Yields 1 quart.

title: spanish lime pie(serves 10 to 12)
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Mix and add melted butter.
Press into 9-inch pie plate.
Bake 8 minutes or until light brown.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together well.
Pour into pie shell at 375° for 45 minutes or until knife inserted comes back clean.

title: cocoa drop cookies
directions: Mix well the sugar, cocoa, canned milk and oleo.
Bring to a full boil. Remove from heat and add peanut butter, vanilla and oatmeal. Drop by spoonful on waxed paper.

title: oriental salad
directions: Shred cabbage into small pieces.
Chop green onions. Put cabbage, onions and as many bean sprouts as desired into a container until ready to serve.

title: sweet minglers
directions: Melt chocolate in microwave or stove top.
Stir in peanut butter.
Gently stir in cereal until coated.
Gently toss cereal in plastic bag filled with the confectioners sugar until well coated.
Store in refrigerator in airtight container.

title: cinnamon-nut squares
directions: Cream butter or margarine.
Gradually add sugar and continue creaming until light and fluffy.
Add egg yolk, flour, cinnamon and salt and mix well.
Spread in buttered 15 x 10 x 1-inch pan.
Brush with lightly beaten egg white and sprinkle with nuts, then press nuts into surface.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Oil 9 x 9 pan and preheat oven to 350°. Sift together the dry ingredients and set aside. In a medium sized bowl, combine the oil, honey and applesauce. Beat the egg and stir into the oil mixture. Gradually stir in the dry ingredients. Fold in the raisins and nuts. Pour the batter into the pan. Bake for 40 minutes. Cool cake in the pan on a wire rack.

title: tortellini soup
directions: Combine green onions and vegetable broth in 5-quart saucepan. Bring to a boil.
Gradually stir tortellini into broth.
Reduce heat.
Cook for 3 minutes.
Stir in pea pods.
Cook for 3 minutes. Stir in pesto sauce.
Ready.

title: macaroni soup
directions: In pan over medium heat, cook sausage, onion, garlic and oregano until sausage is browned.
Spoon off fat.
Add soup, broth, undrained tomatoes, water and pepper.
heat to boiling. Reduce heat to low.
Cook 15 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Stir in macaroni; cook 10 minutes more or until macaroni is tender, stirring occasionally.

title: quick cookies
directions: Boil the milk, sugar and shortening together for 1 minute. Add the remaining ingredients.
Stir and drop by spoonfuls onto waxed paper.

title: cheese ball
directions: Combine softened cream cheese and Cheddar cheese, mixing well. Add onions, lemon juice, Worcestershire sauce and seasonings. Mix well.
Shape into ball and roll in nuts.
Serve with crackers.

title: betsy's lemon brownies
directions: Mix 2 cups flour and powdered sugar.
Cut in Crisco.
Press into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: macaroni and tomatoes
directions: Cook macaroni in saucepan with water to cover, adding salt. Bring to a rolling boil.
Cut heat off and cover saucepan for 5 minutes.
Drain water.
Stir macaroni and add onion.
Bring to a slow boil.
Cover saucepan and let the onion cook 2 minutes.
Add tomatoes, sugar, butter and pepper.

title: bean salad
directions: Mix all together. Place in fridge a few hours or overnight.

title: johnny cake
directions: Mix all ingredients in large bowl by hand.
Mix well.
Pour into greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes until center is set.
Serve warm with maple syrup or cold as a cereal with strawberry and peanut butter.
Pour cold milk over. Good for a snack or as a main breakfast food.

title: scalloped pineapple
directions: Place bread chunks in the bottom of a well-greased 9 x 12 x 2-inch baking dish.
Spread drained pineapple chunks over bread. Beat eggs slightly.
Mix in sugar and melted butter.
Pour over chunks of bread and pineapple.
Bake at 375° for about 40 minutes. Serves 8 to 10.

title: delicious pound cake
directions: Cream butter and Crisco; beat well.
Add sugar slowly and beat well.
Add eggs one at a time and beat thoroughly.
Sift flour, baking powder and salt.
Alternate milk and sifted ingredients while combining with butter, Crisco, egg and sugar mixture.
Add lemon extract.
Pour into greased and floured tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 20 minutes.

title: congealed salad
directions: Mix jello according to directions on box.
Add strawberries, pineapple, banana and pecans.
Pour half of the ingredients into bowl.
Let congeal.
Spread half of the sour cream on this, then add remainder of mixture on that. Spread remainder of sour cream on top.
Let congeal.

title: pastry mix (flaky pie crust)
directions: Sift flour once and measure.
Add salt and sift dry ingredients into mixing bowl.
Add shortening and cut it lightly and quickly into the flour until lumps of fat are about size of peas and are evenly coated with flour.
Add cold water (ice water is preferable).
Sprinkle water into flour and fat mixture, about a teaspoon at a time and mix lightly until firm ball of dough is formed.
If possible, chill dough before rolling out.
Roll pastry on lightly floured board until it is about 1/8-inch in thickness. Fit dough loosely, yet closely, into pan.

title: lemon juice ketchup
directions: Mix ingredients and refrigerate.
Must be kept in refrigerator because recipe has no preservatives.

title: all-summer fruit coffee cake
directions: * Some suggestions are: blueberries; pitted sweet cherries; pitted apricots, nectarines or plums, sliced 1/2-inch thick; peeled and pitted peaches, sliced 1/2-inch thick; and/or peeled and cored apples, sliced 1/4-inch thick.

title: chicken tetrazzini
directions: Boil chicken.
Add salt, pepper, garlic powder and season salt.
Debone.
Save broth and bring to a hard boil.
Add spaghetti to broth.
Boil.
Turn down to a rolling boil.
Cook until spaghetti is done.
Add chicken.

title: dutch apple dessert
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
In medium bowl, combine apples, sweetened condensed milk and cinnamon; set aside.
In large bowl, cut 1/2 cup margarine into 1 cup biscuit mix and sugar.
Cut in remaining 2 tablespoons margarine until crumbly.
Add nuts. Sprinkle evenly over apple mixture.
Bake 1 hour or until golden. Serve warm with ice cream, if desired.

title: 1st prize chocolate cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour 2 round cake pans. Melt margarine and chocolate together.
Cool.
Beat eggs until frothy.
Add buttermilk and vanilla.
Blend dry ingredients into buttermilk mixture.
Add chocolate mixture.
Pour into pans.
Bake about 30 minutes.
Cool and frost.

title: mexican dip
directions: Layer in order in oblong Pyrex dish.
Serve with taco chips.

title: chicken fusilli
directions: In a skillet, cook the chicken breast strips in the oil and butter. Cook the fusilli noodles according to package directions; drain. In a large saucepan, combine the Parmesan cheese, heavy cream, basil, parsley and garlic powder. Cook slowly until thoroughly heated. Then add the noodles and the chicken to cheese sauce. Stir until well blended.

title: creamy pie
directions: Combine crumbs and margarine, pressing bottom of oblong dish. Bake for 13 minutes at 325°.
Chill.

title: zippy's fat-free salad dressing
directions: Combine all ingredients in jar with tight fitting top.
Cover; shake until blended.
Store, covered, in refrigerator.
Shake well before using.

title: potato salad
directions: Boil potatoes until tender; drain and let cool.
Put the next 5 ingredients into the potatoes.
Stir.
Place egg slices on bottom.

title: pistachio inside-outside cake
directions: Blend all ingredients in large bowl, and beat at medium speed for 2 minutes.
Bake in a greased, floured 10-inch Bundt pan at 350° for 50 minutes.
Cool 15 minutes; remove from pan and cool on rack.
Cut into 3 horizontal layers.
Spread 1/3 cup frosting between each layer and spoon rest into center.
Garnish middle with chopped nuts and chill.

title: strawberry delight
directions: Mix together and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cool.

title: no bake granola bars
directions: In a medium saucepan, combine corn syrup and brown sugar. Bring to a boil, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Stir in peanut butter and vanilla and blend well.
Add granola, raisins and/or marshmallows.
Mix well.
Press into an 8 or 9-inch square pan.
Cool and cut into bars.

title: crock pot beans
directions: Mix all together in a large crock pot.
Bake on low all night.
In morning turn to high for 3 to 4 hours.
Ready by noon. Do not stir.

title: mississippi mud
directions: Melt margarine and cocoa together. Add eggs, sugar and other ingredients.
Beat with a spoon. Bake 30 to 35 minutes in a
350° oven.
Set out and sprinkle with miniature marshmallows while hot.

title: fruit cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar together in large bowl. Add eggs, one at a time. Add whiskey and salt. In another bowl, combine cherries, pineapple and pecans with 3/4 cup flour. Stir to coat fruit. Add flour, one cup at a time, to butter and sugar mixture. When this is smooth, add fruit. Mixture will be thick and hard to stir. Spoon mixture into floured pans. Either one large Bundt pan or 2 loaf pans. I use decorative ones. Cook at 250° for 3 hours or 350° for 1 1/2 hours. This is a great cake!

title: strawberry short cake(low-fat)
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water.
Add cold water (or ice if you are in a hurry) and let stand until thick as egg whites.
Using a jello mold or oblong baking dish, put pieces of cake and strawberry slices layered in dish.
After each layer, pour Jell-O mixture.
Top with Cool Whip and garnish with strawberry slices.

title: steak diane
directions: Sprinkle steaks with lemon pepper seasoning.
Coat a large nonstick skillet with cooking spray; add margarine.
Place over medium-high heat until margarine melts.
Add steaks and cook 5 minutes each side or until desired degree of doneness.
Transfer to platter, keep warm.
Add lemon juice, Worcestershire sauce and mustard to skillet; bring to boil, stirring constantly.
Pour over steaks.
Garnish and serve immediately.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Add baking powder, soda, salt and spices and sift together. Cream butter; add sugar and cream together until light and fluffy. Add egg, raisins and nuts.
Add flour, with a small amount at a time, beating after each addition until smooth.
Bake in greased pan, 7 x 5 x 3-inches, in moderate oven, 350°, for about 1 hour.

title: jimmy carter cake
directions: Cream peanut butter and cream cheese together.
Add confectioners sugar and Cool Whip.
Mix and spread over cooled crust.
Then spread with a box of chocolate instant pudding (made according to directions on box) and then a layer of vanilla instant pudding.
Top with Cool Whip.
Refrigerate.

title: pound cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine ingredients.
Bake 1 hour and 10 minutes.

title: rolo cookies
directions: Combine flour, cocoa and soda in a small bowl.
Beat brown sugar, butter and white sugar until fluffy.
Add vanilla and eggs. Add flour mixture.
Stir in 1/2 cup pecans.
Shape 1 tablespoon dough around 1 Rolo candy.
Combine 1 tablespoons sugar and 1/2 cup pecans.
Press ball into mixture.
Place nut side up on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 7 to 9 minutes at 375° or just until cracked.

title: chicken and rice casserole
directions: Saute onion in a small amount of oil.
Add other ingredients and stir.
Pour into a casserole, cover and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: 3 bean salad
directions: Mix brown sugar, white sugar, vinegar and oil; let come to a boil on stove.
Pour over mixed vegetables and let sit overnight. Chill.

title: quick mexican dish
directions: Brown meat and onion;
drain and add the remaining ingredients, except shredded cheese and doritos.
Grease a 9 X 13 inch pan.
Crush Doritos and put half on bottom of pan, the remaining on top with shredded cheese.
Bake at 350 degrees for 25 minutes.
This may be made ahead.
Reheat well.

title: vegetable chili
directions: Saute onion and pepper in oil until onion becomes transparent. Add carrots, beans, mushroom pieces, tomato paste, water and spices.
Cook at low heat until carrot pieces are tender, about 1 hour.
Serve over steamed rice or dry toast points.
Serves four, with about half left for a second meal.
Sometimes it seems more flavorful at the second meal, when it's been reheated.

title: sausage a la russe
directions: Brown sausage meat and pour off extra fat.
Add onion and green pepper and cook 2 to 3 minutes.
Add tomatoes, macaroni and sugar.
Bring to boil.
Be sure macaroni is under liquid.
Cover and simmer 30 minutes, stir occasionally.
Stir in yogurt or sour cream, heat and add pepper to taste.
Sprinkle with parsley. Serves 4.

title: noodles romanoff
directions: Boil noodles in salted water until just tender.
Drain and combine gently with all remaining ingredients except sharp cheese. Place in a buttered 2-quart baking dish and sprinkle grated cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: diet chocolate cupcakes
directions: Mix by hand. Spray muffin pan with Pam.
Pour batter into 5 muffin tins.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: beef and bean round-up
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
In skillet brown beef and onion; drain. Stir in barbecue sauce, brown sugar and beans.
Heat until bubbly. Pour into 2 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Cut biscuits into halves and place around the edge of the bowl.
Sprinkle cheese on the dish and bake at 375° for 22 to 27 minutes or until biscuits are golden brown.

title: reuben chicken
directions: Brown chicken and place in casserole pan.
Cover with sauerkraut, drained; drizzle with Thousand Island dressing.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Place slices of cheese on top the last 10 minutes.

title: shepherd pie
directions: Brown beef with onion and Worcestershire. Mix gravy mix as directed, add to meat and let simmer a few minutes. Pour into casserole dish, top with corn, then cheese and mashed potatoes. Top with more cheese if desired. Bake at 375° for about 20 minutes.

title: chicken loaf
directions: Boil chicken in seasoned water until tender.
Let cool in broth. Skin and cut in 1-inch cubes.
Mix everything together. Bake in greased 3-quart casserole for 1 hour at 350°.
Serve with following Mushroom Sauce.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: chocolate chess pie
directions: Melt first 2 ingredients together over very low heat.
Mix all ingredients together; pour into unbaked pie crust.
Cook at 350° for 25 minutes or until pie begins to crack.

title: angel fluffy salad
directions: Pour water over jello, cream cheese and marshmallows.
Beat with mixer or use blender.
Chill until partially set.
Whip up again.
Add Cool Whip or whipped cream and pineapple.
Chill until firm.

title: sunflower pineapple slaw
directions: Drain pineapple; reserve 2 tablespoons juice.
Combine pineapple with cabbage, carrots and sunflower seeds.
Stir together the mayonnaise, orange juice, reserved pineapple juice, salt and pepper.
Pour over salad mixture; toss and chill.
Serves 6.

title: jewish latkes "potato pancakes"
directions: Mix onion and potato together.
Add soda.
Drain off any liquid and beat in remaining ingredients.
Heat oil and drop batter by tablespoons onto pan.
Fry until golden on the outside; turn only once.
Serve with sour cream.

title: tender pork chops
directions: In medium bowl, mix soup and milk until smooth.
Place pork chops in a baking dish and pour soup over top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: deluxe chipped beef
directions: Heat oil; add raw vegetables and cook until they begin to turn brown.
Stir mushroom soup, water and beef into vegetables.
Cook, stirring as needed, until thickened.
Add pimiento and eggs. Serve on noodles, along with a carrot salad.
Makes 6 servings.

title: beefy bites
directions: Mix all ingredients in bowl. Roll into small balls. Enjoy.

title: chicken supreme with apples and cream
directions: Saute chicken breasts in oil, 4 minutes on each side on medium-high heat.
Remove from pan.
Add butter.
Add shallots and peeled and sliced apples.
Saute 3 minutes.
Add Calvados and chicken broth.
Reduce by half.
Add heavy cream, tarragon and chicken.
Cook on high until thickened.

title: western style chili
directions: Cook onions and green pepper in oil.
Add ground beef; brown. Add remaining ingredients.
Simmer for 30 minutes.

title: standing against the wiles of the devil(eph. 6:10-18)
directions: Mix together thoroughly and pray always.

title: peach pie filling fruit salad
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Chill for several hours.
May also serve as dessert with pound cake or plain cookies.
Makes 6 servings.

title: german short ribs
directions: Coat short ribs with 2 tablespoons flour, salt and pepper. Brown in shortening.
In crock-pot, combine ribs, onions, wine, chili sauce, brown sugar, vinegar, Worcestershire sauce, mustard and chili powder.
Cover and cook on low for 6 to 8 hours.
Turn heat to high and thicken with remaining 2 tablespoons flour (or cornstarch), dissolved in water.
Cook on high for 10 minutes. Serve over wide egg noodles.
Serves 5 or 6.

title: 2 chess pies
directions: Cream butter, sugar, corn meal and flour together.
Mix well. Add vanilla and vinegar.
Mix well.
Best if use electric beater, about 1 to 2 minutes.
Pour into unbaked pie shells.
Cook in oven about 45 minutes or until set good at 325° to 350°.

title: lemon icebox pie
directions: Pie Shell:
Crumble vanilla wafer cookies in bottom of pie pan. Circle edge with whole cookies

title: scotchies
directions: Blend butter and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each egg.
Stir in vanilla, flour and baking powder.
Mix well; stir in nuts.
Pour into greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cool in pan; cut into 24 bars.

title: old bay seasonings chicken cakes(delicious)
directions: Break bread and moisten with milk.
Mix all ingredients and shape into cakes.
Fry quickly until brown.

title: carrot pudding
directions: Cream oleo with sugar.
Add egg and water, then the carrots. Sift together the dry ingredients and add to cream mixture.
Mix thoroughly.
Spoon into greased 6 to 8-cup ring mold.
Bake in 350° oven for about 40 minutes.
This is a good dish to serve with meats.
Serves 6.

title: thick french toast
directions: In a small bowl, beat eggs (or substitute), milk, sugar and salt until smooth and blended.
Arrange the bread in a single layer in a 9-inch square baking dish.
Pour the egg mixture over the bread, turning each slice to coat evenly.
Cover and refrigerate the dish with the bread and egg mixture overnight. (This overnight refrigeration step is extremely important for success because it gives all the good bacteria time to work.)
The next morning, saute the bread in a skillet
until it is golden brown.
This takes about 2 minutes per side.

title: broccoli with linguini
directions: Cut flowerets from broccoli.
Using a sharp knife, peel stalks, cut into 1/2-inch pieces. Steam broccoli in a small amount of salted water until crisp-tender.

title: taco filling
directions: Drain oil from hamburger.
Cook 30 minutes, stirring occasionally.

title: monkey bread
directions: Mix 1/2 cup sugar and 1 teaspoon cinnamon and set aside.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Defrost hash browns. Combine next 7 ingredients and mix with hash browns. Put all in 3-quart casserole. Saut corn flakes in butter and sprinkle on top. Cover and bake at 350° for about 40 minutes.

title: muffins by the pailful(hi-fiber)
directions: Combine brans and salt in large bowl. Stir in boiling water; mix; then add buttermilk. Cool to lukewarm. In mixing bowl, cream together sugar and shortening. Add eggs one at a time, beating well after each addition. Stir into bran mixture. Let set. Combine flour and baking soda. Add to bran mixture and stir just enough to dampen ingredients. Store batter in refrigerator until ready to use. Will keep for 4 weeks.

title: pound cake
directions: Stir together margarine, eggs, sugar and Crisco first.
Add flour, milk and flavoring.
Stir all together.
Do not preheat oven.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour, then 30 minutes at 350°.

title: chocolate zucchini bars
directions: Mix together and bake on cookie sheet at 350° for 18 to 20 minutes.
Can also be frosted, if desired.
They taste just like a brownie.
The kids can't tell the difference.

title: ham roll-ups(microwave)
directions: Microwave cream cheese in small bowl at High (100%) until softened.
Stir in Cheddar cheese, green onion and mustard. Spread cheese mixture on ham slices.
Roll from narrow end.
Cut each roll into 4 pieces.
Secure with toothpick.
Place on paper towel in microwave at High for 1 to 2 minutes.

title: freezer pickles
directions: Mix the cucumbers, onions and green bell pepper in a large bowl.
Sprinkle with salt and let set all night.
Drain.
Wash with cold water.
Mix sugar, vinegar and celery seed together and boil.
Let cool and pour over pickles.
Put in freezer.

title: cheeseburger pie
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Bake pastry shell 8 minutes.
Remove from oven.
Reduce oven to 350°.
Cut 6 slices cheese into pieces; set aside.

title: sour cream banana pudding
directions: Mix pudding using 2 1/2 cups milk.
Add sour cream and whipped topping.
Mix with electric mixer for 5 minutes.
Put layer of mixture on bottom of a deep dish, then add layers of vanilla wafers and thin sliced bananas. Continue layering until all mixture is used.
Chill for 4 hours.
Makes a large pudding.

title: broccoli and cheese casserole
directions: Cook broccoli in one pot; drain well.
Saute butter and onions in small frypan or in a bowl in the microwave.
Cook 3/4 cup rice as package directs in another pot.
In a large pot or bowl, mix together cooked and drained broccoli, sauteed onions, 1/4 cup Velveeta cheese and one can of soup.
Fold in rice.
Pour mixture into your favorite casserole dish.
Bake in 350° oven for 20 to 30 minutes or until casserole is bubbly.

title: low calorie vanilla cream pie
directions: Combine milk, cornstarch, Sweet*10 and salt.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly, until mixture boils (approximately 1 minute).
Blend 1/2 cup
hot mixture into egg.
Then add the hot mixture and cook 1 minute more.
Remove from heat and add vanilla and food coloring.
Add the coconut if desired.
Pour into crust.

title: indian corn stew
directions: Heat oil in heavy skillet. Saute onion and green pepper. Cook until tender. Add meat and brown, stirring frequently. Add remaining ingredients. Simmer 1/2 hour. Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: million dollar pie
directions: Drain pineapple.
Mix lemon juice and milk.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Pour into pie crusts and chill.

title: strawberry pie (2)
directions: Mix half sugar with flour.
Cook strawberries, water and other half of the sugar until hot.
Add rest of ingredients.
Cook until thick.
Put in 2 pie shells.
Cool. Top with Cool Whip and chill.

title: white sauce(1928)
directions: Stir the Mazola, cornstarch and seasoning together in a small saucepan.
Gradually add the milk, stirring constantly.
Bring to a boiling point; boil 3 minutes.

title: toffee meringue torte
directions: Have egg whites at room temperature.
Add vanilla, cream of tartar and salt.
Beat to soft peaks.
Gradually add sugar; beat to stiff peaks.
Cut 2 (9-inch) circles of brown paper; place on cookie sheets.
Cover each with half meringue mixture.
Bake at 275° for 1 hour; let cool in oven.
(Can tint for holidays.) Combine whipped cream and crushed toffee bars.
Spread half between meringue layers and half on top.
Chill in refrigerator for at least 8 hours.
Serves 10.
A heavenly dessert!

title: angel crisp cookies
directions: Cream butter and margarine, then add sugars.
When mixed well add rest of ingredients.
Roll into balls by teaspoon size portions of dough.
May need to add flour to handle and reduce stickiness.
Dip the top of each ball into cold water then into sugar.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Cookies will be lightly brown.

title: fruit delight cobbler
directions: Mix all ingredients, except fruit.
Pour into a baking dish. Pour fruit on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until top is brown.

title: buttermilk pralines
directions: Pour milk, sugar and baking soda into large pot (it will foam up while cooking).
Stir to dissolve sugar.
Let it bubble on medium heat, stirring occasionally, until it turns brownish in color and reaches soft ball stage.
Use candy thermometer, if possible.

title: turkey soup
directions: Place turkey carcass and water in a large soup kettle.
Simmer over low heat for 4 to 5 hours.
Remove carcass from stock. Remove any meat and dice.
Return to stock along with rice, onion, celery, carrots, bay leaf and poultry seasoning.
Add remaining seasonings to taste.
Simmer over medium-low heat until the rice is cooked.
Yield: 8 servings (3-quarts).

title: dilled brussels sprouts
directions: Cook Brussels sprouts according to package directions, omitting salt; drain well.
Combine Brussels sprouts, Italian dressing, sliced green onions and dill weed in a medium mixing bowl, tossing gently.
Cover and refrigerate for at least 8 hours. Serve Brussels sprouts, using a slotted spoon.
Yields about 8 servings.

title: skillet dinner
directions: Brown ground beef.
Add onion and uncooked noodles.
Mix tomato juice with Worcestershire sauce, celery salt, salt and pepper.
Pour over noodle mixture.
Simmer 25 minutes until noodles are cooked.
Stir in sour cream.
Sprinkle with parsley flakes and serve.

title: hot and hearty stew
directions: Coat beef in mixture of flour, chili powder and salt.
Brown in hot shortening or lard in a large Dutch oven.
Add onions and garlic.
Cook until soft, then add tomatoes and crushed red pepper.
Cover and simmer 2 hours, then add potatoes and carrots and cook until vegetables are done, about 45 minutes.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: cranberry bread pudding
directions: Peel off just the rind of the orange, using a vegetable peeler.
Reserve peel, but not the pith.
Peel remaining pith from fruit; discard.
Section orange.

title: low calorie ambrosia
directions: Sprinkle gelatin over orange juice.
Let stand 5 minutes. Bring to a boil.
Remove from heat.
Add 2 tablespoons sugar and the 1 cup boiling water.
Stir until sugar is dissolved.
Pour into bowl.
Add lemon juice, lemon peel, orange juice and orange peel.
Set bowl in ice to chill, stirring occasionally, until thick as egg whites.
Beat egg whites and salt until foamy.
Add rest of sugar.
Beat gelatin.
Fold all together.
Chill for 3 hours.

title: divinity candy
directions: Mix sugar, syrup and water together. Cook until it forms a hard ball when dropped in cold water. Pour slowly over beaten egg whites. Beat until you can drop by spoon fulls on wax paper. Does better on a clear cold day.

title: polish doughnuts
directions: Scald milk and cool to 120°.
Add yeast and 2 cups flour.
Let this mixture stand for 1/2 hour to form a sponge.

title: lemon cream cheese frosting
directions: Let the cream cheese sit at room temperature for 3 hours.
Put it in a mixer bowl with finely grated peel of one lemon.
Add a blop of milk, a blop of lemon juice and approximately 1/3 cup of confectioners sugar.
Beat with electric mixer for 2 minutes.
To make more liquid, add another blop of lemon juice and then milk to get to spreadable consistency.

title: cheesy country spam puff
directions: Heat oven to 375°. In large bowl, combine bread, milk, eggs, mustard, garlic powder and paprika. Beat at medium speed of electric mixer 1 minute or until smooth. Stir in Spam, 1 cup Cheddar cheese and onion. Pour into greased 12 x 8-inch baking dish. Bake 25 minutes. Top with remaining cheeses and bake 5 minutes longer or until cheese is melted. Makes 6 servings.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream together shortening and sugar.
Add eggs and bananas. Add dry ingredients.
Pour into bread pan (makes one loaf).
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: original carrot cake
directions: Mix oil, sugar and eggs (added one at a time) together. Sift the flour, baking powder, soda, cinnamon and salt; add to other ingredients,
then add carrots and nuts.
Bake either in a tube pan
or
3	(9-inch)
cake pans at 350° until toothpick comes out clean.
Ice with Philadelphia cream icing.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Combine all, mix well.
Put into a greased casserole.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: caramel layer squares
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour a 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Melt caramels and 1/3 cup evaporated milk.
Keep warm. Combine cake mix, butter, 1/3 cup evaporated milk and nuts. Press 1/2 dough into the cake pan.
Bake at 350° for 6 minutes. Sprinkle chocolate chips over baked crust; spread caramel mixture over all.
Crumble rest of dough over caramel mixture.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes.
Cool completely.

title: pound cake
directions: Whip the Crisco and margarine together.
Blend in sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time; beat well after each.
Add sifted flour alternately with milk.
Beat well.
Add vanilla.
Beat 2 minutes. Bake 1 1/2 hours at 300°.

title: cold oven pound cake
directions: Cream margarine, shortening and sugar until light and fluffy. Add salt and flavorings.
Add flour, eggs and milk alternately, mixing well after each addition.
Beat on low until thoroughly mixed.
Pour into greased and floured 10-inch tube pan.
Place in cold oven.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Do not open oven door during first hour.

title: mint julep syrup
directions: Combine water and sugar in medium saucepan; bring to boil. Reduce heat.
Cook 10 minutes.
Reduce heat to low; add chopped mint.
Simmer 30 minutes.
Let syrup stand overnight; strain. Fill julep cup (12 ounces) with crushed ice.
Combine bourbon and mint syrup.
Pour over ice.
Garnish with fresh mint.
Serve with straw.
Made every Derby Day since 1950.

title: cocktail meatballs
directions: Mix soup mix with water, allow to set a few minutes.
Blend with meat, roll meat into balls (about the size of a walnut). Melt chili sauce and jelly in a skillet.
Drop meatballs into sauce, simmer about 5 to 8 minutes, turn at least once.
Remove cooked meatballs, cook remaining meatballs. Can be made ahead and freeze until needed.

title: chili dip
directions: Soften cream cheese in microwave.
Add other ingredients; heat thoroughly in microwave.
Put cheese and onions on top.
Serve with Fritos.

title: cashew rice milk
directions: Put in blender and blend until smooth the brown rice, cashews, salt and 2 cups water.
When creamy, add 2 more cups water and vanilla.
Let set overnight.
If needs sweetener, blend in 6 dates or honey.

title: betty's tex-mex beans
directions: Saute onion in small amount of oil until tender.
Add rest of ingredients and simmer for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.
Serve over rice. This is good with cornbread.

title: tex mex - layered dip
directions: Spread refried beans evenly on flat plate or you can use bean dip.

title: pina colada cheesecake
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients; press into bottom and 1-inch up sides of a 10-inch spring-form pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Cool on a wire rack.
Beat cream cheese at medium speed until smooth.
Gradually add 3/4 cup sugar, beating well.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each addition.
Stir in sour cream and next 6 ingredients.
Spoon into crust.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 20 minutes; turn off oven.
Leave cheesecake in oven with door closed 1 hour, then cool to room temperature on a wire rack.
Chill.
Yield:
10 to 12 servings.

title: oatmeal raisin cookies
directions: Cream margarine, shortening, sugars, eggs, corn syrup, water and vanilla; beat well.
Combine flour, baking soda and salt.
Add to creamed mixture.
Beat well. Stir in oats and raisins.
Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls onto ungreased baking sheet.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Cool slightly on sheet before removing to cooling racks.

title: goofy buns
directions: Mix first 8 ingredients and put in hamburger buns; wrap in foil and bake at 450° for 5 to 10 minutes.

title: seven minute frosting
directions: Mix all ingredients in top boiler.
Place over boiling water. Beat at medium speed until frosting stands in peaks.

title: dill pickles
directions: Pack
layer of cucumbers, layer of dill in a crock to 1 gallon of
water.
Add salt and vinegar.	Let come to a boil. Pour
over cucumbers and let stand overnight.
Pack cucumbers in jars with fresh dill.
Reheat liquid.
Fill jars and seal.

title: russian tea
directions: Store in airtight container.
Use 1 heaping teaspoonful per cup hot water.

title: million dollar pie
directions: Combine milk and lemon juice; stir until thickened, then add Cool Whip.
Stir until blended.
Put mixture into graham cracker crust.
Put pie filling on top.
Keep refrigerated.

title: lower fat cocoa brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 350° and adjust oven rack to center position. Whisk flour, cocoa, baking powder and salt together in medium bowl and set aside.

title: baked rice(risrynskaka)
directions: Wash rice well.
Cover with hot water and simmer for 15 minutes.
Drain and rinse under cold water.
Let dry awhile. Combine all ingredients and mix lightly.
Pour into buttered baking dish (can use 2).
Sprinkle with cinnamon or grated almonds, as desired.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.
Serve hot or cold.

title: cantonese salad
directions: Clean spinach; break into small pieces and place in large bowl.
Add bean sprouts, water chestnuts, eggs and bacon.
Toss dressing with salad just before serving.

title: easy chicken pie
directions: Cook chicken in microwave until done, then cut up chicken into bite size pieces.
Mix the cream of chicken soup with the milk in a casserole bowl.
Stir in the chicken (mixed vegetables and/or potatoes may be added).
Mix the Bisquick according to the directions on the box for the pie crust.
Spoon Bisquick over the soup mixture.
Bake in oven at 325° for 40 to 45 minutes, or until top is golden brown.

title: almond cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Generously butter 2 cookie sheets.
In food processor, pulse the almonds with the sugar until finely ground.
In large bowl, beat the egg whites with salt until they form stiff peaks.
Fold in the almond mixture and vanilla with rubber spatula.
Spoon scant tablespoons of dough about 1 1/2 inches apart onto cookie sheets.
Bake in middle oven about 30 minutes until golden.
Let rest one minute, then transfer to rack to cool.

title: indian corn
directions: Cook onion and green pepper in frying pan with butter for 15 minutes.
Add meat and allow to brown well, stirring frequently. Add corn, soup, sugar and salt.
Simmer for about 20 minutes and serve.

title: stuffed artichokes
directions: Remove stems and loose outer leaves from artichokes.
Cut off 1 inch from tops.
Snip off sharp leaf tips.
Brush cut edges with lemon juice.
Place artichokes in steamer basket.
Place over boiling water.
Cover and steam 30 to 40 minutes or until leaf pulls out easily.
(Add more boiling water if necessary.)
Remove artichokes; set aside until cool enough to handle.
Remove center leaves and choke (fuzzy stuff).

title: dream salad
directions: Mix milk with lemon juice.
Add pineapple and cherries and refrigerate overnight.
Next day, add Cool Whip and pecans. Serves 8.

title: tomato pie
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients together and pat into a pie plate. Fill with remaining ingredients.
Bake at 325° for 40 minutes. Serve hot or cold.

title: chocolate cake
directions: Mix flour and sugar.
Mix
and
bring to a rolling boil the oleo, shortening, cocoa
and
water.
Pour
over sugar and flour; mix well.
Add other ingredients, mixing well.
Pour in greased sheet cake pan.
Bake
at
do not preheat oven. Have ready: 1 cup milk
and
cup sugar.
Bring to a boil and pour over the cake while hot.

title: 7 layer salad(make ahead)
directions: Layer the 7 ingredients in a bowl.
Seal the last layer with a layer of mayo or Miracle Whip so no air holes permit air to get in.
Sprinkle 2 teaspoons sugar over dressing.
Sprinkle with grated cheese and bacon bits.
Cover with plastic wrap. Refrigerate overnight or 8 hours.

title: my favorite macaroni salad
directions: Mix all the above together.

title: layered sherbet dessert
directions: Combine first four ingredients, mixing well.
Press mixture firmly, in bottom of a 10-inch tube pan with removable bottom or a 9-inch spring-form pan.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes or until lightly browned.
Cool.

title: sara's iced lemon mousse
directions: Soften gelatin in water in small saucepan.
Add lemon juice and sugar.
Stir over low flame until gelatin is thoroughly dissolved.
Add lemon rind and chill to syrup consistency. Gelatin mixture must be cool before begin added to egg whites.

title: cheese ball
directions: Chop the onion, garlic	and pecans and place in a bowl. Grate the pound of
cheese;
mix	it
with
the chopped onion, garlic and cream cheese.
Sprinkle the parsley and paprika and mix well together.
Roll the
mixture in the pecans and form a ball.
Place in a serving dish and chill.

title: risotto milanese
directions: Melt butter and saute onion.
Cook over low heat, stirring continually.
Add rice, stirring often, until rice has absorbed the butter, about 15 minutes.
Add herbs.
Add the broth, one-half cup at a time.
Keep stirring and cook 10 minutes longer after all the broth has been added.
Remove from heat.
Rice should be done. Add the cheese before serving.
More can be added at the table.

title: pineapple ale
directions: Mix pineapple juice and ginger ale in pitcher.
Pour into 4 glasses.
Garnish each with strawberry and mint leaf.

title: buttermilk salad
directions: Pour pineapple in saucepan and bring to a boil.
Stir in dry jello and dissolve.
Remove from heat and stir in buttermilk.
Let congeal partially.
Add Cool Whip and nuts.
Pour into a greased mold.
Chill 3 hours.

title: breakfast souffle
directions: Brown sausage in skillet, stirring until crumbly.
Drain. Layer bread, sausage and cheese in 9 x 13-inch baking dish. Combine eggs, milk, dry mustard and salt in bowl; mix well.
Pour over layers.
Chill, covered, overnight.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes or until brown.
Yield:
10 servings.

title: fresh peach pie
directions: If using a plain crust, bake and cool.
Cook sugar, corn starch and water until thick.
Add jello immediately.
Place peaches in pie crust; pour jello mixture over peaches and let cool in refrigerator until set.
Top with Cool Whip and serve.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream shortening and sugar together.
Add beaten eggs; blend. Add bananas and milk; blend.
Add dry ingredients, then vanilla and nuts.
Put batter in greased 12 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Combine all ingredients except stuffing; toss gently.
Spoon into a greased 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Bake a 375° for 15 minutes. Sprinkle with stuffing.
Bake additional 15 minutes.

title: rice
directions: Pour water into a heavy saucepan and bring to a boil.
Add salt.
Stir in rice.
Cover and reduce heat.
Simmer 25 minutes.

title: oven caramel corn
directions: Preheat oven to 200°.
Mix brown sugar, butter, corn syrup and salt in heavy saucepan.
Cook and stir over medium heat.
Cook 5 minutes and take pan off heat.
Stir in soda and stir until mixture is foamy.
Pour over popped corn and stir until corn is well coated.
Divide between 2 (9 x 13-inch) pans.
Bake the corn for 1 hour, stirring every 15 minutes.
Cool and store in tightly covered container.

title: bean salad
directions: Mix sugar, oil, vinegar, salt and pepper until dissolved.
Pour over bean mixture.
Let refrigerate overnight.
Drain off excess liquid and serve.

title: florence's eggplant au gratin
directions: Peel and boil eggplant in salted water until soft.
Drain and mash.
Saute onions in butter.
Beat eggs.
Grate cheese.
Combine ingredients; placs in a greased casserole.
Cover with crumbs. Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: easy pretzels
directions: Mix yeast, sugar, salt and warm water.
Add flour and mix. Put dough on waxed paper and knead until smooth.

Cut off pieces and roll into shapes. (The dough cannot be overworked so let children enjoy playing with dough.) Place not too thick and not too thin shapes on greased cookie sheet. Brush with beaten egg. Sprinkle with salt, if desired.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: cranberry pie
directions: Heat oven to 325°. Grease a 9-inch pie plate or fluted quiche dish.
Add cranberries and sprinkle with nuts, raisins and 3/4 cup sugar.
In a medium size bowl, beat egg with the remaining 1/4 cup sugar.
Add flour and butter.
Beat until no lumps remain.
Pour over berry mixture and bake 45 minutes until crust is a light golden brown.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: ugly cake
directions: Mix
well
1 well beaten egg, oleo and cake mix.
Press into bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: pumpkin pie squares
directions: Combine flour, rolled oats, 1/2 cup brown sugar and 1/2 cup butter.
Mix until crumbly, press into ungreased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 350°
for 15 minutes.

title: candy tingalings
directions: Melt butter and chocolate chips over low heat until melted. Add nuts and coconut.
Mix well.
Drop by teaspoon onto wax paper. Cool in refrigerator.
Makes 2 dozen.

title: dream cake
directions: Mix together and bake in greased tube pan for 45 to 55 minutes.

title: baked custard
directions: Scald milk in the top of a double boiler; cool slightly.
Beat eggs thoroughly.
Add salt, sugar and vanilla.
Pour slowly into the hot milk, stirring constantly.
Pour into a 10 x 5 x 3-inch glass baking dish.
Set the dish in a slightly larger pan with 1 inch of water in the bottom.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until a silver knife inserted in the center comes out clean.
Serves 8.

title: minestrone (soup)
directions: Heat oil in large pot; add garlic, onion, celery and parsley. Cook until soft.
Stir in tomato paste and next 7 ingredients. Mix well; bring to boil.
Lower heat, cover and simmer slowly 1 hour.
Add remaining ingredients, except cheese.
Cook 10 to 15 minutes more or until macaroni is tender.
Serve piping hot with plenty of cheese.
Makes 8 generous servings.
Even better the next day.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Saute onion and chili peppers slowly in margarine.
Place 6 tortillas in bottom of glass 9 x 13-inch casserole dish (overlap them slightly).
Add chicken in layers.
Top with onion and pepper mixture.
Add 6 more tortillas.
Pour cream soup, to which 1/4 can water has been added, over tortillas.
Place Swiss cheese slices on top.
Bake at 300° for 30 minutes or until cheese bubbles.

title: aunt loraine's vegetables
directions: Combine vegetables, soup, 1/2 cup cheese, sour cream, pepper, pimento & 1/2 can onions. Pour into 1 qt. casserole dish. Bake, covered, at 350 degrees for 30 minutes. Top with remaining cheese & onions. Bake uncovered 5 minutes longer. Serves 6.

title: quick kabobs
directions: Cut banana, apple, melon and cheese and put on wood skewer. Dip in orange juice and then coconut.
Eat!

title: carrot cake
directions: Mix together the flour, baking powder, baking soda, salt and cinnamon. Add the sugar, oil and eggs and mix well.
Fold in the carrots, pineapple, walnuts and raisins. Blend thoroughly. Pour into three 9-inch round cake pans. Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: crab dip
directions: Cream mayonnaise and cream cheese together.
Add all other ingredients and mix well. Then add crab meat. Better made one day before using.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Cream the butter and sugar.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Add flour with baking soda; mix well.
Drop cookies on cookie sheet or chill and shape into rolls and refrigerate or freeze.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Makes approximately 5 dozen cookies.

title: hummingbird cake
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients in a large bowl; stir until dry ingredients are thoroughly moistened.
Do not beat; stir in vanilla, pineapple, nuts and bananas.
Pour batter into prepared pans.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 28 minutes.

title: cranberry crumble
directions: Put 1 cup sugar and 1 cup water in saucepan and bring to boil. Add cranberries and cook until berries burst. Add orange rind and prunes and pour into shallow 1 1/2-quart baking dish.

title: spaghetti a mor
directions: Brown hamburger and cook spaghetti.
Mix together with remaining ingredients, except cheese.
Mix in half the cheese and reserve the other half.
Sprinkle other half of cheese over mixture.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: ham and potato casserole
directions: Alternate layers of potatoes, ham and cheese.
Mix pepper, flour, butter and soup.
Pour over top and bake at 350° for about 45 minutes to 1 hour in covered casserole dish.

title: five in one casserole
directions: Layer sliced onion first, sliced potatoes next, salt & pepper.
Sprinkle cream style corn on hamburger patties.
Cover with tomato soup.
Bake 350 degrees for 1 hour or until done.

title: breakfast brunch dish
directions: Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: cheesecake squares
directions: Mix cake mix, egg and butter together.
Spread out in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan. Mix cream cheese, eggs and confectioners sugar together.
Pour on top of mixture in pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: old-fashioned spoon bread
directions: Combine corn meal, salt and 1 cup milk in 1 1/2-quart saucepan.
Heat remaining milk and add.
Stir and cook over medium heat until smooth and thick.
Stir in baking powder.
Beat egg yolks and egg whites separately.
Gradually stir in egg yolks. Fold in egg whites.
Melt margarine in 1 1/2-quart baking pan, 9 x 9 x 2-inch.
Pour.
Bake in preheated moderate oven (375°) for 40 minutes.
Serve with butter.
Serves 6.

title: cranberry chutney
directions: Grind frozen cranberries.
Drain pineapple and save juice. Heat juice to dissolve gelatin.
Blend in orange juice concentrate, water and sugar.
Cool.
Add applesauce.

title: cherry pie
directions: In small bowl, combine sugar and flour; mix well.
In saucepan, empty can of pie cherries; add sugar and flour.
Mix. Bring to a boil.
Remove from heat.
Add oleo, extract and coloring.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Add top pie crust.
Bake at 425° for 30 minutes.

title: mexican chicken
directions: Boil chicken and remove bones.
Put in large casserole dish. Sprinkle onion, garlic, salt and pepper.
Sprinkle with cheese. Crush 1/2 bag of chips and sprinkle on top.
Mix soups and Ro-Tel. Pour over chips, then sprinkle with other 1/2 of the chips over the soup mixture.
Cover with foil and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: southern living chutney
directions: Combine first three items.
Cook on low heat for 15 minutes, stirring often.
Remove from heat.
Add remaining ingredients. Cover and refrigerate.

title: joe's jambalaya
directions: Brown ground beef and onion, and drain.
In a 9 x 13 pan, layer pasta, beef and onion, soup, tomatoes and cheese.
Bake at 350 degrees for 30 minutes until bubbly.

title: granny's punch
directions: Mix Jell-O with boiling water.
Add the juices. Chill and when ready to serve, add ginger ale.
This will serve 50 people.

title: chocolate satin pie
directions: Place butter in mixing bowl and whip.
Sift sugar and cocoa together.
Add slowly to whipped butter on low speed.
If mixture is too stiff, add 1 egg and continue beating.
Add eggs, 1 at a time, then vanilla and almond extract.
Beat well.
Whip on high speed until the consistency of whipped cream.
Pour into baked pie shell and chill 2 hours.
Rich and good!!!!

title: smooth and easy clam chowder
directions: Saute onion and clams in margarine.
Set aside.
Boil potatoes until tender.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Mash potatoes slightly.
Soften cream cheese in microwave.
Add milk and flour. Whip.
Turn potatoes to low heat and stir in cheese mixture. Stir in onion and clam saute mixture.
Serve with crackers.

title: cherry refrigerator sheet cake
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water. Add cold water; set aside. Mix and bake cake as directed on package in a 9 x 13-inch pan. Cool cake for 20 to 25 minutes. Poke holes through top of warm cake. Pour Jell-O into the holes. Put in the refrigerator while preparing Topping.

title: one bowl pie(french coconut pie)
directions: Mix all ingredients well (do not use electric mixer).
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° 40-45 minutes.
Center should be firm and feel a little sticky.
Do not overbake.
Cool before slicing.

title: polish mistakes
directions: Brown meat and drain well.
Add all ingredients until cheese melts.
Spread on bread.
Place on cookie sheet and freeze.
When ready to use, heat oven to 350° and bake 10 minutes.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients, set aside. Combine eggs, sugar, oil and vanilla in large bowl. Beat at medium speed until well blended. Stir in zucchini and pecans. Add dry ingredients, stirring just until moistened. Bake in greased and floured loaf pan at 350° for 55 to 60 minutes.

title: jello salad
directions: Mix first three ingredients and cool.
Add cottage cheese and pineapple.
Mix and add rest of ingredients.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: overnight french toast
directions: Arrange bread in a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Beat ingredients until well blended and sugar is dissolved.
Pour over bread.
Cover and refrigerate at least one hour and can be 24 hours, allowing bread to soak up liquid.
Heat oven to 425°.
Lightly grease a jelly roll pan and transfer bread, making sure slices don't touch.
Bake for 12 to 15 minutes, until puffed and lightly browned.
Dust with confectioners sugar and serve immediately.
Makes 4 servings: 423 calories, 10 g fat, 63 g car, 560 mg sod and 228 mg chol.

title: holiday salad
directions: In saucepan, mix the dry pudding and lemon gelatin with the water.
Cook and stir until the mixture boils, then stir in the lemon juice.
Chill in refrigerator until partially set.
Dissolve the dry raspberry gelatin in the 1 cup boiling water.
Mix in the cranberry sauce, celery and pecans.
Chill this until partially set.

title: california marinade
directions: Put all ingredients in a pint size screw top jar.
Cover jar tightly and shake vigorously to mix ingredients well.
Store marinade, tightly covered, in the refrigerator until ready to use. Shake or beat well before using.
Makes about 1 cup marinade.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Cook sugar, cocoa, Karo syrup and milk until a soft ball forms in water.
Remove from heat.
Add butter and peanut butter.
Let set 3 minutes, then beat until it starts to set.
Pour into 9 x 9-inch pan.

title: mobile shrimp gumbo
directions: Brown flour in oil. Add onion and celery and saute lightly. Add soup, water, okra and shrimp.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Add Worcestershire sauce and simmer for 1 hour.
Turn off heat. Add file after boiling stops. Serve over rice with garlic bread.

title: crowd pleasing punch
directions: In a 6 gallon container combine water and the next 6 ingredients.
Mix well.
Just before serving, pour 1/3 of punch mixture into a punch bowl.
Add 1 bottle ginger ale.
As bowl empties, repeat with remaining punch mixture and ginger ale. Yield:
100 servings.

title: two minute hawaiian pie
directions: In large bowl combine vanilla pudding mix (dry), undrained crushed pineapple, sour cream and coconut (if adding); stir until well blended.
Pour mixture into prepared pie crust.
Cover; chill for 2 hours before serving.
Top with whip cream to serve.

title: chocolate delights
directions: Combine sugar, butter, cocoa and milk in saucepan; stir constantly.
Boil 1 minute.
Remove from heat.
Add oats, then peanut butter.
Beat until well mixed.
Drop by tablespoon onto wax paper.
Very good with a glass of milk.

title: kool-aid play dough
directions: Mix together flour, salt and Kool-Aid.
Boil water and oil and add to flour mixture (it's hot).
Knead until well blended.
Store in a plastic bag.

title: banana pudding
directions: Mix pudding mix and milk in a large bowl.
Add condensed milk and Cool Whip, stirring until smooth.
Place vanilla wafers on bottom and side of bowl.
Place sliced banana on top of cookies in bottom; top with some of the pudding mix.
Continue layering until all of the pudding mix is used.
Top with vanilla wafers.

title: egg and sausage casserole
directions: Add all ingredients together.
Let stand in refrigerator overnight.
Cook at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: potato-meat patties
directions: Shape mixture into patties, about 1/2 cup per patty.
Press patties gently between sheets of waxed paper to flatten them to about 3/4-inch thick.
Cook in skillet, using 1 teaspoon oil, butter or margarine per patty; simmer until browned on both sides.

title: corn bread dressing
directions: Crumble corn bread into large mixing bowl.
Add bread crumbs. Saute chopped onions and celery in fat until tender.
Do not brown.
Add to crumbled bread along with giblets and eggs.
Add sage and pepper.
Blend (do not salt).
Add moisture (using broth from cooked giblets).
Dressing should be quite moist, some moisture will be lost in cooking.
Bake in covered pan at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.
Remove cover last 10 minutes to let brown.

title: pizzaiola sauce
directions: Heat oil in
skillet
and
saute
garlic
until golden. Remove and discard garlic.
Add tomatoes and squash with fork. Stir in rest of
ingredients
and
cook until sauce comes to a boil. Lower heat to a
medium
simmer
and cook 15 to 25 minutes, uncovered.
Serve
over
cooked
spaghetti with Parmesan cheese, if desired.
Makes 4 servings.

title: beef and cheese pie
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Brown ground beef, onion and green pepper, then drain and stir in tomato sauce, green beans, garlic salt and salt.
Simmer while preparing crust.

title: peanut butter play dough
directions: Mix peanut butter and honey.
Add dry milk.
If it's too sticky, add some more milk.
If it doesn't stick well, add some honey.
When kids are finished playing, eat!

title: ham rolls
directions: Combine all ingredients except ham. Spread cream cheese mixture evenly on one side of each ham slice.
Roll up and secure with a wooden pick.
Cover and chill.
Carefully slice each roll into pieces.
Serve with toothpicks.
Yields 4 dozen.

title: lazy beef casserole
directions: Cut beef into 2-inch pieces.
In 3-quart casserole dish, combine beef, wine, consomme, salt, pepper and onion.
Mix together bread crumbs and flour and stir into casserole mixture; cover.
Bake at 300° about 3 hours or until beef is tender.
If desired, vegetables (potatoes, carrots, green beans, peas) may be added about 1/2 hour before serving time.
Serves 4.

title: chili
directions: Crumble and brown the meat.
Drain fat.
Stir in tomato sauce and Ro-Tel.
Stir in beans and chili seasoning.
Simmer 10 to 15 minutes.
Yields 16 servings.

title: grandma lill's buns
directions: Pour boiling water over 2/3 cup sugar and salt; cool to lukewarm.
Dissolve the yeast in a small amount of warm water and 1 tablespoon sugar.
Mix these 2 parts together.
Add 3 cups flour, beaten egg and the shortening; stir.
Add remaining flour, kneading in the last part.
Let rise to double in bulk, then punch it down.
Let rise again and put into pans.
Let rise again and bake at 375°.
If this recipe is used for bread, use only 1/3 cup sugar and bake at 350°.
Bake at 375° for buns.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: sweet onion gravy
directions: Place onion and bacon drippings in thick pan or skillet.
Add salt and pepper.
Saute until onions are tender.
Let this simmer. Mix flour and enough water for a thickening.
Pour in mixture and cook until thick like gravy.
Serve with rice or toast.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: peanut butter ice cream pie
directions: Mix crumbs, sugar and oleo. Press into a 9-inch pie plate.

title: prune cake
directions: Mix first 8 ingredients.
Add next 4 ingredients.
Mix and add walnuts, coconut and raisins.
Bake in greased and floured tube pan for 1 hour and 40 minutes at 300°.
Cook cake 20 minutes before dumping on rack.

title: chocolate fudge
directions: Melt margarine and cheese together on low heat.
Mix into powdered sugar and cocoa.
Put on cookie sheets.
Makes a big batch of candy.

title: stuffed baked potatoes
directions: Bake potatoes in 375° oven.
Cut slice from top of each. Scoop out inside; mash.
Add butter, salt, pepper and hot milk to moisten.
Beat fluffy.
Fill shells half full with mashed potatoes.
Combine peas and onion; divide among potato shells. Pile remaining mashed potatoes atop.
Return to oven at 375° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: strawberry bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a bowl, sift flour, soda, salt and cinnamon.
In a large mixing bowl, beat eggs.
Add oil and sugar. Gradually add flour mixture, strawberries and pecans.
Pour into two greased and floured 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pans.
Bake 1 hour or until a toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.

title: stuffed cabbage
directions: Place cabbage in boiling water.
With fork and knife, cut away leaves as they wilt.
Remove from water.
Saute onion in oil.
Add to combined meat, rice and seasonings.
Save some onion to mix with any leftover cabbage to be chopped for bottom of pot.
Take a cabbage leaf and remove thick vein.
Cut leaf in half, if large. Place a tablespoon of meat mixture in leaf.
With hand, fold one side of leaf over mixture and roll.
Tuck in with end of leaf, gently.
Place layer of cabbage in the bottom of pot and place cabbage rolls in layers.
Pour puree and enough water to cover cabbage.
Cook 1 hour.
Do not overcook rice.

title: strawberry pretzel dessert
directions: Press melted butter, brown sugar and pretzels in 8 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Cool slightly and refrigerate. Mix cream cheese, powdered sugar and Cool Whip.
Spread this on pretzel mixture.
Refrigerate 45 minutes.
Dissolve jello in water, add frozen strawberries; pour over cheese.
Let set.
Serve with whipped cream.

title: trachok's zucchini bread
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Grease and flour 2 loaf pans.
Beat eggs until light and fluffy.
Add sugar, oil and vanilla, blending well. Stir in zucchini.
Sift all dry ingredients together.
Blend with creamed mixture.
Fold in nuts and raisins.
Turn into 2 floured and greased pans.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes, then at 350° for 45 minutes or until done.
Cool on racks.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: beef mexican soup
directions: Cook beef or turkey, onion and pepper until browned.
Drain off fat if beef is used.
Stir in sauce mix from Hamburger Helper, water, seasonings and tomatoes with liquid.
Heat to boiling, stirring constantly.
Reduce heat, cover and simmer 10 minutes. Stir in macaroni, corn, beans and okra.
Stir in olives with liquid.
Cover and cook 10 more minutes.
(May substitute two 14 1/2 ounce cans chopped tomatoes with liquid and 4 cups water for one 16 ounce can tomatoes and 5 cups water.)

title: pumpkin bars
directions: In large mixing bowl, beat together eggs, sugar, oil and pumpkin until light and fluffy.
Stir together flour, baking powder, cinnamon, salt and soda.
Add to pumpkin mixture and mix thoroughly.

title: oreo ice cream
directions: Mix all ingredients well, adding enough milk to fill freezer and pour into ice cream freezer.

title: christmas cookies(makes 6 dozen.)
directions: Mix well sugars and oleo. Add eggs and vanilla. Add salt, soda and flour. Stir in chips, raisins and nuts. Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes on sprayed pan.

title: peaches-n-cream
directions: Mix Cool Whip and jello until creamy.
Add cottage cheese. Drain and dice peaches.
Mix together with other ingredients and chill 30 minutes.

title: sugar-free grape and peach slush
directions: Combine all ingredients in blender.
Blend until smooth and serve at once.
Makes 4 (8 ounce) servings.

title: baked macaroni and cheese squares
directions: Cook macaroni according to package directions. Drain. Add remaining ingredients except 1/2 cup cheese and mix well.
Cook and stir over medium heat 3 to 5 minutes. Turn into a well-greased square baking dish. Top with remaining cheese.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes until bubbly.
Let stand 10 minutes, then serve.

title: pig pickin cake
directions: Mix cake mix, eggs, oil and mandarin oranges; beat well. Pour in 3 layer pans. Bake at 375 degrees for 20-25 minutes. Cool completely & frost.

title: crustless coconut pie(easy)
directions: Cream the margarine and sugar.
Add eggs one at a time and beat.
Add milk and flour.
Mix well.
Add other ingredients; mix. Pour into lightly greased 9-inch pie pan and bake at 350° for 50 minutes or until firm.

title: banana pudding
directions: Combine flour, 1 1/3 cups sugar and salt.
Beat egg yolks; combine egg yolks and milk.
Mix well.
Stir in dry ingredients. Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until smooth and thick.
Remove from heat; stir in 1 teaspoon vanilla.
Layer 1/3 vanilla wafers in 4-quart dish; slice 2 bananas over wafers.
Pour 1/3 pudding over; continue two times.
Beat egg whites at room temperature; gradually add remaining sugar until stiff peaks form. Add 1 teaspoon vanilla.
Beat some more.
Top pudding with meringue.
Bake at 425° for 10 to 12 minutes until meringue is browned.

title: ham and scalloped potatoes
directions: Toss sliced potatoes in 1/2 teaspoon cream of tartar and 1 cup water.
Drain.
Put half of ham, potatoes and onions in cooker. Sprinkle with salt and pepper, then grated cheese.
Repeat with remaining half.
Spoon undiluted soup over top.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Cover and cook on low for 8 to 10 hours (high for 4 hours).

title: quickie fruit cobbler
directions: Pour fruit in baking dish.
Pour cake mix on top of fruit, sprinkle melted margarine over top.
Bake at 350° until brown, approximately 40 to 50 minutes.

title: surprise dip for vegetables
directions: In blender or food processor, combine first 7 ingredients for a few seconds.
With processor running, add beer and blend until smooth.
Add salt, if needed.
Chill at least 1 hour before serving.
Serve at room temperature.
Garnish with parsley and paprika.

title: chuck wagon beans
directions: In a 2-quart casserole or bean pot, combine beans, tomato sauce, onion, catsup, brown sugar and seasonings. Bury bacon in beans. Bake, uncovered, in slow oven (300°) 3 1/2 to 4 hours. Toward end of cooking time, fork bacon to top. Center with drained, cooked or canned onions. Makes 6 servings.

title: chinese casserole
directions: Brown meat with celery and onion. Add all ingredients except noodles. Pour mixture into a large baking dish. Top with Chinese noodles. Bake at 325° for 50 minutes. Serve with side order of rice.

title: kraut
directions: Cut up cabbage and put in jars (do not pack).
Pour mixture over cabbage.
Seal jars.

title: sour cream fudge
directions: Combine sugar, salt and sour cream.
Cook to soft ball stage. Add nuts, beat.
Pour into a pan, cut into squares.

title: mashed potatoes supreme
directions: Cook potatoes as you would for mashing.
Drain.
Beat cream cheese, butter and sour cream until well blended.
Add into hot potatoes and beat until light and fluffy.
Season with salt and pepper.
Put into 2-quart casserole dish.
Dot with butter and sprinkle with paprika.
Bake at 325° for 25 minutes.
This can be made a day ahead and refrigerated.

title: orange nuggets
directions: Combine cake mix, eggs, oil and orange juice; beat for 2 to 3 minutes until well blended.
Fold in chopped oranges.
Grease miniature muffin pans.
Pour batter into pans.
Bake for 10 minutes at 350°.
Remove muffins from pan and dip each in Orange Glaze.

title: easy sour cream pound cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Grease and flour Bundt pan and bake at 350° for about 35 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean.

title: m&m cookies
directions: Cream first 5 ingredients.
Sift flour, soda and salt.
Add to creamed mixture well.
Stir in 1/2 cup M&M's.
Reserve remaining candy for decorating.
Drop by teaspoonful on ungreased baking sheet.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.
This makes 6 dozen 2 1/2-inch cookies.
If using self-rising flour, omit soda and salt.

title: rice casserole
directions: Saute in small amount of oil in skillet the onion tops, peppers, water chestnuts and raw rice.
Stir, cooking about 3 minutes.
Mix onion soup mix with 1 1/2 cups water.
Pour into casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes.
Side dish to meat.
May add brown ground meat for a main dish.
So good either way.

title: chicken in sour cream
directions: Place chicken in buttered baking dish.
Dot each piece with butter.
Sprinkle with salt, pepper and paprika.
Combine remaining ingredients and pour over chicken.
Bake in a 350° oven for 1 1/4 to 1 1/2 hours or until chicken is tender and sauce is brown.
Serve with cooked rice and vegetable salad.

title: jewish apple cake
directions: Combine first 7 ingredients, mixing well.
In separate bowl toss apples, sugar and cinnamon.
Fold apple mixture into batter. Pour into greased and floured tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes until done.
Cool 10 minutes, take out to cool completely.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Cut broccoli into bite size pieces.
Fry the bacon until it is crisp, then crumble it.
Slice the purple onion and separate it into rings.
Place all 4 items into a large bowl, then toss with sauce.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Mix all above ingredients thoroughly. Pour into a greased and floured tube pan. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: hot chicken salad deluxe
directions: Saute almonds in margarine.
Drain.
Combine all ingredients except potato chips. Spoon into a lightly greased 1-quart casserole. Sprinkle with potato chips.
Bake at 425° for 20 minutes.
Yields 4 to 6 servings.

title: thin pancakes
directions: In bowl, mix all ingredients except flour.
When blended, add flour.
Blend well.
Heat 8-inch skillet over medium heat.
Brush with shortening.
