Pour batter 2 tablespoons at a time into skillet. Tilt pan to make a 6-inch round thin pancake.
Brown about 1 minute, then turn to brown on the other side.
Serve immediately with butter and syrup.
Makes 14 to 16 pancakes.

title: spinach bites
directions: Mix together all ingredients; spread on flour tortillas.
Roll up tortilla.
Refrigerate rolls until ready to serve.
Cut tortilla rolls into 1/2-inch slices.

title: golden baked onions
directions: Butter a 2-quart, shallow baking dish.
Melt butter in large skillet over medium heat.
Add onions; cook until tender and transparent, stirring frequently (about 15 minutes).
Transfer onions to prepared dish.

title: ham delights
directions: Slice rolls horizontally.
Top bottom layer with cheese and ham.
Replace top.
Cover with the other ingredients which have been mixed together.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: caramel fondue
directions: In pan, combine sugar, cream and butter.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly until mixture boils.
Boil 3 minutes until sauce thickens.
Let stand 3 minutes. Stir in rum.
Serve warm or cold with dippers.

title: seafood chowder
directions: Saute finely chopped vegetables in butter until tender.
Blend in flour.
Add chicken broth and stir until smooth.
Add milk; simmer but do not boil.
Add cheese and stir until melted.
Add seafood and seasonings.
This soup may be made and kept on low setting in crock-pot for several hours; stir occasionally.
Serves 8.

title: pepper steak
directions: Trim fat from meat; cut meat into 1/8-inch strips.
Brown meat in oil in large skillet.
Season with salt.
Add onions and garlic; cook and stir until onions are tender.
Dissolve bouillon cubes in hot water; add with Worcestershire sauce to meat.
Cover; simmer 1 hour or until meat is tender.
Add green peppers; cover and simmer 5 minutes longer.
Combine cornstarch and 1/4 cup water.
Gradually stir into meat mixture.
Cook, stirring until sauce thickens; add tomatoes.
Heat through.
Cook noodles and serve pepper steak over noodles.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: best sugar cookies
directions: Cream the butter with the sugar. Add eggs, one at a time.
Mix the baking powder with the flour and alternate with the juice, extract and rind. Refrigerate overnight.
Take out small amounts. Roll thin. Bake at 350° for 6 to 9 minutes.
(Very easy to work with!)

title: jim's favorite chicken
directions: Sprinkle each chicken piece with dry minced onions, salt, pepper and slices of canned mushrooms.
Roll each piece and wrap with a raw bacon slice.
Mix the soup, sour cream and wine.
Put the chicken in a 12 x 8-inch pan; pour the liquid over it.
Bake for three hours at 285°.
Serve over yellow rice.

title: yogurt cake
directions: Cream together margarine and sugar.
Add eggs and with electric mixer, beat until light and fluffy.
Combine dry ingredients and add to batter.
Add vanilla and yogurt.
Mix total batter at medium speed for three minutes.
Pour into a well-greased 10-inch tube pan or Bundt pan.
Bake at 325° for about 65 minutes.

title: angel pudding cake
directions: Tear cake into small pieces and place in baking dish.
Mix pudding (as stated on box) and pour over cake.
Spread pie filling over pudding.
Spread layer of whipped topping.
Refrigerate, best if overnight.

title: peanut butter rice krispies balls
directions: Blend together the first 4 ingredients; form into balls.
Melt chocolate chips and paraffin wax in double boiler.
Dip candy balls into chocolate; cool on wax paper.

title: orange juice cake
directions: Mix all the ingredients together except the nuts.
Grease and flour tube pan.
Put nuts in bottom of pan, then pour batter over the nuts.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: black forest torte
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Prepare cake mix according to package directions using 2 (8-inch) round cake pans.
Cool in pan on rack 15 minutes.
Remove pan and cool at least 30 minutes.
Cut cake layers horizontally in half, making 4 layers.
Drain pie filling, reserving liquid.
Add 2 tablespoons liqueur to reserved liquid and remaining 2 tablespoons liqueur to cherries.
Reserve 1/2 cherries for top.
Whip cream to soft peaks.
Fold in sugar. Place 1 cup whipped cream in piping bag fitted with star tip. Place 1 cake layer on plate.
Brush with 3 tablespoons reserved cherry liquid mixture.
Top with 1 cup whipped cream.
Poke 1/3 cherries into whipped cream.
Repeat entire process with remaining layers; reserved liquid mixture, whipped cream and cherries. Garnish edge of cake with reserved whipped cream.
Place reserved cherries in center of cake top.
Spoon any remaining cherry liquid over cherries.
Serve immediately.
Quick and easy!

title: peach jello salad
directions: First Layer:
Dissolve jello in hot water.
Add ice cream; blend well.
Put in refrigerator until completely set.

title: shrimp spread
directions: Mix all together and chill at least 3 hours.
Serve with crackers.

title: calico beans
directions: Brown hamburger and onion in pan.
Fry bacon.
Put the rest of ingredients in crock-pot.
Add hamburger, onion and bacon.
Let cook for at least an hour.

title: chocolate chewy cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Combine flour, cocoa and salt.
Blend into butter and sugar mixture.
Stir in chocolate chips and nuts.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 9 minutes (no more).

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Combine and put in bottle.
Store in refrigerator.

title: sweet corn griddle cakes
directions: To the beaten egg, add the milk, grains from the corn, sugar, salt and pepper to taste and flour, enough to make a batter of the proper consistency, sifted with the soda and cream of tartar.
Fry in deep fat.

title: cream fudge
directions: Cook until a drop hardens in cold water.
Then take form fire and beat until nearly cold.
Pour on well buttered plate and when cold, cut in squares.

title: short ribs - korean style
directions: Score meat so it can absorb marinade.
Mix everything, except meat, together in a large bowl.
Add meat.
Let stand at least 1 hour.

title: chocolate chip cheesecake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. In large bowl, beat together cream cheese, eggs, sugar and vanilla; set aside. Slice 1 roll cookie dough into 1/3 inch slices. Arrange slices on bottom of greased 9 x 13-inch glass dish; press together so there are no holes in dough. Spoon cream cheese mixture over dough. Slice second roll of cookie dough and place slices over filling. Bake 45 to 50 minutes or until golden and the center is slightly firm. Remove from oven; let cool, then refrigerate.

title: the 90 calorie banana split
directions: Dissolve gelatin completely in boiling water in medium bowl. Stir in cold water.
Pour into 8-inch square pan.
Refrigerate 3 hours or until firm.
Cut into 1/2-inch cubes.
Divide into 4 dessert dishes.
Halve and split bananas just before serving.
Put 2 pieces in each dish.
Top with Cool Whip and sprinkle with nuts. Contains 90 calories, 2.5 g fat.

title: dietetic pumpkin pie
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Combine egg, sweetener, spices and pumpkin and blend well.
Add milk and orange juice gradually; stir until well blended.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes then reduce heat to 325° and bake until a knife inserted near center comes out clean, about 3/4 hour.

title: zucchini lasagna
directions: Cut off stem and blossom ends of zucchini.
Wash and slice zucchini lengthwise into thin slices.
Saute beef until it loses its color; drain fat.
Add onion, tomato, tomato sauce, 1/4 cup water, salt, pepper, oregano and basil.
Simmer 10 to 12 minutes. Stir together Ricotta, cottage cheese and Mozzarella.

title: cinnamon candy
directions: Mix and stir until it reaches 303° on candy thermometer. Remove from heat; add 1 teaspoon cinnamon oil and red food coloring.
Pour on a long sheet of aluminum foil.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar if desired. Cool.
Break into pieces.
You may have to use a hammer.

title: spinach salad with cashew dressing
directions: Wash spinach and drain water.
Wash cashews.
In a salad bowl, put spinach, chopped green onion and tofu cubes.
Mix it.

title: salsa
directions: Skin tomatoes and chop; chop green peppers, onions and hot peppers.
(Use gloves when chopping hot peppers.)
Cook down (save most of juice to be used in soups, etc.); drain, reserving enough liquid to fill jar.
Put 1/2 teaspoon salt in each pint jar.
Place jars in pressure cooker and when it reaches 15 pounds pressure, turn off.
This may be made hotter or milder, as you desire.

title: salad oil dressing
directions: Mix garlic with oil, then all other items.
Sprinkle Parmesan cheese onto lettuce as you mix other ingredients.
Toss and serve at once.
(Dry lettuce or romaine with towel until dry.)

title: peanut brittle
directions: Put sugar, water and Karo in pan.
Boil until it spins a fine thread, then add the peanuts and stir until the syrup turns amber color or about 10 minutes, then add soda and turn burner off. Stir very fast until soda mixes well.
Pour on greased cookie sheet and let cool.
Break into pieces.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Simmer chicken; drain, skin and cut into strips.
Set aside. Cook onion and garlic in butter until tender.
Add tomatoes, sauce and chilies, covered, for 20 minutes.
Dip each tortilla in tomato mixture.
Place chicken and 2 tablespoons cheese in each.
Roll up.
Seam side down, place in casserole dish with remaining tomato mixture.
Add 1 cup sour cream.
Pour this over enchiladas. Sprinkle with remaining cheese.
Bake, covered, 40 minutes at 350°.

title: russian tea
directions: Boil water.
Add tea and spices.
Simmer for 5 minutes.
Take off heat and steep for 15 minutes.
Remove tea bags and spices. Add juices and sugar.
Chill and serve.

title: ann landers' meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Beat thoroughly.
Bake 1 hour in 350° oven.
Pour tomato sauce over top (optional).

title: glorified rice
directions: Drain pineapple; reserve syrup.
In saucepan, combine rice, water, syrup and salt.
Bring to boil.
Cover and simmer 5 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Cover and let stand 5 minutes.
Add marshmallows, pineapples, banana and juice.
Cool.
Fold in whipped cream.
Chill.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: mom's cherry bars
directions: Mix together by hand (dough will be stiff).
Spread in greased jelly roll pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: egg-topped carrot casserole
directions: Cook carrots in boiling salted water until tender, then drain. Stir in the soup, cheese, onion and green pepper and place in casserole dish.
Top with eggs.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Makes 4 servings.

title: fried corn bread
directions: Add hot water to cornmeal, small amount at a time, until it becomes a medium thin mixture.
In heavy bottom skillet, place 3 tablespoons cooking oil and heat for a few seconds.
With a large spoon drop the cornmeal mixture into frying pan in two or three places, being careful to keep the corn cakes apart from each other (like pancake).
Fry until golden brown.
Turn to fry other side. Serve with a pat of butter on each.

title: scotch shortbread
directions: Place all ingredients on a clean counter and knead ingredients with your hands, just until dough sticks together. Then knead 10 more times.
Place in jelly roll type pan.
Prick surface with a fork.
Bake at 350 for 30 minutes or until lightly brown.

title: cottage cheese salad
directions: Sprinkle jello over cottage cheese.
Add drained pineapple and oranges.
Last of all fold in Cool Whip.
A very simple and easy salad.

title: chicken or veal marsala
directions: Flour chicken lightly.
Put oil and butter in frypan.
Saute chicken.
Place in platter.
Saute mushrooms and garlic.
Remove to platter.
Add some flour to oil and butter in frypan.
It will become thick, then add chicken broth and wine.
Cook until desired thickness.
Return chicken and mushrooms to sauce until hot.
Add fresh parsley.
Serve.

title: quick apple cake
directions: Mix flour, milk, sugar and baking powder well.
Melt butter in a 9 x 9-inch pan. Pour mixture over butter. Add chopped apples in batter.
Push down.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes or until tests done. Serve with whipped topping or ice cream.
You can use blueberries or blackberries.

title: chicken and seafood jambalaya
directions: * Tasso is a highly seasoned cajun smoked ham.

title: cabbage and noodle casserole
directions: In a large kettle, cook noodles for 5 minutes in amount of boiling water specified on package, adding 1 tablespoon oil to water.
Turn off heat and let stand, covered, for 20 minutes.

title: ambrosia
directions: Drain pineapple and oranges.
Combine pineapple, oranges, banana, grapes, marshmallows, coconut and nuts.
Mix sour cream and sugar.
Stir into fruit mixture.
Chill.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: pancake sausage roll-ups
directions: Mix equal parts of creamy Italian dressing and Caesar salad dressing.
Marinate chicken breast fillets in mixture overnight. Cook on grill.

title: chicken or beef casserole
directions: Cook and debone chicken (save broth).
Melt butter and add onion, pepper and celery.
Saute until tender.
Add cheese and melt.
Stir in soup.
Boil noodles in broth.
Drain.
Mix all together in large bowl and put in casserole dish.
Add crushed crackers on top and cook 30 minutes at 350°.

title: black-eyed pea salad
directions: Combine all ingredients; put in covered bowl and refrigerate (the longer it sits, the better).

title: parmesan oven potatoes
directions: Melt butter on cookie sheet with sides or a large pan.
Cut raw potatoes into bite-sized pieces.
Mix together flour and Parmesan cheese.
Dip wet potatoes into flour mixture and place on pan with melted butter.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour or until golden brown, turning occasionally for even browning.

title: white chocolate fudge candy
directions: Mix cream cheese, sugar and vanilla.
Melt chocolate.
Fold into cheese, sugar and nuts.
Put in pan and chill.
Cut into pieces.

title: diet waffles
directions: Mix 2 cups waffle mix, 1 1/4 cups skim milk, 1/2 cup (equivalent to 2 eggs) Egg Beaters and 1/4 cup oil.
Stir until just slightly lumpy.
If batter is too thin, add more mix.

title: roxie dansby's shrimp cocktail sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients and chill overnight.

title: creole corn
directions: Fry bacon slices until they are crisp; remove from skillet. In the skillet, add the corn, green pepper, onion and garlic. Saute, then add tomatoes, catsup, A.1. sauce and sugar.
Shake in chili powder, Worcestershire sauce and salt and pepper to taste. Simmer on top of stove or in oven as long as you like, then crumble bacon on top when ready to serve.
May also be cooked in the microwave oven.

title: homemade chicken strips
directions: Cut chicken into strips 3 x 1 1/2-inches.
Season with salt and pepper.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Line cookie sheet with foil and spray with Pam.
Mix cornflake crumbs, onion powder and Mrs. Dash.
Individually dredge chicken strips with the cornflake mix after coating each piece with Egg Beaters.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes covered.
Continue baking uncovered for 10 minutes.

title: susan's broccoli casserole
directions: In large skillet, saute onion in margarine.
Add soup and Cheez Whiz and stir over low heat until creamy.
Mix rice and broccoli together and put in baking dish.
Pour cheese/soup mixture over top.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: banana split cake
directions: Place on top of pie filling.

title: mark's best chocolate chip cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
In large bowl, beat butter, Crisco, sugar and brown sugar until creamy.
Add eggs and vanilla; beat until light and fluffy.
Stir together flour, baking soda and salt; beat into butter mixture.
Stir in chocolate chips.
Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes until lightly browned.
Cool slightly; remove from cookie sheet to wire rack.
Cool completely.

title: deep dish fudge
directions: Place in a big bowl the chips, Hershey bar, marshmallow cream, butter, nuts and vanilla.
Boil in a saucepan the sugar and evaporated milk.
Boil 5 minutes.
Pour over the mixture in bowl. Pour all fudge in a buttered 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Refrigerate.

title: nut cake
directions: Cream margarine.
Add sugar gradually, then add eggs and vanilla.
Sift together flour, soda, baking powder and salt.
Add to other ingredients alternately with buttermilk.
Mix well and then add nuts.
Pour in greased and floured cake pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes or until done.

title: crunchy chicken breasts
directions: Butter a shallow casserole dish.
Break chicken into bite-size pieces.
Layer in casserole dish: chicken, celery, water chestnuts, soup mixture and mayonnaise, mixed together.
Dot with a little butter and paprika.
Bake for 45 minutes at 350°.
Serves 8.

title: chicken fricassee
directions: Flour chicken and brown in skillet.
Drain fat.
Put chicken into baking dish.
Combine soup, evaporated milk, onion, soy sauce and flour to thicken.
Simmer 5 to 10 minutes.
Pour over chicken breasts.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.
Serve with rice.

title: million dollar cake
directions: Cream sugar and oleo until white.
Add eggs, one at a time. Add milk, nuts and coconut.
Bake in Bundt cake pan in 300° oven for 1 hour.

title: moist chocolate cake
directions: Mix together oleo, eggs, sugar and cocoa.
Add dry ingredients, then sour milk and water.
Bake at 350°.
A very good and moist cake.

title: broccoli bread
directions: Beat eggs; add margarine, onion, cottage cheese, broccoli and salt.
Stir in cornbread; mix well.
Pour into greased 7 x 11-inch pan.
Bake at 400° for 25 to 30 minutes or until done in the center.

title: beef and biscuit casserole
directions: Brown hamburger and onion. Add green pepper, tomato sauce, chili powder and garlic salt. Simmer 15 minutes. Remove from heat and cool slightly. Add 1 cup cheese, 2 beaten eggs and sour cream. Line bottom of 9 X 13 pan with 1 can of biscuits (separated). Pour hamburger mixture over biscuits. Top with remaining can of biscuits. Spread 1 cup of cheese over top of biscuits. Bake at 350° about 1/2 hour of until biscuits are brown.

title: famous wesson oil fruit cake
directions: Heat oven to 275°.
Line pans with lightly greased brown paper.
Combine oil, sugar and eggs.
Beat 2 minutes in large bowl.
Combine 1 cup of flour with nuts and fruits.
Sift remaining flour with baking powder, salt and spices.
Stir into Wesson oil mixture alternately with orange juice.
Pour batter over fruit mixture; blend well.
Turn into prepared pans.
Place a pan of water on lower oven rack.
Bake cake 2 1/2 to 3 hours or until done.
Cool on wire racks.
Remove from pans; peel off paper.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients together; spoon drop onto a cookie sheet. Bake at 325° for 15 minutes.

title: mexican meat loaf
directions: Brown ground beef, onion, and green pepper. Drain well. Mix with soups and taco sauce. Simmer for 2 1/2 hrs. Pour into casserole dish and cover with Doritos. Top with cheese. Bake at 250° for 20 minutes or until cheese is melted.

title: ritz cookies
directions: Spread peanut butter between Ritz crackers, making little sandwiches.
In a double boiler melt chocolate almond bark.
Dip peanut butter crackers in melted crackers and set on wax paper to cool.

title: oatmeal cream filled cookies
directions: Cream margarine and sugars.
Add vanilla and eggs, one at a time.
Stir flour, salt and soda together and add to mixture.
Add oatmeal last.
Bake 15 minutes at 300°, 1 tablespoon batter for each cookie.

title: poverty cake
directions: Cook the first 4 ingredients.
Cool and add the remaining ingredients.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes or until done.

title: bouillon rice
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: cheese ball
directions: Add all ingredients, except pecans, starting with cheese, until well blended. Roll into ball, then roll in chopped pecans. Refrigerate until hard. Serve with crackers.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Cut broccoli flowerets in small pieces.
Saute bacon until crisp.
Cut onion into slices and then into julienne strips. Combine broccoli, bacon, onion and raisins in large bowl.
In a small bowl, whisk together mayonnaise, sugar, vinegar and pepper. Combine dressing with vegetables and refrigerate for at least 2 hours before serving, mixing once during this time.
Top with 1/2 cup toasted sunflower seeds if desired.

title: cracklin' bread
directions: Break cracklins
into
small
pieces.
Over
these pour boiling water and let
stand
10 minutes.
Then pour them with the water into corn
meal.
Add
more
water
to the dough, if needed. Add a little salt.
Shape the dough into small pones. Bake in a lightly
greased iron skillet in hot oven (400°) for 45 minutes or less.

title: laura's peanut butter incredibles
directions: Melt margarine in large bowl and add peanut butter.
Stir until smooth.
Add sugar and graham cracker crumbs.
Stir until well blended.
Press crumb mixture into a buttered jelly roll pan or 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.

title: apple cake
directions: Combine apples with sugar. Add oil and vanilla to eggs.
Mix together dry ingredients.
Add to egg mixture, alternating with apples.
Pour in a 9 x 13-inch greased pan. Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: easy cherry-nut bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease 10 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
In large mixing bowl, stir together sugar, egg, milk, nuts and cherries.
Add biscuit mix; beat briskly 30 seconds (just count to 30).
Turn into pan.
Bake 45 to 50 minutes or until done.
(There will be a slight crack in top.) Cool slightly before slicing.

title: crispy oatmeal cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Grease cookie sheets.
Mix in bowl oatmeal, brown sugar, flour and salt.
Stir in melted butter.
Add slightly beaten egg and vanilla.
Blend well.
Arrange by half teaspoons at least 2 inches apart on cookie sheets or baking pan. Bake until lightly browned, about 7 minutes.
Cool slightly.
As soon as firm enough, remove from pans.
Yields 90 cookies.

title: chicken tetrazzini
directions: Heat chicken broth; stir flour and whipping cream together until there are no lumps.
Add milk to this mixture and pour into chicken broth.
Add shredded cheese and stir over low heat until cheese is melted.
Add seasonings to taste and stir in chicken. Pour over cooked noodles in casserole dishes.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.
Makes two 9 x 13-inch pans.

title: mixed vegetable casserole
directions: Butter a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour in vegetables.
In a dish or bowl, mix the celery, bell pepper, onions, mayonnaise and cheese. Pour over vegetables.
Crush 1 sleeve of Premium crackers. Sprinkle over casserole and slice 1 stick oleo over crackers and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: chocolate fudge cake
directions: Cream butter.
Gradually add sugar, beating well.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each.
Add chocolate; mix well. Add vanilla.
Combine flour, soda and salt; gradually add alternately with sour cream, beating well after each addition. Add water carefully; mix well (batter will be very thin).
Pour into greased and floured 9-inch cake pans (round).
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes, or until cake bounces back at the touch.

title: meat casserole
directions: Brown beef, onion and green pepper.
Add remaining ingredients, except cheese.
Place in large, flat pan.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Refrigerate overnight to let all flavors blend. Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.

title: pear and pineapple jam
directions: Mix all together and cook until thick. Remove from heat and put in jam jars and seal.

title: midnight lace walnut tart
directions: Prepare Orange Tart Shell.
In a large bowl using a wire whisk, lightly beat eggs and sugar.
Stir in remaining ingredients except chocolate; mix well.
Place tart shell in pan on a baking sheet.
Pour egg mixture into shell; don't let filling spill over sides.
Bake in lower third of preheated 350° oven for 30 minutes. Raise tart on baking sheet to center of oven.
Continue baking 15 minutes or until filling just puffs and center feels firm.
Cool completely on a wire rack.
Unmold tart onto serving plate.

title: baked chicken salad
directions: Combine chicken and next 8 ingredients in bowl; mix well. Spoon into greased 9 x 13-inch inch baking dish.
Sprinkle with almonds.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes or until bubbly.

title: 60-minute clover rolls
directions: In a large mixing bowl, combine 1 1/2 cups flour, sugar, yeast and salt. Heat milk, water and butter until very warm (120° to 130°). Add to dry ingredients; beat 2 minutes, scraping bowl occasionally. Add 1/2 cup flour; beat 2 minutes, scraping bowl occasionally. Stir in enough remaining flour to form a soft dough. Place in a greased bowl, turning once to grease top. Cover bowl; place bowl in a pan filled with 98° water. Let rise 15 minutes. Turn onto a floured surface. Shape dough into 24 balls and place in well-greased muffin cups. With kitchen shears, cut each ball in half, then into quarters, cutting through almost to the bottom of rolls. Cover and let rise 15 minutes. Bake at 425° for 12 minutes or until golden brown. Remove from baking pans; cool on wire rack. Yield: 2 dozen.

title: venison roast
directions: Place in greased roasting pan.
Add salt and pepper to taste. Cover the entire roast with bacon and sprinkle with basil leaves. Cook 3 1/2 hours at 300°.

title: fruit dip
directions: Mix together until smooth and creamy; chill until hardened. Serve with fresh fruit; especially good with strawberries.

title: baked corn
directions: Combine all ingredients; mix well.
Pour into buttered 2-quart casserole.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: easy sticky buns
directions: Sprinkle nuts in a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Put frozen rolls over them.
Sprinkle pudding powder over rolls.
Pour melted butter over, then brown sugar mixed with cinnamon.
Cover and let rise overnight.
Bake in 350° oven for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: batter bread
directions: Sprinkle yeast on warm water.
Stir until dissolved.
Add shortening, salt, sugar and 1 1/2 cups of flour.
Let rise until 1-inch from top of pan (about 40 minutes).
Bake 45 to 50 minutes at 375°.

title: cherry dump cake
directions: Spread pineapple in bottom of a 9 x 13-inch glass pan.
Spread pie filling on top of pineapple. Sprinkle dry cake mix on top of pie filling.
Pour melted butter on top of cake mix.
Bake at 325° for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: one-pan blueberry cobbler
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Melt margarine in an 11 x 7-inch baking pan.
Add milk, Bisquick and sugar.
Stir until smooth.
Drop spoonfuls of filling over batter.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes, until golden brown.
(The batter rises to the top as it bakes, forming a cake-like crust.)

title: squash casserole
directions: Slice squash and place in bottom of baking dish.
Saute onion in melted butter until tender.
Pour onion and butter over squash. Spread soup over squash.
Sprinkle cheese on top.
Crush crackers; sprinkle over cheese.
Bake at 350° until soup bubbles through, about 30 to 35 minutes.

title: southern chicken pecan log
directions: Place each breast half between pieces of wax paper and pound until thin.
Mix molasses and mustard.
Salt and pepper the chicken, then coat in the molasses mixture.
Roll in ground pecans.
Chill to set for 1 hour.
Heat olive oil in a skillet over medium heat.
Add chicken and cook until springy to the touch, about 5 to 6 minutes on each side.

title: chocolate yeast cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs and chocolate.
Add flour alternately with milk, mixing well.
Add vanilla and nuts.
Soften yeast in warm water and mix.
Add to batter and mix well.
Let stand, covered, overnight.
Add mixture of soda and water; mix very well.
Bake in a tube pan for 1 hour and 15 minutes at 325°.

title: jelly roll
directions: Sift together the flour, salt and baking powder and set aside.
In a medium bowl, beat the eggs until thick and lemon colored.
Add sugar a little at a time and the vanilla.

title: rhode island coffee milk drink
directions: Pour about 3 squirts of coffee syrup (chocolate syrup) into a glass and then add skim milk.

title: orange pie
directions: Mix milk with lemon juice; beat until thick.
Pour in Cool Whip; beat well.
Stir oranges and pecans into mixture.
Pour into crust; chill overnight.
Makes 2 pies.

title: punch for 50
directions: At least 24 hours before serving, mix all ingredients except sherbet together.
Refrigerate.
Add sherbet before serving.

title: flea fleeing dog biscuits(for your canine friends)
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Oil or grease several cookie sheets. Cut a template in the shape of a dog bone.

title: cream cheese frosting
directions: In a small bowl, combine ingredients.
Beat at low speed to mix; then at high speed to blend smoothly.
Makes 1 1/2 cups.

title: bean casserole
directions: Drain water from beans; drain liquid from mushrooms and add to Cheddar cheese soup.
Blend well.
Mix soup, mushrooms and beans. Put in casserole dish and cover with French fried onions.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until it's heated thoroughly.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Put broccoli in a baking dish.
Pour soup over top and put onion rings on top.
Bake in oven 20 minutes at 350°.

title: rice and black bean salad
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients in a large bowl.
Whisk together oil and lime juice in a small bowl.
Pour over rice mixture and toss to coat.
Season with salt and pepper.
Cover and refrigerate.

title: blueberry salad
directions: Dissolve jello with 3 cups boiling water and 1 cup pineapple juice.
Add blueberries and crushed pineapple.
Put in refrigerator to harden.

title: 7-up cake
directions: Cream together butter and sugar for 20 minutes.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add flour, lemon extract and 7-Up.
Pour into well-greased cake pan and bake at 325° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: cheesecake bites
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In medium saucepan over low heat, melt chips and butter until smooth.
Stir in graham cracker crumbs, reserving 1/3 cup for later use.
Press remaining mixture in 13 x 9-inch pan.

title: duggins bean soup
directions: Cook for 30 minutes or more.
Soup may be kept in refrigerator, covered, or may be frozen.

title: ultimate sugar cookies
directions: Combine sugar and shortening in large bowl.
Beat at medium speed of electric mixer until blended.
Add eggs, syrup and vanilla.
Beat until well blended and fluffy.
Combine flour, baking powder, baking soda and salt.
Add gradually to creamed mixture at low speed.
Mix until well blended.
Divide dough into 4 quarters.
Wrap each quarter of dough with plastic wrap. Refrigerate at least 1 hour.
Keep refrigerated until ready to use.
Heat oven to 375°.

title: cheesy corn
directions: Combine all ingredients. Mix well. Cover and cook on low for 4 hours.

title: pie crust(makes 2 crusts)
directions: Mix and roll like any other pie crust.

title: biscuits with cracklings
directions: Dissolve yeast in milk.
Add salt to flour, then work in cracklings as for pie crust.
Combine egg with sour cream and add to flour mixture with dissolved yeast.
Mix quickly.
Shape into ball and refrigerate a few hours.
Roll out on floured board and fold up like a handkerchief.
Chill.
Repeat rolling and folding and chill again, about 3 times.
Roll out on floured board to 1/2-inch thickness and cut with round cutter.
Place on greased cookie sheet.
Let raise until about double in size.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: green beans with roquefort and walnuts(makes 6 to 8 servings)
directions: Bring a saucepan of water to a boil.
Add the beans.
Simmer until crisp-tender, about 3 minutes.
Drain; rinse under cold water.
Drain again; set aside.

title: summer berry pie
directions: Mix berries in large bowl; pour into pastry shell.
Mix sugar and cornstarch in medium saucepan.
Gradually stir in water until smooth.
Stirring constantly, cook on medium heat until mixture comes to a boil.
Boil 1 minute.
Remove from heat.
Stir in gelatin until dissolved.
Cool to room temperature.
Pour over berries in pastry shell.

title: red potato salad
directions: Wash and cut potatoes in 3/4-inch dices (leave skins on).
Boil potatoes gently in lightly salted water until cooked, but firm. Drain potatoes and place in a large mixing bowl.
Pour vinegar, salt, Nature's Seasons and pepper over potatoes and toss to coat. Let potatoes sit uncovered for at least an hour unless you wish to serve the salad warm.
Dice onion and celery and add to potatoes. Coarsely chop 5 of the eggs and add to mix.
Add mayonnaise and gently mix well.
Slice last egg and place around top of salad. Garnish by lightly sprinkling with paprika and a few parsley leaves.

title: oatmeal banana cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In large bowl mash 3 bananas.
Add salad oil, oats, dates, nuts, vanilla and salt.
Drop by rounded tablespoonfuls onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes.

title: turkey quesadillas
directions: Spray pan with butter spray.
Brown tortilla shell until lightly golden.
Place turkey and cheese in shell and fold over. When tortilla is lightly golden, remove, cut into 3 sections and serve hot.
Delicious dipped in salsa.

title: indian relish(very old)
directions: Grind up onions, peppers and tomatoes.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cook all ingredients for 1/2 hour.
Start timing when you see it start to boil.
Place in sterile canning jars.

title: rice pilaf with peas
directions: Begin 40 minutes ahead of time.

title: hot chocolate mix
directions: Mix well and store in covered container.
Place 1/3 cup mix in cup and fill with hot water.

title: molasses sponge cake
directions: Mix all the ingredients together.
The last thing, add one cup of boiling water.
Bake at 350° to 375° for about 30 minutes. Watch it because molasses burns easily.
Stick knife in.
When it comes out clean,
it's done.

title: oven-fried sesame chicken
directions: Combine sesame seed, flour and pepper.
Dip chicken pieces into soy sauce; dredge in sesame mixture.

title: potato and coconut candy
directions: Mix all ingredients, except chocolate and paraffin.
Drop mixture by heaping teaspoonfuls onto waxed paper.
Roll into balls.
Chill 1/2 to 1 hour or until firm.
If mixture is too soft to form balls, chill before shaping.

title: gumdrop cake
directions: Mix sugar and butter.
Add egg yolks.
Sift and add dry ingredients.
Add potatoes.
Alternate, adding milk and flour.
Add cooked raisins and gumdrops.
Fold in well beaten egg whites.
Bake in a moderate oven, either in layer pans, or tube, 1 1/2 hours or until done.

title: one dish meal
directions: Place first 6 ingredients in buttered casserole dish in order shown.
Add salt and pepper.
Use the pan that was used to brown the meat to heat tomato soup and water.
When heated, pour over casserole.
Bake for 2 hours at 350°.

title: sausage casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine eggs, milk, dry mustard and salt.
Add cubed bread.
Fold in cheese and sausage.
Cook in a large rectangular flat uncovered casserole dish for 45 minutes to 1 hour.
(Watch for last 30 minutes for burning.)

title: honeyed cereal mix
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients; mix remaining ingredients.
Cook the brown sugar, honey, margarine or butter and cinnamon approximately 3 minutes until syrupy.
Pour syrup over cereal mixture and bake on cookie sheet at 325° for 20 to 25 minutes. Stir at least twice.
Cool on wax paper and store in tight container.

title: chocolate chip peanut butter brownies
directions: Cream butter and peanut butter.
Gradually add sugar, beating well.
Combine flour, baking powder and salt; add to creamed mixture, stirring well.
Stir in vanilla and chocolate chips. Pour batter in a greased 8 inch square pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cool and cut into squares.

title: butter almond coffee cake
directions: Place half of batter in pan.
Sprinkle evenly with half of nut-sugar mixture.
Top with remaining batter, then sprinkle with remaining nuts and sugar.
Bake until skewer inserted in center comes out clean, 45 to 55 minutes.
Melt 1/2 stick butter and drizzle evenly over warm cake in pan.
Unmold from pan when cool. Makes 1 large coffee cake.
Keeps well and may be frozen up to six months, either sliced, pieces or whole.

title: australian fish(servings:  4)
directions: Melt butter in skillet over low heat.
Add mushrooms and saute over medium heat until tender.
Rub oil over shallow 4-quart baking dish and sprinkle with grated cheese.
Place fish on cheese.
Sprinkle fish with salt and pepper.
Add onions and top with mushrooms.
Pour wine over fillets.
Bake at 450° for 20 minutes or until fish flakes.
Sprinkle with lemon juice and parsley.

title: super pork chops
directions: Season and brown pork chops in small amount of fat.
Top each pork chop with 1 slice of onion, 1 slice of lemon, 1 tablespoon brown sugar and 1 tablespoon catsup.
Add water.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour or until done.

title: asparagus casserole
directions: Layer first 5 ingredients in 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan. Melt together soup and Cheez Whiz. Pour over other layers and bake 1 to 1 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: japanese pasta
directions: Prepare pasta according to package directions; drain. In a nonstick skillet, saute the flank steak over high heat. If it begins to stick, add a little soy sauce, 1 tablespoon at a time. When the steak is cooked through, reduce the heat to medium-low and add the soy sauce, red bell pepper, carrots and the scallions. Increase heat to medium-high and cook 3 minutes. Toss with pasta and serve.

title: homemade cranberry sauce
directions: Wash cranberries.
Cover with water.
Cook about 10 minutes at slow boil.
Cranberries will "pop."
Strain through Foley food mill; sieve and turn to get thick pulp.
Add sugar and cinnamon. Slow boil and cook down to thicken.
Usually done when film forms on top.
Test by allowing small amount to cool on plate.
Slant plate to test for thickness.
Pour in jar.
Seal or refrigerate.

title: quick pizza
directions: Toast English muffins.
On each half, place pizza sauce, pepperoni and cheese.
Place in microwave for 2 to 3 minutes.

title: cheese roll
directions: Mix well.
Make a roll about 2 inches in diameter.
Roll in chili powder, wrap in wax paper and refrigerate.
Slice and serve.

title: cheese quiche squares
directions: Beat eggs 3 minutes.
Combine flour, baking powder and salt; add to eggs and mix well.
Stir in cheese and peppers.
Pour into a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Cut into squares.
Yields about 12 servings.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Cream butter and sugar well.
Add one egg at a time, beating well after each.
Sift dry ingredients twice.
Add flour and cream alternately and blend well.
Grease tube pan.
Bake at 300° for 1 1/4 hours.

title: greek cookies
directions: Put butter in mixer; add powdered sugar, then add egg.
When well blended, add flour, one cup at a time.
Knead real well. Keep kneading and add pecans, a few at a time.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: taco pie
directions: Brown and drain hamburger.
Add water and taco mix.
Simmer 5 to 10 minutes.
Line bottom of 13 x 9-inch baking dish with crescent rolls.
Put 1/2 of corn chips on rolls, then layer beef, sour cream and cheese.
Top with remaining chips.
Bake at 325° for 20 minutes or until rolls are brown.

title: fido's favorite treats(dog biscuits)
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
Grease cookie sheets.
In a large bowl, combine rolled oats, margarine and boiling water; let stand 10 minutes.
Stir in cornmeal, sugar, bouillon, milk, cheese and egg; mix well.

title: oven omelet
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Beat eggs, milk and salt.
Stir in meat, cheese and onion.
Pour into a greased baking dish (11 1/2 x 7 1/2-inch).
Bake, uncovered, for 40 to 45 minutes or until omelet is set and top is golden brown.
Makes 4 large or 6 medium servings.

title: oatmeal raisin cookies(low cholesterol)
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Grease baking sheet.
Combine Crisco, brown sugar, egg whites, milk and vanilla in large bowl.
Beat at medium speed for 1 1/2 minutes.
Scrape sides often.
Batter may appear slightly curdled.
Combine oats, flour, salt, baking soda and cinnamon in separate bowl.
Beat into mixture at low speed; stir in raisins.
Drop by tablespoon onto baking sheet.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 9 minutes.

title: haystacks
directions: Melt butterscotch pieces in a double boiler.
Add noodles and peanuts.
Stir until well coated.
Drop from teaspoon onto waxed paper to form small clusters.

title: orange glazed pork chops
directions: Dust pork chops lightly with salt and pepper, then dredge lightly in flour. Brown on both sides in oil. Combine orange juice, marmalade, sugar and vinegar; pour evenly over chops in skillet.
Cover and simmer for about 45 minutes or until meat is very tender.
Serve sauce spooned over each chop. Delicious!

title: zucchini stuffing casserole
directions: Cook zucchini in salt water until tender; drain.
Saute carrots
and
onions in margarine.	Stir in stuffing mix, soup and sour cream.
Add zucchini gently.	Put in buttered casserole and top with grated cheese or crumbs.
Bake at 350° about 40 minutes.

title: quick corn relish
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Serve as a relish or on a bed of lettuce as a salad.

title: beef stew casserole
directions: Put meat in casserole and cover with soups mixed with water. Bake in 350° oven 2 1/2 hours, 45 minutes before meat is done add cut up vegetables.

title: heavenly hash
directions: Mix first 7 ingredients in mixing bowl.
Pour into serving bowl, top with whipped cream and garnish with cherries.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Saute broccoli and onions in butter until tender.
Mix together broccoli mixture, rice and soup.
Put in casserole dish and sprinkle cheese on top.
Bake at 350°
for 30 minutes or until bubbly.

title: potato salad
directions: Cook potatoes.
Let cool and dice into small pieces.
Combine in the order given:
3 beaten eggs, sugar, flour, water and vinegar.
Boil until thick, stirring constantly.
When thick, add butter or margarine, salt and pepper.
Add to potatoes and diced vegetables.
Make day ahead; refrigerate.
Stir every couple of hours.
Serves 12.

title: cream of broccoli soup
directions: Cook broccoli in boiling water until tender, uncovered. Remove and mash broccoli in blender or food processor.
Add hot milk and 2 cups of broccoli water and bouillon.

title: graham cracker toffee
directions: Line cookie sheet with aluminum foil.
Then line with crackers, broken into fourths.
Bring the first 3 ingredients to a boil and cook 3 minutes.
Pour over the cookies and sprinkle with nuts. Bake at 350° for 8 minutes, no more.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Wash mushrooms.
Remove and discard stems.
Mix together remaining ingredients.
Pour mixture into mushroom caps at a slightly rounded level.
Place stuffed mushrooms on a cookie sheet and bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes, until mushrooms turn dark and are soft.
Serve warm.
Remaining mixture makes a great spread for crackers.

title: green chili pie
directions: Brown hamburger and set aside. Heat soup over medium heat and add cream cheese. Once cream cheese is melted add chopped green onions and green chilies. Line pie pan or rectangular pan with flour tortillas to cover bottom. Spoon soup mixture over tortillas. Crumble hamburger over soup. Sprinkle grated cheese over hamburger. Top with flour tortilla(s) torn in strips. Bake 20 minutes at 300.

title: zucchini rounds
directions: In mixing bowl, stir together biscuit mix, cheese and pepper. Stir in beaten eggs just until moistened.
Fold in zucchini.
Melt margarine in 10-inch skillet over medium heat.
Use 2 tablespoons mixture for each round and cook 2 to 3 minutes on each side, or until brown.
Makes 6 servings.

title: curried hamburger and rice
directions: Combine all ingredients in a casserole dish.
Cover.
Bake at 350°
for 1 hour.
Stir once while baking.
Serve with curried fruit and sour cream or yogurt.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Cream together butter and peanut butter.
Add sugars, and the rest of ingredients in the order listed.
Mix all together; chill dough.
Form into balls and flatten with fork.
Sprinkle with a little sugar.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: dirt pie (oreos)
directions: Mix pudding by directions and add other ingredients.
Crush Oreos and put on top.
Refrigerate.

title: lea's christmas wreath
directions: Place rolls on pizza pan with points out. Mix all ingredients and spoon onto rolls. Pull points over filling. Sprinkle with extra bell peppers. Bake at 350° until brown.

title: overnight breakfast casserole
directions: Use a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Place cubed bread on bottom of pan. Brown meat, put on bread.
Beat eggs.
Add seasonings and milk, pour over meat and bread.
Add mushroom soup.
Sprinkle cheese on top.
Refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Unroll crescent rolls and line a large cookie sheet, pressing dough together at edges.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
When cool, mix cream cheese, Miracle Whip, chopped onion and Hidden Valley dressing.
Spread on crust, then cover with chopped vegetables.
Press lightly into cheese mixture and top with shredded cheese.
Refrigerate.

title: preserves cake
directions: Mix first 10 ingredients in order given.
Add preserves, then black walnuts or other nuts.
Bake in well-greased tube pan at 300° for about 2 hours.

title: chicken and rice bake
directions: Cook chicken until browned.
Cook rice, then put in 9 x 13 pan. Mix cream of chicken soup in separate bowl. Place chicken on rice and pour soup evenly over ingredients. Layer vegetables and top with cheese or crackers.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: sun-dried tomato dip
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well with a fork. Yield: 1 1/2 cups.

title: lemony no bake cheesecake
directions: In small bowl, dissolve jello in boiling water; set aside. In medium bowl, with electric mixer, beat cream cheese until smooth; gradually beat in dissolved gelatin. Fold whipped topping into cheese mixture; spoon into crust. I put either strawberries or blueberries, sometimes both on top. I have also doubled recipe and put in 9 x 13 dish. You can also top with cherry pie filling instead of berries. Chill 4 hours or until firm.

title: date delight
directions: Combine dates, sugar and egg in a medium sauce or fry pan. Place over low heat and cook, stirring constantly until mixture bubbles and thickens. Remove from heat and stir in salt and vanilla.
Add cereal and nuts and mix slightly.
Shape into small balls and roll in coconut. Let stand until cool and firm.
Serves as cookie or candy. Make about 24 1 1/4 inch balls.

title: guilt free wickedly chocolate cake
directions: Boil water, stir in coffee and set aside to cool.
In mixing bowl, sift together flour, cocoa, soda, powder and salt.
Stir until blended well.
Add prunes (use every serid), vanilla, eggs and milk and stir just until blended.
Gently stir coffee into batter.

title: chicken parmigiana
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In shallow bowl, combine bread crumbs and 1/4 cup Parmesan cheese.
Place egg in another bowl and beat. Dip chicken in egg and coat with bread crumbs.
Heat olive oil in large skillet over medium-high heat.
Add chicken and saute 5 minutes on each side.
Remove to plate.

title: sugarless apple pie
directions: Mix corn starch and thawed apple juice in medium kettle.
Cook over medium heat until it begins to clear.
Stir in apples and cinnamon.
Pour into unbaked pie crust- top with crust.
Bake 35 to 45 minutes at 350 degrees.

title: orange coconut balls
directions: Mix wafers, oleo, orange juice and nuts together. Roll into small balls, then roll in coconut. Chill.

title: microwave broccoli casserole
directions: Cook onion and celery in margarine in microwave until tender. Prepare rice, then broccoli in microwave and mix ingredients. Return to microwave and cook on Medium about 15 minutes, covered.

title: jello delight
directions: In large mixing bowl, add Jell-O.
(Do not add water.) Use dry.
Mix the next 4 ingredients.
Chill before use.
Serves 7 to 10.

title: hurry up chicken
directions: Place chicken in baking dish.
Mix other ingredients and pour over chicken.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: butter tarts(makes 1 dozen)
directions: Combine all ingredients except raisins and mix well.
Put raisins in bottom of tart shells and then divide filling evenly between them.
Should be 2/3 full.
Bake on bottom shelf of oven at 425° for 15 minutes.
These should be runny.

title: *meatballs with gravy("chiofti cu culeas")
directions: Mix well the above ingredients and shape into 2-inch meatballs.
Fry in skillet with 2 tablespoons butter and save the drippings.

title: cheese and bacon potatoes
directions: Mix cheese and mayonnaise.
Stir in all ingredients; put in buttered 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle with bacon on top.
Bake for 50 minutes at 350°.

title: *peanut butter fudge
directions: Mix sugar, milk and butter.
Cook to soft ball stage.
Remove from heat and beat.
Add peanut butter and vanilla; beat vigorously until thick.
Pour into buttered pan and cut into squares.

title: pumpkin pie squares
directions: Combine flour, oats, 1/2 cup brown sugar and butter.
Mix until crumbly.
Press into ungreased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: butterfinger cake
directions: Break angel food cake in small pieces.
Crush candy between wax paper.
Mix by hand the egg yolks, butter and powdered sugar. Fold in Cool Whip.
Layer in pan the cake, filling and candy until you run out.

title: crescent roll lasagne
directions: Spread rolls on cookie sheet and pinch together.
Brown hamburger, sausage and onions together; drain.
Add spices and tomato paste.
Mix well.

title: apricot pecan balls
directions: In a bowl, stir together the vanilla wafers, pecans, 1/2 cup powdered sugar and apricots.
Stir in corn syrup and brandy. Using 1 level tablespoon for each cookie, shape mixture into balls.
Roll in remaining 1/4 cup powdered sugar.
Store in covered container.
Makes a lot of balls (3 dozen).

title: oatmeal cake
directions: Pour boiling water over oatmeal and oleo and let stand 20 minutes.
Mix eggs, brown sugar and white sugar and beat well. Add flour, cinnamon and baking soda and beat well.
Mix both mixtures together.
Pour in a greased and floured pan.
Bake 30 minutes at 300°.

title: earthquake cake
directions: Mix coconut and nuts. Press into a 9 x 13-inch baking pan. Blend cake mix according to package directions and pour over crust. Blend together cream cheese, powdered sugar and butter. Drop by spoonfuls on top of cake batter. DO NOT STIR! Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: crazy cake
directions: Sift dry ingredients into an ungreased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Level off with a fork.
Make 3 holes in the flour mixture; pour vinegar in one, salad oil in another and vanilla in the third.
Add water and mix with fork or spoon.
Do not beat but be sure it is well mixed.
Bake at 325° for 30 to 35 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean when tested.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients in a baking dish.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Cook until cheese is melted and turning brown.
Serve warm.

title: rainbow shrimp salad
directions: Split each shrimp lengthwise.

Combine shrimp, rice, celery, green pepper, onion, mayonnaise, salt and pepper; cover and chill. Before serving, spoon mixture onto lettuce; garnish with tomato wedges and, if desired, with whole shrimp.
Serve with lemon wedges and French dressing (optional).

title: strawberry bread
directions: Mix well. Turn into buttered and floured 10-inch tube pan. Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: salsa sauce
directions: Bring the first 9 ingredients to a boil.
Add the cornstarch mixture to the salsa to thicken.
Put into pint jars and process 15 minutes in a hot water bath.
Hot, but good!

title: jordan marsh blueberry muffins
directions: Mix together butter, sugar and eggs first.
Sift together flour, baking powder and salt and mix with first three ingredients.
Beat in milk.
Stir blueberries into mixture. Butter the top and inside of muffin tin.
Fill each tin to the top; sprinkle with sugar (can make 12 to 15 muffins).
Bake in 375° oven for 25 to 30 minutes.
Leave in pan for 30 minutes before removing.

title: ham and swiss casserole
directions: Cook and drain noodles.
Combine pepper, celery soup, sour cream and onion in bowl.
In greased 13x9x2-inch dish layer noodles, ham, cheese and soup mixture.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: sour cream potatoes
directions: Peel and dice potatoes.
Cook until tender.
Pour off water. Saute onion in margarine.
Add parsley. Cook slowly.
Add salt and pour over diced and cooked potatoes.
Fold in sour cream lightly. Top with cheese.
Bake at 350° until cheese melts.

title: tangy meat loaf
directions: In a large bowl combine catsup, brown sugar and mustard. Reserve 4 tablespoons for topping.
Add remaining ingredients except beef.
Mix well and let stand 5 minutes.
Add ground beef. Mix well.
Shape into a loaf.
Bake at 350° for 65 minutes. Spread on glaze.
Bake an additional 15 minutes.

title: pancake cookies
directions: Mix sugar, eggs and butter.
Add butter.
Slowly stir in sifted flour.
Add milk or water in small amounts until thick but mushy. Drop spoonfuls into greased and floured cookie sheet.
Bake at 350 - 375 until cookies bounce back when touched.

title: stir-fry
directions: In a wok or heavy frypan, heat on medium high heat.
Add oil and brown franks and sausage.
Remove and set aside.
Add rest of ingredients, except chicken broth.
Fry about 15 minutes, stirring frequently.
Add chicken broth and meat.
Cover with lid; simmer until tender.
Salt and pepper to taste.

title: cheesy potatoes
directions: Melt butter and cheese together.
Add salt.
Slowly add sour cream, stirring, over medium heat.
Peel potatoes.
Shred baked potatoes.
Stir in baked potatoes.
Put in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Dot with butter.
Bake for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: apricot bar cookies
directions: Cream margarine, sugar, flour, nuts and coconut.
Press 3/4 mixture in buttered cookie sheet.
Bake 10 minutes at 350°, then add preserves over crust.
Add 1 heaping tablespoonful flour to remaining mixture.
Crumble over preserves.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes.
Cut in bars.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Sift together flour, soda and salt.
In large bowl, cream together sugar, brown sugar, shortening, egg, peanut butter and vanilla.
Spoon on cookie sheet and cook at 375° until done.

title: cheese soup
directions: Saute over low heat onions, garlic and celery in a large saucepan.
Add flour and blend.
Add cheese, wine and milk; stir often.
Heat; but do not boil.

title: pineapple pasta refresher
directions: Cook pasta according to package directions; drain.
Rinse with cold water quickly; drain well.

title: cheese cake
directions: Mix crumbs and sugar.
Stir in melted margarine.
Press in bottom and sides of pie plate.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes. Cool.
Reduce oven temperature to 300°.
Beat cream cheese and sugar in a large bowl.
Add vanilla.
Beat in eggs, 1 at a time. Pour over crust and bake 1 hour or until center is firm.
Cool. Top with fruit or sour cream or keep plain.
Chill for 3 hours.

title: spaghetti with ricotta
directions: Cook spaghetti as directed on package.
Drain.
Turn into warm bowl, stir in melted butter.
Add Ricotta and toss gently to blend.
Sprinkle with grated cheese, salt and pepper.
Garnish with chopped parsley.
Yields 4 servings.

title: congo bars
directions: Combine light brown sugar, eggs, oil and vanilla in large bowl with mixer.
Add 1 cup flour and 1 tablespoon milk; mix thoroughly.
Add remaining flour and milk; mix well.
Fold in chips and nuts.
Bake in a greased and floured pan (9 x 13-inch) at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: creamed peas and potatoes
directions: Place potatoes in a sauce pan, cover with water and cook until tender.
Cook peas separately until done, add the sugar (do not over cook).
Meanwhile in sauce pan melt margarine, add salt, pepper, flour to form a paste.
Then slowly add milk.
Bring to a boil and boil 1 minute.
Cook until thick and bubbly.
Drain potatoes and peas.
Put together and pour sauce over all.
Stir to coat.
Serve immediately.

title: no-sugar cookies
directions: Stir with a wooden spoon until well mixed.
Put onto a greased cookie sheet.
Drop dough by tablespoons, 2 inches apart.
Bake 20 minutes at 375°.
Makes 2 1/2 dozen (80 calories).

title: round steak stew
directions: Cut steak into bite size pieces and place in large pot.
Add tomatoes and juice, soup, potatoes, onion and green beans.
Stir together well and bring to boil.
Add salt; reduce heat to low. Cook for 3 to 3 1/2 hours (until meat and potatoes are tender and gravy is thick).
Serve over egg noodles or rice.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix and roll into small balls.
Bake on a cookie sheet lined with a paper bag for 20 to 30 minutes at 350°.

title: italian meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients thoroughly.
Put in 2 small loaf pans or one large.
Bake covered in 375° oven for at least 1 hour.
Uncover to brown some.

title: hot spiced cider
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Simmer and cover for 20 minutes.

title: lazy peach cobbler
directions: Melt butter.
Combine melted butter and peaches in baking dish.
Mix sugar, flour and milk.
Stir well.
Pour this mixture over peaches and butter.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes. Makes its own crust.

title: barbecue beef
directions: Combine all ingredients, pour over meat in Dutch oven.
Cover tightly.
Bake at 300° for 6 hours.

title: mayonnaise cake
directions: Mix all dry ingredients together.
Beat in water, mayonnaise and vanilla.
Beat with mixer until smooth.
Lightly grease and flour 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Cool and use Cool Whip for topping.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Cream together sugar and flour with oleo.
Add eggs, vanilla and buttermilk.
Pour into unbaked pie shell and bake at 400° for 35 to 45 minutes.

title: carrot cake
directions: Blend eggs, sugar and oil.
Sift flour with soda and cinnamon. Add to egg mixture.
Fold in carrots and pecans.
Place in three 9-inch cake pans.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: apple torte
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Spread in greased pie plate.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: parisienne chicken
directions: Place cutlets in shallow baking dish.
In saucepan, mix all other ingredients.
Bring to boil, reduce and simmer for 5 minutes.
Pour sauce over chicken and bake, uncovered, at 450° for 15 minutes.
Reduce heat to 375° and bake for 45 minutes, or until tender.
Baste frequently.
Serves 6.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Cook and drain ground beef.
Add onion and salt.
Cook and drain macaroni.
In large bowl, mix spaghetti sauce, ground beef and macaroni.
Pour mixture into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Add pepperoni on top of mixture.
Add cheese.
Bake at 350° until cheese is golden brown.

title: easy flaky pastry
directions: Mix flour and salt; cut in Crisco.
Add water; mix and place on floured board.
Knead until dough sticks together.
Roll into crust.
Bake at 375° for about 10 to 15 minutes.
Makes 3 crusts.

title: pineapple casserole
directions: Mix sugar, flour, cheese and pineapple in a casserole dish. Place crackers on top.
Dribble butter over crackers.
Bake in a 350° oven for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: italian braised beef
directions: Dredge stew beef in flour and brown.
Drain canned mushrooms; set mushrooms aside and add reserved liquid to meat.
Add onion, Worcestershire sauce, water, oregano and basil to meat.
Cover tightly and cook slowly on low heat for 2 hours.
Add mushroom pieces and tomato sauce.
Continue cooking 45 minutes.
Cook macaroni; when tender, drain and add butter, Parmesan cheese and parsley.
In large bowl, pour sauce over macaroni.
Blend and eat!

title: church
directions: Mix pastor and people in large box.
Knead into followers of God.
Next, mix love, faith and prayer into bowl and stir, then blend in God.
Combine in 11 x 14-inch pan and bake it in the oven of life.

title: potatoes romanoff
directions: Combine cottage cheese, onion, salt and sour cream.
Fold in potatoes and pour into buttered casserole.
Top with cheese; sprinkle with paprika.
Bake for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: oyster cracker snacks
directions: Mix together Ranch dressing, dill weed, lemon pepper and garlic salt; set aside.
Pour hot oil over crackers and stir well. Sprinkle dry mixture over and mix well.

title: turtle fudge
directions: Combine sugar, margarine and evaporated milk in heavy 2 1/2 to 3-quart saucepan; bring to a full rolling boil, stirring constantly.
Boil 5 minutes over medium heat or until thermometer reaches 234°, stirring constantly to prevent scorching.
Remove from heat.
Add chocolate pieces and stir until melted.
Add remaining ingredients and heat until well blended.
Pour into a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Cool at room temperature and cut into squares. Makes 3 1/2 pounds.

title: homemade apple pie
directions: Place sliced apples in bottom of deep dish crust until well filled.
Cut up enough butter on top of apples to taste.
Mix together sugar, cinnamon and flour; pour on top of apples.
Place regular crust on top of deep dish pan and pinch crust together with fork.
Cut pieces of butter up on top of pie to make crust brown.
Bake at 400° until pie looks done, about 40 minutes.

title: crab cakes
directions: Mix all together with enough crumbs to hold together.
Shape into patties.
Roll in extra crumbs and deep fry (moderate temperature) until light brown.

title: king ranch chicken casserole
directions: After boiling chicken and letting cool, make long bite sized strips with chicken.
Put ingredients except cheese and tortillas in large bowl; mix well.

title: peach pie alaska
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Add ice cream by spoonfuls. Stir until melted and smooth.
Blend in whipped topping and fruit. Chill, if necessary, until mixture will mound.
Spoon into crust. Chill until set (about 3 hours) or freeze until firm.
Garnish with peach slices.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Whip the cream cheese until soft and fluffy. Add sugar and peanut butter, then slowly add milk.
Fold in Cool Whip and pour into cooled pie crust.
Freeze 5 to 6 hours.
Let set at room temperature about 15 minutes before serving.

title: cheesy chicken casserole
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Pour stuffing mix into greased, shallow, 2-quart casserole.
Mix cheese, chicken, diced peppers and flour in a large bowl.
Spoon over stuffing mix.
Beat eggs in same large bowl; stir in milk and pepper.
Pour over cheese mixture.

title: morning glory muffins
directions: Process oil, eggs, sugar and vanilla in food processor, until well blended, about 30 seconds.
Add carrot, apple and remaining ingredients.
Pulse blender until combined.
Do not overprocess. Spoon batter into 12 cup muffin pan.
Bake in preheated 375° oven about 20 minutes.

title: mother's fruit bars
directions: Grease and flour baking pans.
Spread 2 cups pecans in bottom of 2 (9 x 13-inch) baking pans.
Make a batter by mixing butter, sugar, eggs, vanilla and flour.
Pour this carefully over nuts. Do not mix nuts into batter.
Sprinkle 1/2 cup nuts and fruit over batter.
Bake 1 hour at 300°.
Cut while hot into small squares. Cool in pans.
Remove and store in airtight container.
They freeze well.

title: roman holiday bake
directions: In skillet, brown beef and cook sausage, onion and oregano until done.
Stir to separate meat.
Pour off fat.
Add soups and water and mix.
Set aside.
Cook noodles as directed and drain. In separate containers refrigerate meat mixture and noodles overnight.
Combine meat mixture and noodles and pour in 2 qt. shallow baking dish (12 x 8 x 2) and cover.
Place in cold oven. Bake at 400 degrees for 40 minutes.
Stir.
Top with cheese and bake until cheese melts.

title: coconut caramel dessert
directions: Mix the flour, 3/4 cup
softened butter and 3/4 cup chopped pecans and pat in a 9 x
13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: endive stuffed with cheese
directions: Separate endive leaves, wash and chill in cold water for 10 minutes to crisp them.
Mash cheeses until well blended; fold in pecans.
Dry leaves and fill with mixture.
Decorate with watercress, chopped tomatoes or a pinch of caviar.
Makes 48.

title: chicken and rice casserole with cornflakes
directions: Stew chicken in about 4 cups water.
Remove chicken from bone and cut into pieces.
Cook rice in chicken broth.
This rice will need to be kind of juicy, not too dry.

title: barbecued shrimp
directions: In a 2-quart saucepan, heat butter and oil.
Add Worcestershire sauce, pepper, lemons, Tabasco, Italian seasoning, garlic, paprika and salt.
Mix thoroughly.
Simmer 5 to 7 minutes. Divide shrimp between 2 Dutch ovens and pour sauce over each. Cook 6 to 8 minutes, or until shrimp begin to turn pink.
Bake for 10 minutes, turning shrimp once.
Serve with French bread for dipping.
Serves 8.

title: chili con queso
directions: Brown ground beef, onion and bell pepper.
Drain.
Add chunks of cheese on low heat until it melts.
Add garlic powder and chopped tomatoes with chilies.
Heat thoroughly.
Serve warm as chip and dip with Mexican tortilla chips.

title: chocolate zucchini loaf
directions: Stir all ingredients together.
Beat till well mixed.
Pour into 3 loaf pans or 13 x 9 cake pan.
Sprinkle top with chocolate chips.
Bake 45-50 minutes at 350°.

title: peanut butter pinwheels
directions: Mix together sugar, butter, vanilla, salt and enough milk to moisten.
Mix until real smooth and creamy.
Divide in half.
Roll each piece about 1/4-inch thick in an oblong shape in between sheets of wax paper.

title: sticky gooey cake
directions: Mix and pat first 3 ingredients in a 13 x 9-inch greased pan. Mix next four ingredients and pour over cake. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: glarch(resembles gak)
directions: Mix glue and food coloring in disposable pint container and stir.
Knead mixture on a paper covered surface until smooth (couple of minutes).
If it sticks to your hands, add a teaspoon of starch.
If too stringy, add 1/3 teaspoon glue.
This does not store well.

title: chicken rice casserole
directions: Wash chicken; pat dry.
Heat 4 tablespoons butter and oil in large skillet over medium heat.
Brown chicken well on all sides. Remove chicken from pan; add onion, green pepper and garlic to pan.
Saute until golden brown.
Add rice; cook 2 minutes.
Add chicken broth, bay leaf, salt and pepper; bring to boil.
Grease 2 quart casserole.
Pour in rice mixture; top each chicken.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Cook tomatoes in 1 tablespoon butter; place on chicken.
Sprinkle cheese.
Bake 15 minutes.

title: slice and bake oatmeal cookies
directions: Combine flour, sugar and shortening.
Mix well.
Beat in eggs and vanilla.
Add flour, mixing well.
Stir in oatmeal and nuts. Mix mixture and make roll.
Put in wax paper and freeze.
Then slice and bake at 375° for 6 to 10 minutes.
Makes 6 dozen.

title: janessa's broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli and onions until tender.
Drain and pour into casserole dish.
Add cheese, cream of mushroom soup and egg.
Mix together until blended evenly.
Cook for 1 hour at 350 degrees until the top is golden brown.
Crush up Ritz crackers and sprinkle on top.

title: hunter's lima bean dinner
directions: Wash dried limas and cover with water.
Add salt and onion powder to taste.
Bring to a boil.
Remove from heat and let set for 1 hour.
Add sausages and bring to a boil again.
Lower heat and simmer covered for 1 to 2 hours until beans are tender, stirring only once or twice.
Frequent stirring causes beans to loose shape and turn to mush.

title: carrot relish
directions: Grind carrots in vegetable chopper as fine as possible.
Grind up lemon in fine pieces (including some rind).
Add to ground carrots.
Add 3/4 to 1 cup sugar.
Refrigerate for about 1 hour. Serves 10 to 12.
Also can be added to lemon jello (lots of Vitamins A and C).

title: wheat germ zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs. Add oil, sugars and maple flavoring.
Stir in zucchini.
In separate bowl, combine dry ingredients. Add to zucchini mixture. Stir in nuts.
Pour into greased and floured loaf pans. Bake at 350° for 50 minutes, or until tests done with toothpick. Makes 2 loaves.

title: cherry pudding dessert
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Refrigerate well before serving.

title: hush puppiesgroves, texas
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients.
Stir in egg and milk.
Let stand a few minutes.
Then stir again.
Drop by heaping tsp. into hot fat and fry 5 minutes or until browned and cooked through, turning once or twice.
Makes about 18.

title: chess pie
directions: Mix all ingredients well; pour in pie shell.
Cook at 350° until pie is done.

title: coconut frosting
directions: Beat cream cheese.
Blend in sugar, milk and extract.
Fold in whipped topping and coconut.
Makes about 4 cups or enough to frost tops and sides of 2 (8 or 9-inch) cake layers or a 13 x 9-inch cake.

title: lemon chess bars
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients together and press in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix the remaining ingredients and pour over cake mix.
Bake 55 minutes at 325°.
Let cool and cut into squares.

title: spaghetti with sausage
directions: This recipe is a snap and if you like spicy food, you will love this!

title: cabbage soup
directions: Cut up cabbage into bite size pieces.
Add to large pot of boiling water.
Chop up the onions and add along with the tomatoes.
Cut up celery and add with onion soup mix.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
When the cabbage is almost done, add the small can of mushrooms.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Boil chicken.
Let cool and debone.
Saute celery and onion in butter until tender.
Add cream of chicken soup, milk and mushrooms.
Simmer for 5 minutes.
Add cheese and chicken.
Drain boiled noodles.
Simmer sauce an additional 15 minutes.
Pour sauce over noodles.

title: cranberry waldorf
directions: Grind cranberries. Combine with marshmallows and sugar. Cover and chill overnight. Add apples, grapes, pecans and salt. Fold in Cool Whip (2 cups or more). Chill. Serve in large bowl or individual lettuce cups. Garnish with clusters of green and red grapes, if desired. Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: grandma hills rolls
directions: Scald milk; let cool and add yeast.
Add rest of ingredients except last flour.
Let rise for 1 hour.
Knead flour into mixture. Let rise until double in size; knead down.
Rest for 10 minutes. Shape into rolls.
Place in greased pan.
Bake at 350°. (Cloverleaf for 12 to 15 minutes and Parker House for 20 to 25 minutes.)

title: sausage and rice casserole
directions: Brown sausage in frying pan and pour off grease.
Add chopped onion, garlic and green pepper to sausage and simmer until tender. Wash rice several times to remove starch.
Add to mixture in baking dish along with the soups and water.
Bake 1 to 1 1/2 hours at 350°, stirring occasionally.
Serves 6.

title: vegetable bars
directions: Lay crescent rolls flat on pan and bake for 10 minutes at temperature given on package.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Mix all ingredients, alternating moist and dry ingredients. Pour into cake pans. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: fresh peach pie
directions: Mix sugar, cornstarch, salt, white syrup and water and bring to a boil. Cook until thick and clear. Add the peach jello. Cool thoroughly. Peel and slice the peaches and add to filling. Put in the crust. Refrigerate.

title: creamy chicken and vegetable casserole
directions: Bone, skin and split chicken breasts.
Melt butter.
Saute mushrooms, peppers and onions 3 minutes.
Stir in spinach; cook 2 minutes.
Remove from heat; add soup, sour cream, paprika and pepper.
Mix well.

title: chicken florentine
directions: Thaw spinach souffles; spread over the bottom of a 9 x 13-inch casserole dish sprayed with Pam.
Place chopped chicken on top of spinach.

Combine mayonnaise, cream of mushroom soup, water chestnuts, onion, parsley and Parmesan cheese; pour over chicken. Combine Ritz crackers and butter; sprinkle on top of casserole. Bake at 325° for 50 minutes.
Serves 8 to 10.
Great served with browned rice and a congealed salad.

title: golden sunbeam cake
directions: Beat yolks until fluffy.
Add remaining ingredients, using mixer on low speed.
Beat no more than necessary.
Bake in ungreased pan for one hour at 350°.

title: apple chip cake
directions: Mix in large bowl the ingredients in order given.
Batter will be stiff.
Bake in greased and floured pan approximately 45 minutes at 325°.
Serve with whipped cream.

title: snickerdoodles
directions: Mix ingredients well. Make into balls and roll in 1 teaspoon cinnamon and 1 tablespoon sugar. Bake at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: coconut filling
directions: Combine milk, sugar, butter, flour and vanilla in a saucepan. Cook, stirring constantly, over medium heat until thickened, about 12 minutes. Remove from heat. Stir in coconut and pecans.
Beat until thickened and cooled.
Yields enough to fill and top one 3 layer cake.

title: best ever italian salad
directions: Make your salad by placing tomatoes, black olives, green olives, yellow pepper, lettuce, broccoli and the beans in a large bowl.
In another bowl, add Parmesan cheese, Dijon mustard and the wine vinegar; whisk together.
Add olive oil, a small amount at a time, whisking constantly.
Add parsley and basil; mix well.
Add lemon juice, salt and pepper.
Pour dressing over salad; toss until evenly coated.
Add the sliced eggs.
Toss all together. Makes 6 servings.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar; beat well, add eggs one at a time.
Add flour a little at a time and milk, beating after each addition. Add vanilla and beat well.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 20 minutes.

title: green peas au gratin
directions: Cook peas using package directions.
Drain well.
Combine peas, water chestnuts and soup; mix gently.
Stir in cheese. Place in lightly greased casserole.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes until bubbly.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Mix everything together and roll the dough into balls. Refrigerate.

title: hungarian goulash
directions: Cut beef steak into small pieces. Melt butter in heavy pan; add steak and onions.
Saute until onions are transparent.
Add paprika, garlic, lemon peel, caraway seed, stewed tomatoes, beef stock and egg noodles.
Thicken with flour.
Cook noodles separately, then add to all other ingredients.
Low simmer for 45 minutes.

title: banana muffins
directions: Sift first 4 ingredients. Stir in bran. Combine egg, bananas, milk and oil. Add all at once to dry ingredients, stirring just to moisten. Fill well greased muffin pans 2/3 full. Bake 400° for 20-25 minutes. Makes 1 dozen.

title: layered lettuce salad
directions: Tear lettuce and make a thick layer in bottom of dish. Sprinkle chopped celery and onion on top of lettuce.
Drain peas and pour over layer.
Add a thick layer of mayonnaise.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese thickly.
Top with bacon.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: breakfast sausage(also good as lunch sausage)
directions: Brown sausage, drain well.
Put milk, eggs, salt and mustard into bowl.
Add bread cubes, cheese and sausage.
Pour into baking dish (7 x 11 inches or 8 x 12).
Refrigerate overnight.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.
Let stand a few minutes before serving.
Serves 8.

title: applesauce drop cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Sift together flour, baking soda, salt, cinnamon and nutmeg; set aside.
In the large bowl of an electric mixer, using the "cream" setting, beat butter and gradually add the sugars.
Beat until light and fluffy.
Add egg and beat until blended.
Reduce speed to low and add the applesauce and sifted dry ingredients.
Beat just until all ingredients are blended together, using a rubber spatula to scrape down the sides.
Remove from the mixer and stir in the oats, raisins, nuts and chocolate. Drop dough by tablespoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheets about 1 inch apart.
Bake 8 minutes; remove from cookie sheets to cool. Makes 5 dozen.

title: chicken hawaiian
directions: In skillet, brown chicken in shortening; pour off fat.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cover; simmer 30 minutes or until done. Makes 4 servings.

title: "philly" cheese ball
directions: Combine cheese food, cream cheese and margarine; mix until well blended. Add remaining ingredients; mix well.
Mold into 2 balls.
May be rolled in chopped pecans or black pepper.
Chill until firm.

title: white chocolate trash
directions: In large bowl mix peanuts, pretzel sticks, Crispix and Corn and Rice Chex cereal.
Melt in microwave white chocolate chips and cooking oil.
Pour melted chips and oil over other mixture in bowl; mix well.
Lay out 2 widths of waxed paper on table.
Spray with Pam.
Spread mixture out in a single layer and let cool.
Put in gallon Ziploc bag and enjoy.

title: raw apple nut pound cake
directions: Mix oil, sugar and eggs with electric mixer.
Sift flour, salt and soda together and add to the mixture; mix well.
Fold in apples, walnuts, coconut and raisins by hand.
Batter will be thick.
Bake 1 hour and 20 minutes at 350° in tube pan.

title: peanut butter rice krispie squares
directions: Mix sugar and stir over heat until it dissolves, then add peanut butter.
Stir until smooth.
Add Rice Krispies and then put in buttered pan; press down.

title: friendship tea mix
directions: Optional:
Add extra package apricot jello for more flavor.

title: zucchini rice with sausage
directions: Brown sausage.
Push to one side and remove all but 2 Tbsp. fat.
Add rice, zucchini and onion.
Cook and stir until slightly browned.
Stir in tomato, water, mustard, salt and pepper.
Bring to a boil.
Cover and simmer 5 minutes.
Stir in cheese.
Heat to melt cheese.
Serves 4.

title: peppermint punch
directions: Blend 3 pints softened ice cream with all milk.
Add extract and few drops of coloring.
Gradually add 7-Up and stir gently. Stir in remaining ice cream.

title: quick cherry dessert
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs; beat until fluffy.
Add the almond extract.
Stir in flour and baking powder; mix until smooth.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Cook sweet potatoes until tender; mash. Add melted butter, sugar and flavoring.
Beat eggs and Eagle Brand milk.
Put in unbaked pie shell.
Bake 10 minutes in 400° oven.
Turn to 300°, bake 30 minutes.

title: seafoam
directions: Boil sugar, syrup and water until it forms a hard ball in the water.
Beat whites and salt, using an electric beater on high speed for 3 minutes in a large bowl.
Pour syrup slowly into beaten egg whites, beating constantly until the mixture passes the glossy stage; add vanilla.
Continue to beat until the mixture forms peaks when beaters are raised.
Drop on waxed paper by spoons and let harden.

title: fresh cauliflower salad
directions: Mix together cauliflower and raisins and set aside. Fry bacon until crisp and remove from fat.
Fry onion in bacon fat until crispy brown. Drain fat.
Mix crisp bacon and onion with cauliflower and raisins. Mix Miracle Whip with sugar and salt. Mix Miracle Whip into bacon mixture.

title: banana-apple cake
directions: Spray glass pan with Pam.
Mix oil, sugar, egg and all other ingredients.
Place mixture in glass dish and bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: scalloped potato casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients except butter and corn.
Place in a 2-quart casserole.
Pour butter over top.
Sprinkle corn flakes over all.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
For small servings, bake in two (1-quart) casseroles.
Serve one and freeze the other for later.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Cook macaroni according to directions; drain and add butter. Set aside and when cool, add eggs.
Brown hamburger with onion and green pepper; add flour, sugar and oregano, the garlic powder and tomato sauce.
